12 /** \class TCling
13 
14 This class defines an interface to the cling C++ interpreter.
15 
16 Cling is a full ANSI compliant C++-11 interpreter based on
17 clang/LLVM technology.
18 */

233 R__DLLEXPORT void TCling__DEBUG__printName(clang::Decl* D) {
234  if (clang::NamedDecl* ND = llvm::dyn_cast<clang::NamedDecl>(D)) {
235  std::string name;
236  {
237  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(name);
238  ND->getNameForDiagnostic(OS, D->getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy(),
239  true /*Qualified*/);
240  }
241  printf("%s\n", name.c_str());
242  }
243 }

262  static const std::string gInterpreterClassDef = R"ICF(
263 #undef ClassDef
264 #define ClassDef(name, id) \
265 _ClassDefInterp_(name,id,virtual,) \
266 static int DeclFileLine() { return __LINE__; }
267 #undef ClassDefNV
268 #define ClassDefNV(name, id) \
269 _ClassDefInterp_(name,id,,) \
270 static int DeclFileLine() { return __LINE__; }
271 #undef ClassDefOverride
272 #define ClassDefOverride(name, id) \
273 _ClassDefInterp_(name,id,,override) \
274 static int DeclFileLine() { return __LINE__; }
275 )ICF";

278 #define __ROOTCLING__ 1

280 #define ClassDef(name,id) \
281 _ClassDefOutline_(name,id,virtual,) \
282 static int DeclFileLine() { return __LINE__; }
283 #undef ClassDefNV
284 #define ClassDefNV(name, id)\
285 _ClassDefOutline_(name,id,,)\
286 static int DeclFileLine() { return __LINE__; }
287 #undef ClassDefOverride

289 _ClassDefOutline_(name,id,,override)\

293 // The macros below use ::Error, so let's ensure it is included
294  static const std::string gClassDefInterpMacro = R"ICF(
295 #include "TError.h"
296 
297 #define _ClassDefInterp_(name,id,virtual_keyword, overrd) \
298 private: \
299 public: \
300  static TClass *Class() { static TClass* sIsA = 0; if (!sIsA) sIsA = TClass::GetClass(#name); return sIsA; } \
301  static const char *Class_Name() { return #name; } \
302  virtual_keyword Bool_t CheckTObjectHashConsistency() const overrd { return true; } \
303  static Version_t Class_Version() { return id; } \
304  static TClass *Dictionary() { return 0; } \
305  virtual_keyword TClass *IsA() const overrd { return name::Class(); } \
306  virtual_keyword void ShowMembers(TMemberInspector&insp) const overrd { ::ROOT::Class_ShowMembers(name::Class(), this, insp); } \
307  virtual_keyword void Streamer(TBuffer&) overrd { ::Error("Streamer", "Cannot stream interpreted class."); } \
308  void StreamerNVirtual(TBuffer&ClassDef_StreamerNVirtual_b) { name::Streamer(ClassDef_StreamerNVirtual_b); } \
309  static const char *DeclFileName() { return __FILE__; } \
310  static int ImplFileLine() { return 0; } \
311  static const char *ImplFileName() { return __FILE__; }
312 )ICF";

375 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
376 /// Update TClingClassInfo for a class (e.g. upon seeing a definition).
377 
378 static void TCling__UpdateClassInfo(const NamedDecl* TD)
379 {
380  static Bool_t entered = kFALSE;
381  static vector<const NamedDecl*> updateList;
382  Bool_t topLevel;
383 
384  if (entered) topLevel = kFALSE;
385  else {
386  entered = kTRUE;
387  topLevel = kTRUE;
388  }
389  if (topLevel) {
390  ((TCling*)gInterpreter)->UpdateClassInfoWithDecl(TD);
391  } else {
392  // If we are called indirectly from within another call to
393  // TCling::UpdateClassInfo, we delay the update until the dictionary loading
394  // is finished (i.e. when we return to the top level TCling::UpdateClassInfo).
395  // This allows for the dictionary to be fully populated when we actually
396  // update the TClass object. The updating of the TClass sometimes
397  // (STL containers and when there is an emulated class) forces the building
398  // of the TClass object's real data (which needs the dictionary info).
399  updateList.push_back(TD);
400  }
401  if (topLevel) {
402  while (!updateList.empty()) {
403  ((TCling*)gInterpreter)->UpdateClassInfoWithDecl(updateList.back());
404  updateList.pop_back();
405  }
406  entered = kFALSE;
407  }
408 }
409 
410 void TCling::UpdateEnumConstants(TEnum* enumObj, TClass* cl) const {
411  const clang::Decl* D = static_cast<const clang::Decl*>(enumObj->GetDeclId());
412  if(const clang::EnumDecl* ED = dyn_cast<clang::EnumDecl>(D)) {
413  // Add the constants to the enum type.
414  for (EnumDecl::enumerator_iterator EDI = ED->enumerator_begin(),
415  EDE = ED->enumerator_end(); EDI != EDE; ++EDI) {
416  // Get name of the enum type.
417  std::string constbuf;
418  if (const NamedDecl* END = llvm::dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(*EDI)) {
419  PrintingPolicy Policy((*EDI)->getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
420  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(constbuf);
421  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
422  Policy.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
423  (END)->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, Policy, /*Qualified=*/false);
424  }
425  const char* constantName = constbuf.c_str();
426 
427  // Get value of the constant.
428  Long64_t value;
429  const llvm::APSInt valAPSInt = (*EDI)->getInitVal();
430  if (valAPSInt.isSigned()) {
431  value = valAPSInt.getSExtValue();
432  } else {
433  value = valAPSInt.getZExtValue();
434  }
435 
436  // Create the TEnumConstant or update it if existing
437  TEnumConstant* enumConstant = nullptr;
438  TClingClassInfo* tcCInfo = (TClingClassInfo*)(cl ? cl->GetClassInfo() : 0);
439  TClingDataMemberInfo* tcDmInfo = new TClingDataMemberInfo(fInterpreter, *EDI, tcCInfo);
440  DataMemberInfo_t* dmInfo = (DataMemberInfo_t*) tcDmInfo;
441  if (TObject* encAsTObj = enumObj->GetConstants()->FindObject(constantName)){
442  ((TEnumConstant*)encAsTObj)->Update(dmInfo);
443  } else {
444  enumConstant = new TEnumConstant(dmInfo, constantName, value, enumObj);
445  }
446 
447  // Add the global constants to the list of Globals.
448  if (!cl) {
449  TCollection* globals = gROOT->GetListOfGlobals(false);
450  if (!globals->FindObject(constantName)) {
451  globals->Add(enumConstant);
452  }
453  }
454  }
455  }
456 }
457 
458 TEnum* TCling::CreateEnum(void *VD, TClass *cl) const
459 {
460  // Handle new enum declaration for either global and nested enums.
461 
462  // Create the enum type.
463  TEnum* enumType = 0;
464  const clang::Decl* D = static_cast<const clang::Decl*>(VD);
465  std::string buf;
466  if (const EnumDecl* ED = llvm::dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(D)) {
467  // Get name of the enum type.
468  PrintingPolicy Policy(ED->getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
469  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(buf);
470  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
471  Policy.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
472  ED->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, Policy, /*Qualified=*/false);
473  // If the enum is unnamed we do not add it to the list of enums i.e unusable.
474  }
475  if (buf.empty()) {
476  return 0;
477  }
478  const char* name = buf.c_str();
479  enumType = new TEnum(name, VD, cl);
480  UpdateEnumConstants(enumType, cl);
481 
482  return enumType;
483 }
484 
485 void TCling::HandleNewDecl(const void* DV, bool isDeserialized, std::set<TClass*> &modifiedTClasses) {
486  // Handle new declaration.
487  // Record the modified class, struct and namespaces in 'modifiedTClasses'.
488 
489  const clang::Decl* D = static_cast<const clang::Decl*>(DV);
490 
491  if (!D->isCanonicalDecl() && !isa<clang::NamespaceDecl>(D)
492  && !dyn_cast<clang::RecordDecl>(D)) return;
493 
494  if (isa<clang::FunctionDecl>(D->getDeclContext())
495  || isa<clang::TagDecl>(D->getDeclContext()))
496  return;
497 
498  // Don't list templates.
499  if (const clang::CXXRecordDecl* RD = dyn_cast<clang::CXXRecordDecl>(D)) {
500  if (RD->getDescribedClassTemplate())
501  return;
502  } else if (const clang::FunctionDecl* FD = dyn_cast<clang::FunctionDecl>(D)) {
503  if (FD->getDescribedFunctionTemplate())
504  return;
505  }
506 
507  if (const RecordDecl *TD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(D)) {
508  if (TD->isCanonicalDecl() || TD->isThisDeclarationADefinition())
509  TCling__UpdateClassInfo(TD);
510  }
511  else if (const NamedDecl *ND = dyn_cast<NamedDecl>(D)) {
512 
513  if (const TagDecl *TD = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(D)) {
514  // Mostly just for EnumDecl (the other TagDecl are handled
515  // by the 'RecordDecl' if statement.
516  TCling__UpdateClassInfo(TD);
517  } else if (const NamespaceDecl* NSD = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
518  TCling__UpdateClassInfo(NSD);
519  }
520 
521  // We care about declarations on the global scope.
522  if (!isa<TranslationUnitDecl>(ND->getDeclContext()))
523  return;
524 
525  // Enums are lazyly created, thus we don not need to handle them here.
526  if (isa<EnumDecl>(ND))
527  return;
528 
529  // ROOT says that global is enum(lazylycreated)/var/field declared on the global
530  // scope.
531  if (!(isa<VarDecl>(ND)))
532  return;
533 
534  // Skip if already in the list.
535  if (gROOT->GetListOfGlobals()->FindObject(ND->getNameAsString().c_str()))
536  return;
537 
538  // Put the global constants and global enums in the corresponding lists.
539  gROOT->GetListOfGlobals()->Add(new TGlobal((DataMemberInfo_t *)
540  new TClingDataMemberInfo(fInterpreter,
541  cast<ValueDecl>(ND), 0)));
542  }
543 }

668 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
669 /// Find a template decl within N nested namespaces, 0<=N<inf
670 /// Assumes 1 and only 1 template present and 1 and only 1 entity contained
671 /// by the namespace. Example: ns1::ns2::..::nsN::myTemplate
672 /// Returns nullptr in case of error
673 
674 static clang::ClassTemplateDecl* FindTemplateInNamespace(clang::Decl* decl)
675 {
676  using namespace clang;
677  if (NamespaceDecl* nsd = llvm::dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(decl)){
678  return FindTemplateInNamespace(*nsd->decls_begin());
679  }
680 
681  if (ClassTemplateDecl* ctd = llvm::dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(decl)){
682  return ctd;
683  }
684 
685  return nullptr; // something went wrong.
686 }

700 
701 int TCling_GenerateDictionary(const std::vector<std::string> &classes,
702  const std::vector<std::string> &headers,
703  const std::vector<std::string> &fwdDecls,
704  const std::vector<std::string> &unknown)
705 {
706  //This function automatically creates the "LinkDef.h" file for templated
707  //classes then executes CompileMacro on it.
708  //The name of the file depends on the class name, and it's not generated again
709  //if the file exist.
710  if (classes.empty()) {
711  return 0;
712  }
713  // Use the name of the first class as the main name.
714  const std::string& className = classes[0];
715  //(0) prepare file name
716  TString fileName = "AutoDict_";
717  std::string::const_iterator sIt;
718  for (sIt = className.begin(); sIt != className.end(); ++sIt) {
719  if (*sIt == '<' || *sIt == '>' ||
720  *sIt == ' ' || *sIt == '*' ||
721  *sIt == ',' || *sIt == '&' ||
722  *sIt == ':') {
723  fileName += '_';
724  }
725  else {
726  fileName += *sIt;
727  }
728  }
729  if (classes.size() > 1) {
730  Int_t chk = 0;
731  std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator it = classes.begin();
732  while ((++it) != classes.end()) {
733  for (UInt_t cursor = 0; cursor != it->length(); ++cursor) {
734  chk = chk * 3 + it->at(cursor);
735  }
736  }
737  fileName += TString::Format("_%u", chk);
738  }
739  fileName += ".cxx";
740  if (gSystem->AccessPathName(fileName) != 0) {
741  //file does not exist
742  //(1) prepare file data
743  // If STL, also request iterators' operators.
744  // vector is special: we need to check whether
745  // vector::iterator is a typedef to pointer or a
746  // class.
747  static const std::set<std::string> sSTLTypes {
748  "vector","list","forward_list","deque","map","unordered_map","multimap",
749  "unordered_multimap","set","unordered_set","multiset","unordered_multiset",
750  "queue","priority_queue","stack","iterator"};
751  std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator it;
752  std::string fileContent("");
753  for (it = headers.begin(); it != headers.end(); ++it) {
754  fileContent += "#include \"" + *it + "\"\n";
755  }
756  for (it = unknown.begin(); it != unknown.end(); ++it) {
757  TClass* cl = TClass::GetClass(it->c_str());
758  if (cl && cl->GetDeclFileName()) {
759  TString header(gSystem->BaseName(cl->GetDeclFileName()));
760  TString dir(gSystem->DirName(cl->GetDeclFileName()));
761  TString dirbase(gSystem->BaseName(dir));
762  while (dirbase.Length() && dirbase != "."
763  && dirbase != "include" && dirbase != "inc"
764  && dirbase != "prec_stl") {
765  gSystem->PrependPathName(dirbase, header);
766  dir = gSystem->DirName(dir);
767  }
768  fileContent += TString("#include \"") + header + "\"\n";
769  }
770  }
771  for (it = fwdDecls.begin(); it != fwdDecls.end(); ++it) {
772  fileContent += "class " + *it + ";\n";
773  }
774  fileContent += "#ifdef __CINT__ \n";
775  fileContent += "#pragma link C++ nestedclasses;\n";
776  fileContent += "#pragma link C++ nestedtypedefs;\n";
777  for (it = classes.begin(); it != classes.end(); ++it) {
778  std::string n(*it);
779  size_t posTemplate = n.find('<');
780  std::set<std::string>::const_iterator iSTLType = sSTLTypes.end();
781  if (posTemplate != std::string::npos) {
782  n.erase(posTemplate, std::string::npos);
783  if (n.compare(0, 5, "std::") == 0) {
784  n.erase(0, 5);
785  }
786  iSTLType = sSTLTypes.find(n);
787  }
788  fileContent += "#pragma link C++ class ";
789  fileContent += *it + "+;\n" ;
790  fileContent += "#pragma link C++ class ";
791  if (iSTLType != sSTLTypes.end()) {
792  // STL class; we cannot (and don't need to) store iterators;
793  // their shadow and the compiler's version don't agree. So
794  // don't ask for the '+'
795  fileContent += *it + "::*;\n" ;
796  }
797  else {
798  // Not an STL class; we need to allow the I/O of contained
799  // classes (now that we have a dictionary for them).
800  fileContent += *it + "::*+;\n" ;
801  }
802  }
803  fileContent += "#endif\n";
804  //end(1)
805  //(2) prepare the file
806  FILE* filePointer;
807  filePointer = fopen(fileName, "w");
808  if (filePointer == NULL) {
809  //can't open a file
810  return 1;
811  }
812  //end(2)
813  //write data into the file
814  fprintf(filePointer, "%s", fileContent.c_str());
815  fclose(filePointer);
816  }
817  //(3) checking if we can compile a macro, if not then cleaning
818  Int_t oldErrorIgnoreLevel = gErrorIgnoreLevel;
819  gErrorIgnoreLevel = kWarning; // no "Info: creating library..."
820  Int_t ret = gSystem->CompileMacro(fileName, "k");
821  gErrorIgnoreLevel = oldErrorIgnoreLevel;
822  if (ret == 0) { //can't compile a macro
823  return 2;
824  }
825  //end(3)
826  return 0;
827 }
828 
829 int TCling_GenerateDictionary(const std::string& className,
830  const std::vector<std::string> &headers,
831  const std::vector<std::string> &fwdDecls,
832  const std::vector<std::string> &unknown)
833 {
834  //This function automatically creates the "LinkDef.h" file for templated
835  //classes then executes CompileMacro on it.
836  //The name of the file depends on the class name, and it's not generated again
837  //if the file exist.
838  std::vector<std::string> classes;
839  classes.push_back(className);
840  return TCling_GenerateDictionary(classes, headers, fwdDecls, unknown);
841 }

867  void exceptionErrorHandler(void * /*user_data*/,
868  const std::string& reason,

908 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
909 /// Try hard to avoid looking up in the Cling database as this could enduce
910 /// an unwanted autoparsing.
911 
912 bool TClingLookupHelper__ExistingTypeCheck(const std::string &tname,
913  std::string &result)
914 {
915  result.clear();
916 
917  unsigned long offset = 0;
918  if (strncmp(tname.c_str(), "const ", 6) == 0) {
919  offset = 6;
920  }
921  unsigned long end = tname.length();
922  while( end && (tname[end-1]=='&' || tname[end-1]=='*' || tname[end-1]==']') ) {
923  if ( tname[end-1]==']' ) {
924  --end;
925  while ( end && tname[end-1]!='[' ) --end;
926  }
927  --end;
928  }
929  std::string innerbuf;
930  const char *inner;
931  if (end != tname.length()) {
932  innerbuf = tname.substr(offset,end-offset);
933  inner = innerbuf.c_str();
934  } else {
935  inner = tname.c_str()+offset;
936  }
937 
938  //if (strchr(tname.c_str(),'[')!=0) fprintf(stderr,"DEBUG: checking on %s vs %s %lu %lu\n",tname.c_str(),inner,offset,end);
939  if (gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(inner)
940  || TClassTable::Check(inner,result) ) {
941  // This is a known class.
942  return true;
943  }
944 
945  THashTable *typeTable = dynamic_cast<THashTable*>( gROOT->GetListOfTypes() );
946  TDataType *type = (TDataType *)typeTable->THashTable::FindObject( inner );
947  if (type) {
948  // This is a raw type and an already loaded typedef.
949  const char *newname = type->GetFullTypeName();
950  if (type->GetType() == kLong64_t) {
951  newname = "Long64_t";
952  } else if (type->GetType() == kULong64_t) {
953  newname = "ULong64_t";
954  }
955  if (strcmp(inner,newname) == 0) {
956  return true;
957  }
958  if (offset) result = "const ";
959  result += newname;
960  if ( end != tname.length() ) {
961  result += tname.substr(end,tname.length()-end);
962  }
963  if (result == tname) result.clear();
964  return true;
965  }
966 
967  // Check if the name is an enumerator
968  const auto lastPos = TClassEdit::GetUnqualifiedName(inner);
969  if (lastPos != inner) // Main switch: case 1 - scoped enum, case 2 global enum
970  {
971  // We have a scope
972  // All of this C gymnastic is to avoid allocations on the heap
973  const auto enName = lastPos;
974  const auto scopeNameSize = ((Long64_t)lastPos - (Long64_t)inner) / sizeof(decltype(*lastPos)) - 2;
975  char *scopeName = new char[scopeNameSize + 1];
976  strncpy(scopeName, inner, scopeNameSize);
977  scopeName[scopeNameSize] = '\0';
978  // Check if the scope is in the list of classes
979  if (auto scope = static_cast<TClass *>(gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(scopeName))) {
980  auto enumTable = dynamic_cast<const THashList *>(scope->GetListOfEnums(false));
981  if (enumTable && enumTable->THashList::FindObject(enName)) return true;
982  }
983  // It may still be in one of the loaded protoclasses
984  else if (auto scope = static_cast<TProtoClass *>(gClassTable->GetProtoNorm(scopeName))) {
985  auto listOfEnums = scope->GetListOfEnums();
986  if (listOfEnums) { // it could be null: no enumerators in the protoclass
987  auto enumTable = dynamic_cast<const THashList *>(listOfEnums);
988  if (enumTable && enumTable->THashList::FindObject(enName)) return true;
989  }
990  }
991  delete [] scopeName;
992  } else
993  {
994  // We don't have any scope: this could only be a global enum
995  auto enumTable = dynamic_cast<const THashList *>(gROOT->GetListOfEnums());
996  if (enumTable && enumTable->THashList::FindObject(inner)) return true;
997  }
998 
999  if (gCling->GetClassSharedLibs(inner))
1000  {
1001  // This is a class name.
1002  return true;
1003  }
1004 
1005  return false;
1006 }

1039 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1040 ///\returns true if the module map was loaded, false on error or if the map was
1041 /// already loaded.
1042 static bool RegisterPrebuiltModulePath(clang::Preprocessor& PP,
1043  const std::string& FullPath) {
1044  assert(llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(FullPath));
1045  FileManager& FM = PP.getFileManager();
1046  // FIXME: In a ROOT session we can add an include path (through .I /inc/path)
1047  // We should look for modulemap files there too.
1048  const DirectoryEntry *DE = FM.getDirectory(FullPath);
1049  if (DE) {
1050  HeaderSearch& HS = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo();
1051  const FileEntry *FE = HS.lookupModuleMapFile(DE, /*IsFramework*/ false);
1052  // FIXME: Calling IsLoaded is slow! Replace this with the appropriate
1053  // call to the clang::ModuleMap class.
1054  if (FE && !gCling->IsLoaded(FE->getName().data())) {
1055  if (!HS.loadModuleMapFile(FE, /*IsSystem*/ false)) {
1056  // We have loaded successfully the modulemap. Add the path to the
1057  // prebuilt module paths.
1058  HS.getHeaderSearchOpts().AddPrebuiltModulePath(FullPath);
1059  return true;
1060  }
1061  Error("TCling::LoadModule", "Could not load modulemap in the current directory");
1062  }
1063  }
1064  return false;
1065 }
1066 
1067 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1068 ///\returns true if the module was loaded.
1069 static bool LoadModule(const std::string &ModuleName, cling::Interpreter &interp, bool Complain = true)
1070 {
1071  // When starting up ROOT, cling would load all modulemap files on the include
1072  // paths. However, in a ROOT session, it is very common to run aclic which
1073  // will invoke rootcling and possibly produce a modulemap and a module in
1074  // the current folder.
1075  //
1076  // Before failing, try loading the modulemap in the current folder and try
1077  // loading the requested module from it.
1078  clang::Preprocessor& PP = interp.getCI()->getPreprocessor();
1079  std::string currentDir = gSystem->WorkingDirectory();
1080  assert(!currentDir.empty());
1081  RegisterPrebuiltModulePath(PP, currentDir);
1082  return interp.loadModule(ModuleName, Complain);
1083 }
1084 
1085 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1086 /// Loads the C++ modules that we require to run any ROOT program. This is just
1087 /// supposed to make a C++ module from a modulemap available to the interpreter.
1088 static void LoadModules(const std::vector<std::string> &modules, cling::Interpreter &interp)
1089 {
1090  for (const auto &modName : modules)
1091  LoadModule(modName, interp);
1092 }

1094 static bool IsFromRootCling() {
1095  // rootcling also uses TCling for generating the dictionary ROOT files.
1096  const static bool foundSymbol = dlsym(RTLD_DEFAULT, "usedToIdentifyRootClingByDlSym");
1097  return foundSymbol;
1098 }

1100 static std::string GetModuleNameAsString(clang::Module *M, const clang::Preprocessor &PP)
1101 {
1102  const HeaderSearchOptions &HSOpts = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getHeaderSearchOpts();
1103 
1104  std::string ModuleFileName;
1105  if (!HSOpts.PrebuiltModulePaths.empty())
1106  // Load the module from *only* in the prebuilt module path.
1107  ModuleFileName = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo().getModuleFileName(M->Name, /*ModuleMapPath*/"", /*UsePrebuiltPath*/ true);
1108  if (ModuleFileName.empty()) return "";
1109 
1110  std::string ModuleName = llvm::sys::path::filename(ModuleFileName);
1111  // Return stem of the filename
1112  return std::string(llvm::sys::path::stem(ModuleName));
1113 }
1114 
1115 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1116 /// Initialize the cling interpreter interface.
1117 /// \param argv - array of arguments passed to the cling::Interpreter constructor
1118 /// e.g. `-DFOO=bar`. The last element of the array must be `nullptr`.
1119 
1120 TCling::TCling(const char *name, const char *title, const char* const argv[])
1121 : TInterpreter(name, title), fGlobalsListSerial(-1), fInterpreter(0),
1122  fMetaProcessor(0), fNormalizedCtxt(0), fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo(0),
1123  fClingCallbacks(0), fAutoLoadCallBack(0),
1124  fTransactionCount(0), fHeaderParsingOnDemand(true), fIsAutoParsingSuspended(kFALSE)
1125 {
1126  const bool fromRootCling = IsFromRootCling();
1127 
1128  fCxxModulesEnabled = false;
1129 #ifdef R__USE_CXXMODULES
1130  fCxxModulesEnabled = true;
1131 #endif
1132 
1133  llvm::install_fatal_error_handler(&exceptionErrorHandler);
1134 
1135  fTemporaries = new std::vector<cling::Value>();
1136 
1137  std::vector<std::string> clingArgsStorage;
1138  clingArgsStorage.push_back("cling4root");
1139  for (const char* const* arg = argv; *arg; ++arg)
1140  clingArgsStorage.push_back(*arg);
1141 
1142  // rootcling sets its arguments through TROOT::GetExtraInterpreterArgs().
1143  if (!fromRootCling) {
1144  ROOT::TMetaUtils::SetPathsForRelocatability(clingArgsStorage);
1145 
1146  // Add -I early so ASTReader can find the headers.
1147  std::string interpInclude(TROOT::GetEtcDir().Data());
1148  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-I" + interpInclude);
1149 
1150  // Add include path to etc/cling.
1151  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-I" + interpInclude + "/cling");
1152 
1153  // Add the root include directory and etc/ to list searched by default.
1154  clingArgsStorage.push_back(std::string(("-I" + TROOT::GetIncludeDir()).Data()));
1155 
1156  // Add the current path to the include path
1157  // TCling::AddIncludePath(".");
1158 
1159  // Attach the PCH (unless we have C++ modules enabled which provide the
1160  // same functionality).
1161  if (!fCxxModulesEnabled) {
1162  std::string pchFilename = interpInclude + "/allDict.cxx.pch";
1163  if (gSystem->Getenv("ROOT_PCH")) {
1164  pchFilename = gSystem->Getenv("ROOT_PCH");
1165  }
1166 
1167  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-include-pch");
1168  clingArgsStorage.push_back(pchFilename);
1169  }
1170 
1171  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-Wno-undefined-inline");
1172  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-fsigned-char");
1173  }
1174 
1175  // Process externally passed arguments if present.
1176  llvm::Optional<std::string> EnvOpt = llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("EXTRA_CLING_ARGS");
1177  if (EnvOpt.hasValue()) {
1178  StringRef Env(*EnvOpt);
1179  while (!Env.empty()) {
1180  StringRef Arg;
1181  std::tie(Arg, Env) = Env.split(' ');
1182  clingArgsStorage.push_back(Arg.str());
1183  }
1184  }
1185 
1186  // FIXME: This only will enable frontend timing reports.
1187  EnvOpt = llvm::sys::Process::GetEnv("ROOT_CLING_TIMING");
1188  if (EnvOpt.hasValue())
1189  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-ftime-report");
1190 
1191  // Add the overlay file. Note that we cannot factor it out for both root
1192  // and rootcling because rootcling activates modules only if -cxxmodule
1193  // flag is passed.
1194  if (fCxxModulesEnabled && !fromRootCling)
1195  clingArgsStorage.push_back("-modulemap_overlay=" + std::string(TROOT::GetIncludeDir().Data()));
1196 
1197  std::vector<const char*> interpArgs;
1198  for (std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator iArg = clingArgsStorage.begin(),
1199  eArg = clingArgsStorage.end(); iArg != eArg; ++iArg)
1200  interpArgs.push_back(iArg->c_str());
1201 
1202  // Activate C++ modules support. If we are running within rootcling, it's up
1203  // to rootcling to set this flag depending on whether it wants to produce
1204  // C++ modules.
1205  TString vfsArg;
1206  if (fCxxModulesEnabled && !fromRootCling) {
1207  // We only set this flag, rest is done by the CIFactory.
1208  interpArgs.push_back("-fmodules");
1209  // We should never build modules during runtime, so let's enable the
1210  // module build remarks from clang to make it easier to spot when we do
1211  // this by accident.
1212  interpArgs.push_back("-Rmodule-build");
1213  }
1214 
1215 #ifdef R__FAST_MATH
1216  // Same setting as in rootcling_impl.cxx.
1217  interpArgs.push_back("-ffast-math");
1218 #endif
1219 
1220 #ifdef R__EXTERN_LLVMDIR
1221  TString llvmResourceDir = R__EXTERN_LLVMDIR;
1222 #else
1223  TString llvmResourceDir = TROOT::GetEtcDir() + "/cling";
1224 #endif
1225  // Add statically injected extra arguments, usually coming from rootcling.
1226  for (const char** extraArgs = TROOT::GetExtraInterpreterArgs();
1227  extraArgs && *extraArgs; ++extraArgs) {
1228  if (!strcmp(*extraArgs, "-resource-dir")) {
1229  // Take the next arg as the llvm resource directory.
1230  llvmResourceDir = *(++extraArgs);
1231  } else {
1232  interpArgs.push_back(*extraArgs);
1233  }
1234  }
1235 
1236  for (const auto &arg: TROOT::AddExtraInterpreterArgs({})) {
1237  interpArgs.push_back(arg.c_str());
1238  }
1239 
1240  fInterpreter = new cling::Interpreter(interpArgs.size(),
1241  &(interpArgs[0]),
1242  llvmResourceDir);
1243 
1244  if (!fromRootCling) {
1245  fInterpreter->installLazyFunctionCreator(llvmLazyFunctionCreator);
1246  }
1247 
1248  // Don't check whether modules' files exist.
1249  fInterpreter->getCI()->getPreprocessorOpts().DisablePCHValidation = true;
1250 
1251  // Until we can disable autoloading during Sema::CorrectTypo() we have
1252  // to disable spell checking.
1253  fInterpreter->getCI()->getLangOpts().SpellChecking = false;
1254 
1255 
1256  // We need stream that doesn't close its file descriptor, thus we are not
1257  // using llvm::outs. Keeping file descriptor open we will be able to use
1258  // the results in pipes (Savannah #99234).
1259  static llvm::raw_fd_ostream fMPOuts (STDOUT_FILENO, /*ShouldClose*/false);
1260  fMetaProcessor = new cling::MetaProcessor(*fInterpreter, fMPOuts);
1261 
1262  if (fInterpreter->getCI()->getLangOpts().Modules) {
1263  // Setup core C++ modules if we have any to setup.
1264 
1265  // Load libc and stl first.
1266 #ifdef R__MACOSX
1267  LoadModules({"Darwin", "std"}, *fInterpreter);
1268 #else
1269  LoadModules({"libc", "stl"}, *fInterpreter);
1270 #endif
1271 
1272  // Load core modules
1273  // This should be vector in order to be able to pass it to LoadModules
1274  std::vector<std::string> CoreModules = {"ROOT_Foundation_C","ROOT_Config",
1275  "ROOT_Foundation_Stage1_NoRTTI", "Core", "RIO"};
1276 
1277  // FIXME: Reducing those will let us be less dependent on rootmap files
1278  static constexpr std::array<const char*, 3> ExcludeModules =
1279  { { "Rtools", "RSQLite", "RInterface"} };
1280 
1281  LoadModules(CoreModules, *fInterpreter);
1282 
1283  // Take this branch only from ROOT because we don't need to preload modules in rootcling
1284  if (!fromRootCling) {
1285  // Dynamically get all the modules and load them if they are not in core modules
1286  clang::CompilerInstance &CI = *fInterpreter->getCI();
1287  clang::ModuleMap &moduleMap = CI.getPreprocessor().getHeaderSearchInfo().getModuleMap();
1288  clang::Preprocessor &PP = CI.getPreprocessor();
1289  std::vector<std::string> ModulesPreloaded;
1290 
1291  for (auto I = moduleMap.module_begin(), E = moduleMap.module_end(); I != E; ++I) {
1292  clang::Module *M = I->second;
1293  assert(M);
1294 
1295  std::string ModuleName = GetModuleNameAsString(M, PP);
1296  if (!ModuleName.empty() &&
1297  std::find(CoreModules.begin(), CoreModules.end(), ModuleName) == CoreModules.end()
1298  && std::find(ExcludeModules.begin(), ExcludeModules.end(), ModuleName) == ExcludeModules.end()) {
1299  if (M->IsSystem && !M->IsMissingRequirement)
1300  LoadModule(ModuleName, *fInterpreter);
1301  else if (!M->IsSystem && !M->IsMissingRequirement)
1302  ModulesPreloaded.push_back(ModuleName);
1303  }
1304  }
1305  LoadModules(ModulesPreloaded, *fInterpreter);
1306  }
1307 
1308  // Check that the gROOT macro was exported by any core module.
1309  assert(fInterpreter->getMacro("gROOT") && "Couldn't load gROOT macro?");
1310 
1311  // C99 decided that it's a very good idea to name a macro `I` (the letter I).
1312  // This seems to screw up nearly all the template code out there as `I` is
1313  // common template parameter name and iterator variable name.
1314  // Let's follow the GCC recommendation and undefine `I` in case any of the
1315  // core modules have defined it:
1316  // https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Complex-Numbers.html
1317  fInterpreter->declare("#ifdef I\n #undef I\n #endif\n");
1318 
1319  // These macros are from loading R related modules, which conflict with
1320  // user's code.
1321  fInterpreter->declare("#ifdef PI\n #undef PI\n #endif\n");
1322  fInterpreter->declare("#ifdef ERROR\n #undef ERROR\n #endif\n");
1323  }
1324 
1325  // For the list to also include string, we have to include it now.
1326  // rootcling does parts already if needed, e.g. genreflex does not want using
1327  // namespace std.
1328  if (fromRootCling) {
1329  fInterpreter->declare("#include \"RtypesCore.h\"\n"
1330  "#include <string>\n"
1331  "using std::string;\n"
1332  "#include <cassert>\n");
1333  } else {
1334  fInterpreter->declare("#include \"Rtypes.h\"\n"
1335  + gClassDefInterpMacro + "\n"
1336  + gInterpreterClassDef + "\n"
1337  "#undef ClassImp\n"
1338  "#define ClassImp(X);\n"
1339  "#include <string>\n"
1340  "using namespace std;\n"
1341  "#include <cassert>\n");
1342  }
1343 
1344  // We are now ready (enough is loaded) to init the list of opaque typedefs.
1345  fNormalizedCtxt = new ROOT::TMetaUtils::TNormalizedCtxt(fInterpreter->getLookupHelper());
1346  fLookupHelper = new ROOT::TMetaUtils::TClingLookupHelper(*fInterpreter, *fNormalizedCtxt, TClingLookupHelper__ExistingTypeCheck, TClingLookupHelper__AutoParse);
1347  TClassEdit::Init(fLookupHelper);
1348 
1349  // Initialize the cling interpreter interface.
1350  fMore = 0;
1351  fPrompt[0] = 0;
1352  fMapfile = 0;
1353 // fMapNamespaces = 0;
1354  fRootmapFiles = 0;
1355  fLockProcessLine = kTRUE;
1356 
1357  fAllowLibLoad = !fromRootCling;
1358  // Disallow auto-parsing in rootcling
1359  fIsAutoParsingSuspended = fromRootCling;
1360  // Disable the autoloader until it is explicitly enabled.
1361  SetClassAutoloading(false);
1362 
1363  ResetAll();
1364 #ifndef R__WIN32
1365  //optind = 1; // make sure getopt() works in the main program
1366 #endif // R__WIN32
1367 
1368  // Enable dynamic lookup
1369  if (!fromRootCling) {
1370  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup();
1371  }
1372 
1373  // Attach cling callbacks last; they might need TROOT::fInterpreter
1374  // and should thus not be triggered during the equivalent of
1375  // TROOT::fInterpreter = new TCling;
1376  std::unique_ptr<TClingCallbacks>
1377  clingCallbacks(new TClingCallbacks(fInterpreter));
1378  fClingCallbacks = clingCallbacks.get();
1379  fClingCallbacks->SetAutoParsingSuspended(fIsAutoParsingSuspended);
1380  fInterpreter->setCallbacks(std::move(clingCallbacks));
1381 
1382 }
1383 
1384 
1385 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1386 /// Destroy the interpreter interface.
1387 
1388 TCling::~TCling()
1389 {
1390  delete fMapfile;
1391 // delete fMapNamespaces;
1392  delete fRootmapFiles;
1393  delete fMetaProcessor;
1394  delete fTemporaries;
1395  delete fNormalizedCtxt;
1396  delete fInterpreter;
1397  delete fLookupHelper;
1398  gCling = 0;
1399 #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
1400 #if R__MUST_REVISIT(6,2)
1401  Warning("~TCling", "Interface not available yet.");
1402 #ifdef R__COMPLETE_MEM_TERMINATION
1403  // remove all cling objects
1404 #endif
1405 #endif
1406 #endif
1407  //--
1408 }

1413 void TCling::Initialize()

1417 
1418 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1419 /// Wrapper around dladdr (and friends)
1420 
1421 static std::string FindLibraryName(void (*func)())
1422 {
1423 #if defined(__CYGWIN__) && defined(__GNUC__)
1424  return {};
1425 #elif defined(G__WIN32)
1426  MEMORY_BASIC_INFORMATION mbi;
1427  if (!VirtualQuery (func, &mbi, sizeof (mbi)))
1428  {
1429  return {};
1430  }
1431 
1432  HMODULE hMod = (HMODULE) mbi.AllocationBase;
1433  char moduleName[MAX_PATH];
1434 
1435  if (!GetModuleFileNameA (hMod, moduleName, sizeof (moduleName)))
1436  {
1437  return {};
1438  }
1439  return moduleName;
1440 #else
1441  Dl_info info;
1442  if (dladdr((void*)func, &info) == 0) {
1443  // Not in a known shared library, let's give up
1444  return {};
1445  } else {
1446  if (strchr(info.dli_fname, '/'))
1447  return info.dli_fname;
1448  // Else absolute path. For all we know that's a binary.
1449  // Some people have dictionaries in binaries, this is how we find their path:
1450  // (see also https://stackoverflow.com/a/1024937/6182509)
1451 # if defined(R__MACOSX)
1452  char buf[PATH_MAX] = { 0 };
1453  uint32_t bufsize = sizeof(buf);
1454  if (_NSGetExecutablePath(buf, &bufsize) >= 0)
1455  return buf;
1456  return info.dli_fname;
1457 # elif defined(R__UNIX)
1458  char buf[PATH_MAX] = { 0 };
1459  // Cross our fingers that /proc/self/exe exists.
1460  if (readlink("/proc/self/exe", buf, sizeof(buf)) > 0)
1461  return buf;
1462  std::string pipeCmd = std::string("which \"") + info.dli_fname + "\"";
1463  FILE* pipe = popen(pipeCmd.c_str(), "r");
1464  if (!pipe)
1465  return info.dli_fname;
1466  std::string result;
1467  while (fgets(buf, sizeof(buf), pipe)) {
1468  result += buf;
1469  }
1470  pclose(pipe);
1471  return result;
1472 # else
1473 # error "Unsupported platform."
1474 # endif
1475  return {};
1476  }
1477 #endif
1478 
1479 }
1480 
1481 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1482 /// Helper to initialize TVirtualStreamerInfo's factor early.
1483 /// Use static initialization to insure only one TStreamerInfo is created.
1484 static bool R__InitStreamerInfoFactory()
1485 {
1486  // Use lambda since SetFactory return void.
1487  auto setFactory = []() {
1488  TVirtualStreamerInfo::SetFactory(new TStreamerInfo());
1489  return kTRUE;
1490  };
1491  static bool doneFactory = setFactory();
1492  return doneFactory; // avoid unused variable warning.
1493 }
1494 
1495 
1496 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1497 /// Tries to load a PCM; returns true on success.
1498 
1499 bool TCling::LoadPCM(const std::string &pcmFileNameFullPath)
1500 {
1501 
1502  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoloadOff(this);
1503  SuspendAutoParsing autoparseOff(this);
1504  assert(!pcmFileNameFullPath.empty());
1505  assert(llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(pcmFileNameFullPath));
1506  if (!llvm::sys::fs::exists(pcmFileNameFullPath)) {
1507  return false;
1508  }
1509 
1510  // Easier to work with the ROOT interfaces.
1511  TString pcmFileName = pcmFileNameFullPath;
1512 
1513  // Prevent the ROOT-PCMs hitting this during auto-load during
1514  // JITting - which will cause recursive compilation.
1515  // Avoid to call the plugin manager at all.
1516  R__InitStreamerInfoFactory();
1517 
1518  if (gROOT->IsRootFile(pcmFileName)) {
1519  Int_t oldDebug = gDebug;
1520  if (gDebug > 5) {
1521  gDebug -= 5;
1522  ::Info("TCling::LoadPCM", "Loading ROOT PCM %s", pcmFileName.Data());
1523  } else {
1524  gDebug = 0;
1525  }
1526 
1527  TDirectory::TContext ctxt;
1528 
1529  TFile *pcmFile = new TFile(pcmFileName+"?filetype=pcm","READ");
1530 
1531  auto listOfKeys = pcmFile->GetListOfKeys();
1532 
1533  // This is an empty pcm
1534  if (
1535  listOfKeys &&
1536  (
1537  (listOfKeys->GetSize() == 0) || // Nothing here, or
1538  (
1539  (listOfKeys->GetSize() == 1) && // only one, and
1540  !strcmp(((TKey*)listOfKeys->At(0))->GetName(), "EMPTY") // name is EMPTY
1541  )
1542  )
1543  ) {
1544  delete pcmFile;
1545  gDebug = oldDebug;
1546  return kTRUE;
1547  }
1548 
1549  TObjArray *protoClasses;
1550  if (gDebug > 1)
1551  ::Info("TCling::LoadPCM","reading protoclasses for %s \n",pcmFileName.Data());
1552 
1553  pcmFile->GetObject("__ProtoClasses", protoClasses);
1554 
1555  if (protoClasses) {
1556  for (auto obj : *protoClasses) {
1557  TProtoClass * proto = (TProtoClass*)obj;
1558  TClassTable::Add(proto);
1559  }
1560  // Now that all TClass-es know how to set them up we can update
1561  // existing TClasses, which might cause the creation of e.g. TBaseClass
1562  // objects which in turn requires the creation of TClasses, that could
1563  // come from the PCH, but maybe later in the loop. Instead of resolving
1564  // a dependency graph the addition to the TClassTable above allows us
1565  // to create these dependent TClasses as needed below.
1566  for (auto proto : *protoClasses) {
1567  if (TClass* existingCl
1568  = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(proto->GetName())) {
1569  // We have an existing TClass object. It might be emulated
1570  // or interpreted; we now have more information available.
1571  // Make that available.
1572  if (existingCl->GetState() != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
1573  DictFuncPtr_t dict = gClassTable->GetDict(proto->GetName());
1574  if (!dict) {
1575  ::Error("TCling::LoadPCM", "Inconsistent TClassTable for %s",
1576  proto->GetName());
1577  } else {
1578  // This will replace the existing TClass.
1579  TClass *ncl = (*dict)();
1580  if (ncl) ncl->PostLoadCheck();
1581 
1582  }
1583  }
1584  }
1585  }
1586 
1587  protoClasses->Clear(); // Ownership was transfered to TClassTable.
1588  delete protoClasses;
1589  }
1590 
1591  TObjArray *dataTypes;
1592  pcmFile->GetObject("__Typedefs", dataTypes);
1593  if (dataTypes) {
1594  for (auto typedf: *dataTypes)
1595  gROOT->GetListOfTypes()->Add(typedf);
1596  dataTypes->Clear(); // Ownership was transfered to TListOfTypes.
1597  delete dataTypes;
1598  }
1599 
1600  TObjArray *enums;
1601  pcmFile->GetObject("__Enums", enums);
1602  if (enums) {
1603  // Cache the pointers
1604  auto listOfGlobals = gROOT->GetListOfGlobals();
1605  auto listOfEnums = dynamic_cast<THashList*>(gROOT->GetListOfEnums());
1606  // Loop on enums and then on enum constants
1607  for (auto selEnum: *enums){
1608  const char* enumScope = selEnum->GetTitle();
1609  const char* enumName = selEnum->GetName();
1610  if (strcmp(enumScope,"") == 0){
1611  // This is a global enum and is added to the
1612  // list of enums and its constants to the list of globals
1613  if (!listOfEnums->THashList::FindObject(enumName)){
1614  ((TEnum*) selEnum)->SetClass(nullptr);
1615  listOfEnums->Add(selEnum);
1616  }
1617  for (auto enumConstant: *static_cast<TEnum*>(selEnum)->GetConstants()){
1618  if (!listOfGlobals->FindObject(enumConstant)){
1619  listOfGlobals->Add(enumConstant);
1620  }
1621  }
1622  }
1623  else {
1624  // This enum is in a namespace. A TClass entry is bootstrapped if
1625  // none exists yet and the enum is added to it
1626  TClass* nsTClassEntry = TClass::GetClass(enumScope);
1627  if (!nsTClassEntry){
1628  nsTClassEntry = new TClass(enumScope,0,TClass::kNamespaceForMeta, true);
1629  }
1630  auto listOfEnums = nsTClassEntry->fEnums.load();
1631  if (!listOfEnums) {
1632  if ( (kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsUnion) & nsTClassEntry->Property() ) {
1633  // For this case, the list will be immutable once constructed
1634  // (i.e. in this case, by the end of this routine).
1635  listOfEnums = nsTClassEntry->fEnums = new TListOfEnums(nsTClassEntry);
1636  } else {
1637  //namespaces can have enums added to them
1638  listOfEnums = nsTClassEntry->fEnums = new TListOfEnumsWithLock(nsTClassEntry);
1639  }
1640  }
1641  if (listOfEnums && !listOfEnums->THashList::FindObject(enumName)){
1642  ((TEnum*) selEnum)->SetClass(nsTClassEntry);
1643  listOfEnums->Add(selEnum);
1644  }
1645  }
1646  }
1647  enums->Clear();
1648  delete enums;
1649  }
1650 
1651  delete pcmFile;
1652 
1653  gDebug = oldDebug;
1654  } else {
1655  if (gDebug > 5)
1656  ::Info("TCling::LoadPCM", "Loading clang PCM %s", pcmFileName.Data());
1657 
1658  }
1659  return kTRUE;
1660 }
1661 
1662 //______________________________________________________________________________
1663 
1664 namespace {
1665  using namespace clang;
1666 
1667  class ExtLexicalStorageAdder: public RecursiveASTVisitor<ExtLexicalStorageAdder>{
1668  // This class is to be considered an helper for autoparsing.
1669  // It visits the AST and marks all classes (in all of their redeclarations)
1670  // with the setHasExternalLexicalStorage method.
1671  public:
1672  bool VisitRecordDecl(clang::RecordDecl* rcd){
1673  if (gDebug > 2)
1674  Info("ExtLexicalStorageAdder",
1675  "Adding external lexical storage to class %s",
1676  rcd->getNameAsString().c_str());
1677  auto reDeclPtr = rcd->getMostRecentDecl();
1678  do {
1679  reDeclPtr->setHasExternalLexicalStorage();
1680  } while ((reDeclPtr = reDeclPtr->getPreviousDecl()));
1681 
1682  return false;
1683  }
1684  };
1685 
1686 
1687 }
1688 
1689 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1690 /// List of dicts that have the PCM information already in the PCH.
1691 static const std::unordered_set<std::string> gIgnoredPCMNames = {"libCore",
1692  "libRint",
1693  "libThread",
1694  "libRIO",
1695  "libImt",
1696  "libcomplexDict",
1697  "libdequeDict",
1698  "liblistDict",
1699  "libforward_listDict",
1700  "libvectorDict",
1701  "libmapDict",
1702  "libmultimap2Dict",
1703  "libmap2Dict",
1704  "libmultimapDict",
1705  "libsetDict",
1706  "libmultisetDict",
1707  "libunordered_setDict",
1708  "libunordered_multisetDict",
1709  "libunordered_mapDict",
1710  "libunordered_multimapDict",
1711  "libvalarrayDict",
1712  "G__GenVector32",
1713  "G__Smatrix32"};
1714 
1715 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1716 /// Inject the module named "modulename" into cling; load all headers.
1717 /// headers is a 0-terminated array of header files to #include after
1718 /// loading the module. The module is searched for in all $LD_LIBRARY_PATH
1719 /// entries (or %PATH% on Windows).
1720 /// This function gets called by the static initialization of dictionary
1721 /// libraries.
1722 /// The payload code is injected "as is" in the interpreter.
1723 /// The value of 'triggerFunc' is used to find the shared library location.
1724 
1725 void TCling::RegisterModule(const char* modulename,
1726  const char** headers,
1727  const char** includePaths,
1728  const char* payloadCode,
1729  const char* fwdDeclsCode,
1730  void (*triggerFunc)(),
1731  const FwdDeclArgsToKeepCollection_t& fwdDeclsArgToSkip,
1732  const char** classesHeaders,
1733  Bool_t lateRegistration /*=false*/,
1734  Bool_t hasCxxModule /*=false*/)
1735 {
1736  const bool fromRootCling = IsFromRootCling();
1737  // We need the dictionary initialization but we don't want to inject the
1738  // declarations into the interpreter, except for those we really need for
1739  // I/O; see rootcling.cxx after the call to TCling__GetInterpreter().
1740  if (fromRootCling) return;
1741 
1742  // When we cannot provide a module for the library we should enable header
1743  // parsing. This 'mixed' mode ensures gradual migration to modules.
1744  llvm::SaveAndRestore<bool> SaveHeaderParsing(fHeaderParsingOnDemand);
1745  fHeaderParsingOnDemand = !hasCxxModule;
1746 
1747  // Treat Aclic Libs in a special way. Do not delay the parsing.
1748  bool hasHeaderParsingOnDemand = fHeaderParsingOnDemand;
1749  bool isACLiC = strstr(modulename, "_ACLiC_dict") != nullptr;
1750  if (hasHeaderParsingOnDemand && isACLiC) {
1751  if (gDebug>1)
1752  Info("TCling::RegisterModule",
1753  "Header parsing on demand is active but this is an Aclic library. Disabling it for this library.");
1754  hasHeaderParsingOnDemand = false;
1755  }
1756 
1757 
1758  // Make sure we relookup symbols that were search for before we loaded
1759  // their autoparse information. We could be more subtil and remove only
1760  // the failed one or only the one in this module, but for now this is
1761  // better than nothing.
1762  fLookedUpClasses.clear();
1763 
1764  // Make sure we do not set off autoloading or autoparsing during the
1765  // module registration!
1766  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoLoadOff(this);
1767 
1768  for (const char** inclPath = includePaths; *inclPath; ++inclPath) {
1769  TCling::AddIncludePath(*inclPath);
1770  }
1771  cling::Transaction* T = 0;
1772  // Put the template decls and the number of arguments to skip in the TNormalizedCtxt
1773  for (auto& fwdDeclArgToSkipPair : fwdDeclsArgToSkip){
1774  const std::string& fwdDecl = fwdDeclArgToSkipPair.first;
1775  const int nArgsToSkip = fwdDeclArgToSkipPair.second;
1776  auto compRes = fInterpreter->declare(fwdDecl.c_str(), &T);
1777  assert(cling::Interpreter::kSuccess == compRes &&
1778  "A fwd declaration could not be compiled");
1779  if (compRes!=cling::Interpreter::kSuccess){
1780  Warning("TCling::RegisterModule",
1781  "Problems in declaring string '%s' were encountered.",
1782  fwdDecl.c_str()) ;
1783  continue;
1784  }
1785 
1786  // Drill through namespaces recursively until the template is found
1787  if(ClassTemplateDecl* TD = FindTemplateInNamespace(T->getFirstDecl().getSingleDecl())){
1788  fNormalizedCtxt->AddTemplAndNargsToKeep(TD->getCanonicalDecl(), nArgsToSkip);
1789  }
1790 
1791  }
1792 
1793  // FIXME: Remove #define __ROOTCLING__ once PCMs are there.
1794  // This is used to give Sema the same view on ACLiC'ed files (which
1795  // are then #included through the dictionary) as rootcling had.
1796  TString code = gNonInterpreterClassDef;
1797  if (payloadCode)
1798  code += payloadCode;
1799 
1800  std::string dyLibName = FindLibraryName(triggerFunc);
1801 
1802  if (dyLibName.empty()) {
1803  ::Error("TCling::RegisterModule", "Dictionary trigger function for %s not found", modulename);
1804  return;
1805  }
1806 
1807  // The triggerFunc may not be in a shared object but in an executable.
1808  bool isSharedLib = cling::DynamicLibraryManager::isSharedLibrary(dyLibName);
1809 
1810  bool wasDlopened = false;
1811 
1812  // If this call happens after dlopen has finished (i.e. late registration)
1813  // there is no need to dlopen the library recursively. See ROOT-8437 where
1814  // the dyLibName would correspond to the binary.
1815  if (!lateRegistration) {
1816 
1817  if (isSharedLib) {
1818  // We need to open the dictionary shared library, to resolve symbols
1819  // requested by the JIT from it: as the library is currently being dlopen'ed,
1820  // its symbols are not yet reachable from the process.
1821  // Recursive dlopen seems to work just fine.
1822  void* dyLibHandle = dlopen(dyLibName.c_str(), RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_GLOBAL);
1823  if (!dyLibHandle) {
1824 #ifdef R__WIN32
1825  char dyLibError[1000];
1826  FormatMessageA(FORMAT_MESSAGE_FROM_SYSTEM, NULL, GetLastError(), MAKELANGID(LANG_NEUTRAL, SUBLANG_DEFAULT),
1827  dyLibError, sizeof(dyLibError), NULL);
1828 #else
1829  const char* dyLibError = dlerror();
1830  if (dyLibError)
1831 #endif
1832  {
1833  if (gDebug > 0) {
1834  ::Info("TCling::RegisterModule",
1835  "Cannot open shared library %s for dictionary %s:\n %s",
1836  dyLibName.c_str(), modulename, dyLibError);
1837  }
1838  }
1839  } else {
1840  fRegisterModuleDyLibs.push_back(dyLibHandle);
1841  wasDlopened = true;
1842  } // if (!dyLibHandle) .. else
1843  } // if (dyLibName)
1844  } // if (!lateRegistration)
1845 
1846  if (hasHeaderParsingOnDemand && fwdDeclsCode){
1847  // We now parse the forward declarations. All the classes are then modified
1848  // in order for them to have an external lexical storage.
1849  std::string fwdDeclsCodeLessEnums;
1850  {
1851  // Search for enum forward decls and only declare them if no
1852  // declaration exists yet.
1853  std::string fwdDeclsLine;
1854  std::istringstream fwdDeclsCodeStr(fwdDeclsCode);
1855  std::vector<std::string> scopes;
1856  while (std::getline(fwdDeclsCodeStr, fwdDeclsLine)) {
1857  const auto enumPos = fwdDeclsLine.find("enum __attribute__((annotate(\"");
1858  // We check if the line contains a fwd declaration of an enum
1859  if (enumPos != std::string::npos) {
1860  // We clear the scopes which we may have carried from a previous iteration
1861  scopes.clear();
1862  // We check if the enum is not in a scope. If yes, save its name
1863  // and the names of the enclosing scopes.
1864  if (enumPos != 0) {
1865  // it's enclosed in namespaces. We need to understand what they are
1866  auto nsPos = fwdDeclsLine.find("namespace");
1867  R__ASSERT(nsPos < enumPos && "Inconsistent enum and enclosing scope parsing!");
1868  while (nsPos < enumPos && nsPos != std::string::npos) {
1869  // we have a namespace, let's put it in the collection of scopes
1870  const auto nsNameStart = nsPos + 10;
1871  const auto nsNameEnd = fwdDeclsLine.find('{', nsNameStart);
1872  const auto nsName = fwdDeclsLine.substr(nsNameStart, nsNameEnd - nsNameStart);
1873  scopes.push_back(nsName);
1874  nsPos = fwdDeclsLine.find("namespace", nsNameEnd);
1875  }
1876  }
1877  clang::DeclContext* DC = 0;
1878  for (auto &&aScope: scopes) {
1879  DC = cling::utils::Lookup::Namespace(&fInterpreter->getSema(), aScope.c_str(), DC);
1880  if (!DC) {
1881  // No decl context means we have to fwd declare the enum.
1882  break;
1883  }
1884  }
1885  if (scopes.empty() || DC) {
1886  // We know the scope; let's look for the enum.
1887  size_t posEnumName = fwdDeclsLine.find("\"))) ", 32);
1888  R__ASSERT(posEnumName != std::string::npos && "Inconsistent enum fwd decl!");
1889  posEnumName += 5; // skip "\"))) "
1890  while (isspace(fwdDeclsLine[posEnumName]))
1891  ++posEnumName;
1892  size_t posEnumNameEnd = fwdDeclsLine.find(" : ", posEnumName);
1893  R__ASSERT(posEnumNameEnd != std::string::npos && "Inconsistent enum fwd decl (end)!");
1894  while (isspace(fwdDeclsLine[posEnumNameEnd]))
1895  --posEnumNameEnd;
1896  // posEnumNameEnd now points to the last character of the name.
1897 
1898  std::string enumName = fwdDeclsLine.substr(posEnumName,
1899  posEnumNameEnd - posEnumName + 1);
1900 
1901  if (clang::NamedDecl* enumDecl
1902  = cling::utils::Lookup::Named(&fInterpreter->getSema(),
1903  enumName.c_str(), DC)) {
1904  // We have an existing enum decl (forward or definition);
1905  // skip this.
1906  R__ASSERT(llvm::dyn_cast<clang::EnumDecl>(enumDecl) && "not an enum decl!");
1907  (void)enumDecl;
1908  continue;
1909  }
1910  }
1911  }
1912 
1913  fwdDeclsCodeLessEnums += fwdDeclsLine + "\n";
1914  }
1915  }
1916 
1917  if (fwdDeclsCodeLessEnums.size() != 0){ // Avoid the overhead if nothing is to be declared
1918  auto compRes = fInterpreter->declare(fwdDeclsCodeLessEnums, &T);
1919  assert(cling::Interpreter::kSuccess == compRes &&
1920  "The forward declarations could not be compiled");
1921  if (compRes!=cling::Interpreter::kSuccess){
1922  Warning("TCling::RegisterModule",
1923  "Problems in compiling forward declarations for module %s: '%s'",
1924  modulename, fwdDeclsCodeLessEnums.c_str()) ;
1925  }
1926  else if (T){
1927  // Loop over all decls in the transaction and go through them all
1928  // to mark them properly.
1929  // In order to do that, we first iterate over all the DelayedCallInfos
1930  // within the transaction. Then we loop over all Decls in the DeclGroupRef
1931  // contained in the DelayedCallInfos. For each decl, we traverse.
1932  ExtLexicalStorageAdder elsa;
1933  for (auto dciIt = T->decls_begin();dciIt!=T->decls_end();dciIt++){
1934  cling::Transaction::DelayCallInfo& dci = *dciIt;
1935  for(auto dit = dci.m_DGR.begin(); dit != dci.m_DGR.end(); ++dit) {
1936  clang::Decl* declPtr = *dit;
1937  elsa.TraverseDecl(declPtr);
1938  }
1939  }
1940  }
1941  }
1942 
1943  // Now we register all the headers necessary for the class
1944  // Typical format of the array:
1945  // {"A", "classes.h", "@",
1946  // "vector<A>", "vector", "@",
1947  // "myClass", payloadCode, "@",
1948  // nullptr};
1949 
1950  std::string temp;
1951  for (const char** classesHeader = classesHeaders; *classesHeader; ++classesHeader) {
1952  temp=*classesHeader;
1953 
1954  size_t theTemplateHash = 0;
1955  bool addTemplate = false;
1956  size_t posTemplate = temp.find('<');
1957  if (posTemplate != std::string::npos) {
1958  // Add an entry for the template itself.
1959  std::string templateName = temp.substr(0, posTemplate);
1960  theTemplateHash = fStringHashFunction(templateName);
1961  addTemplate = true;
1962  }
1963  size_t theHash = fStringHashFunction(temp);
1964  classesHeader++;
1965  for (const char** classesHeader_inner = classesHeader; 0!=strcmp(*classesHeader_inner,"@"); ++classesHeader_inner,++classesHeader){
1966  // This is done in order to distinguish headers from files and from the payloadCode
1967  if (payloadCode == *classesHeader_inner ){
1968  fPayloads.insert(theHash);
1969  if (addTemplate) fPayloads.insert(theTemplateHash);
1970  }
1971  if (gDebug > 2)
1972  Info("TCling::RegisterModule",
1973  "Adding a header for %s", temp.c_str());
1974  fClassesHeadersMap[theHash].push_back(*classesHeader_inner);
1975  if (addTemplate) {
1976  if (fClassesHeadersMap.find(theTemplateHash) == fClassesHeadersMap.end()) {
1977  fClassesHeadersMap[theTemplateHash].push_back(*classesHeader_inner);
1978  }
1979  addTemplate = false;
1980  }
1981  }
1982  }
1983  }
1984 
1985  if (gIgnoredPCMNames.find(modulename) == gIgnoredPCMNames.end()) {
1986  llvm::SmallString<256> pcmFileNameFullPath(dyLibName);
1987  // The path dyLibName might not be absolute. This can happen if dyLibName
1988  // is linked to an executable in the same folder.
1989  llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(pcmFileNameFullPath);
1990  llvm::sys::path::remove_filename(pcmFileNameFullPath);
1991  llvm::sys::path::append(pcmFileNameFullPath,
1992  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetModuleFileName(modulename));
1993  if (!LoadPCM(pcmFileNameFullPath.str().str())) {
1994  ::Error("TCling::RegisterModule", "cannot find dictionary module %s",
1995  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetModuleFileName(modulename).c_str());
1996  }
1997  }
1998 
1999  clang::Sema &TheSema = fInterpreter->getSema();
2000 
2001  bool ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded = false;
2002  if (hasCxxModule) {
2003  std::string ModuleName = modulename;
2004  if (llvm::StringRef(modulename).startswith("lib"))
2005  ModuleName = llvm::StringRef(modulename).substr(3).str();
2006 
2007  // In case we are directly loading the library via gSystem->Load() without
2008  // specifying the relevant include paths we should try loading the
2009  // modulemap next to the library location.
2010  clang::Preprocessor &PP = TheSema.getPreprocessor();
2011  // Can be nullptr in case of libCore.
2012  if (!dyLibName.empty())
2013  RegisterPrebuiltModulePath(PP, llvm::sys::path::parent_path(dyLibName));
2014 
2015  // FIXME: We should only complain for modules which we know to exist. For example, we should not complain about
2016  // modules such as GenVector32 because it needs to fall back to GenVector.
2017  ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded = LoadModule(ModuleName, *fInterpreter, /*Complain=*/ !isACLiC);
2018  if (!ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded) {
2019  // Only report if we found the module in the modulemap.
2020  clang::HeaderSearch &headerSearch = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo();
2021  clang::ModuleMap &moduleMap = headerSearch.getModuleMap();
2022  if (moduleMap.findModule(ModuleName))
2023  Info("TCling::RegisterModule", "Module %s in modulemap failed to load.", ModuleName.c_str());
2024  }
2025  }
2026 
2027  { // scope within which diagnostics are de-activated
2028  // For now we disable diagnostics because we saw them already at
2029  // dictionary generation time. That won't be an issue with the PCMs.
2030 
2031  clangDiagSuppr diagSuppr(TheSema.getDiagnostics());
2032 
2033 #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
2034 #if R__MUST_REVISIT(6,2)
2035  Warning("TCling::RegisterModule","Diagnostics suppression should be gone by now.");
2036 #endif
2037 #endif
2038 
2039  if (!ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded && !hasHeaderParsingOnDemand){
2040  SuspendAutoParsing autoParseRaii(this);
2041 
2042  const cling::Transaction* watermark = fInterpreter->getLastTransaction();
2043  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult compRes = fInterpreter->parseForModule(code.Data());
2044  if (isACLiC) {
2045  // Register an unload point.
2046  fMetaProcessor->registerUnloadPoint(watermark, headers[0]);
2047  }
2048 
2049  assert(cling::Interpreter::kSuccess == compRes &&
2050  "Payload code of a dictionary could not be parsed correctly.");
2051  if (compRes!=cling::Interpreter::kSuccess) {
2052  Warning("TCling::RegisterModule",
2053  "Problems declaring payload for module %s.", modulename) ;
2054  }
2055  }
2056  }
2057 
2058  // Now that all the header have been registered/compiled, let's
2059  // make sure to 'reset' the TClass that have a class init in this module
2060  // but already had their type information available (using information/header
2061  // loaded from other modules or from class rules).
2062  if (!ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded && !hasHeaderParsingOnDemand) {
2063  // This code is likely to be superseded by the similar code in LoadPCM,
2064  // and have been disabled, (inadvertently or awkwardly) by
2065  // commit 7903f09f3beea69e82ffba29f59fb2d656a4fd54 (Refactor the routines used for header parsing on demand)
2066  // whereas it seems that a more semantically correct conditional would have
2067  // been 'if this module does not have a rootpcm'.
2068  // Note: this need to be review when the clang pcm are being installed.
2069  // #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
2070  while (!fClassesToUpdate.empty()) {
2071  TClass *oldcl = fClassesToUpdate.back().first;
2072  if (oldcl->GetState() != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
2073  // if (gDebug > 2) Info("RegisterModule", "Forcing TClass init for %s", oldcl->GetName());
2074  DictFuncPtr_t dict = fClassesToUpdate.back().second;
2075  fClassesToUpdate.pop_back();
2076  // Calling func could manipulate the list so, let maintain the list
2077  // then call the dictionary function.
2078  TClass *ncl = dict();
2079  if (ncl) ncl->PostLoadCheck();
2080  } else {
2081  fClassesToUpdate.pop_back();
2082  }
2083  }
2084  }
2085 
2086  if (!ModuleWasSuccessfullyLoaded && !hasHeaderParsingOnDemand) {
2087  // __ROOTCLING__ might be pulled in through PCH
2088  fInterpreter->declare("#ifdef __ROOTCLING__\n"
2089  "#undef __ROOTCLING__\n"
2090  + gInterpreterClassDef +
2091  "#endif");
2092  }
2093 
2094  if (wasDlopened) {
2095  assert(isSharedLib);
2096  void* dyLibHandle = fRegisterModuleDyLibs.back();
2097  fRegisterModuleDyLibs.pop_back();
2098  dlclose(dyLibHandle);
2099  }
2100 }

2112 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2113 /// If the dictionary is loaded, we can remove the class from the list
2114 /// (otherwise the class might be loaded twice).
2115 
2116 void TCling::UnRegisterTClassUpdate(const TClass *oldcl)
2117 {
2118  typedef std::vector<std::pair<TClass*,DictFuncPtr_t> >::iterator iterator;
2119  iterator stop = fClassesToUpdate.end();
2120  for(iterator i = fClassesToUpdate.begin();
2121  i != stop;
2122  ++i)
2123  {
2124  if ( i->first == oldcl ) {
2125  fClassesToUpdate.erase(i);
2126  return;
2127  }
2128  }
2129 }

2132 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2133 /// Let cling process a command line.
2134 ///
2135 /// If the command is executed and the error is 0, then the return value
2136 /// is the int value corresponding to the result of the executed command
2137 /// (float and double return values will be truncated).
2138 ///
2139 
2140 // Method for handling the interpreter exceptions.
2141 // the MetaProcessor is passing in as argument to teh function, because
2142 // cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult is a nested class and it cannot be
2143 // forward declared, thus this method cannot be a static member function
2144 // of TCling.
2145 
2146 static int HandleInterpreterException(cling::MetaProcessor* metaProcessor,
2147  const char* input_line,
2148  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult& compRes,
2149  cling::Value* result)
2150 {
2151  try {
2152  return metaProcessor->process(input_line, compRes, result);
2153  }
2154  catch (cling::InterpreterException& ex)
2155  {
2156  Error("HandleInterpreterException", "%s.\n%s", ex.what(), "Execution of your code was aborted.");
2157  ex.diagnose();
2158  compRes = cling::Interpreter::kFailure;
2159  }
2160  return 0;
2161 }
2162 
2163 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2164 
2165 bool TCling::DiagnoseIfInterpreterException(const std::exception &e) const
2166 {
2167  if (auto ie = dynamic_cast<const cling::InterpreterException*>(&e)) {
2168  ie->diagnose();
2169  return true;
2170  }
2171  return false;
2172 }
2173 
2174 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2175 
2176 Long_t TCling::ProcessLine(const char* line, EErrorCode* error/*=0*/)
2177 {
2178  // Copy the passed line, it comes from a static buffer in TApplication
2179  // which can be reentered through the Cling evaluation routines,
2180  // which would overwrite the static buffer and we would forget what we
2181  // were doing.
2182  //
2183  TString sLine(line);
2184  if (strstr(line,fantomline)) {
2185  // End-Of-Line action
2186  // See the comment (copied from above):
2187  // It is a "fantom" method to synchronize user keyboard input
2188  // and ROOT prompt line (for WIN32)
2189  // and is implemented by
2190  if (gApplication) {
2191  if (gApplication->IsCmdThread()) {
2192  R__LOCKGUARD(fLockProcessLine ? gInterpreterMutex : 0);
2193  gROOT->SetLineIsProcessing();
2194 
2195  UpdateAllCanvases();
2196 
2197  gROOT->SetLineHasBeenProcessed();
2198  }
2199  }
2200  return 0;
2201  }
2202 
2203  if (gGlobalMutex && !gInterpreterMutex && fLockProcessLine) {
2204  gGlobalMutex->Lock();
2205  if (!gInterpreterMutex)
2206  gInterpreterMutex = gGlobalMutex->Factory(kTRUE);
2207  gGlobalMutex->UnLock();
2208  }
2209  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(fLockProcessLine ? gInterpreterMutex : 0);
2210  gROOT->SetLineIsProcessing();
2211 
2212  struct InterpreterFlagsRAII {
2213  cling::Interpreter* fInterpreter;
2214  bool fWasDynamicLookupEnabled;
2215 
2216  InterpreterFlagsRAII(cling::Interpreter* interp):
2217  fInterpreter(interp),
2218  fWasDynamicLookupEnabled(interp->isDynamicLookupEnabled())
2219  {
2220  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup(true);
2221  }
2222  ~InterpreterFlagsRAII() {
2223  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup(fWasDynamicLookupEnabled);
2224  gROOT->SetLineHasBeenProcessed();
2225  }
2226  } interpreterFlagsRAII(fInterpreter);
2227 
2228  // A non-zero returned value means the given line was
2229  // not a complete statement.
2230  int indent = 0;
2231  // This will hold the resulting value of the evaluation the given line.
2232  cling::Value result;
2233  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult compRes = cling::Interpreter::kSuccess;
2234  if (!strncmp(sLine.Data(), ".L", 2) || !strncmp(sLine.Data(), ".x", 2) ||
2235  !strncmp(sLine.Data(), ".X", 2)) {
2236  // If there was a trailing "+", then CINT compiled the code above,
2237  // and we will need to strip the "+" before passing the line to cling.
2238  TString mod_line(sLine);
2239  TString aclicMode;
2240  TString arguments;
2241  TString io;
2242  TString fname = gSystem->SplitAclicMode(sLine.Data() + 3,
2243  aclicMode, arguments, io);
2244  if (aclicMode.Length()) {
2245  // Remove the leading '+'
2246  R__ASSERT(aclicMode[0]=='+' && "ACLiC mode must start with a +");
2247  aclicMode[0]='k'; // We always want to keep the .so around.
2248  if (aclicMode[1]=='+') {
2249  // We have a 2nd +
2250  aclicMode[1]='f'; // We want to force the recompilation.
2251  }
2252  if (!gSystem->CompileMacro(fname,aclicMode)) {
2253  // ACLiC failed.
2254  compRes = cling::Interpreter::kFailure;
2255  } else {
2256  if (strncmp(sLine.Data(), ".L", 2) != 0) {
2257  // if execution was requested.
2258 
2259  if (arguments.Length()==0) {
2260  arguments = "()";
2261  }
2262  // We need to remove the extension.
2263  Ssiz_t ext = fname.Last('.');
2264  if (ext != kNPOS) {
2265  fname.Remove(ext);
2266  }
2267  const char *function = gSystem->BaseName(fname);
2268  mod_line = function + arguments + io;
2269  indent = HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, mod_line, compRes, &result);
2270  }
2271  }
2272  } else {
2273  // not ACLiC
2274  size_t unnamedMacroOpenCurly;
2275  {
2276  std::string code;
2277  std::string codeline;
2278  std::ifstream in(fname);
2279  while (in) {
2280  std::getline(in, codeline);
2281  code += codeline + "\n";
2282  }
2283  unnamedMacroOpenCurly
2284  = cling::utils::isUnnamedMacro(code, fInterpreter->getCI()->getLangOpts());
2285  }
2286 
2287  fCurExecutingMacros.push_back(fname);
2288  if (unnamedMacroOpenCurly != std::string::npos) {
2289  compRes = fMetaProcessor->readInputFromFile(fname.Data(), &result,
2290  unnamedMacroOpenCurly);
2291  } else {
2292  // No DynLookup for .x, .L of named macros.
2293  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup(false);
2294  indent = HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, mod_line, compRes, &result);
2295  }
2296  fCurExecutingMacros.pop_back();
2297  }
2298  } // .L / .X / .x
2299  else {
2300  if (0!=strncmp(sLine.Data(), ".autodict ",10) && sLine != ".autodict") {
2301  // explicitly ignore .autodict without having to support it
2302  // in cling.
2303 
2304  // Turn off autoparsing if this is an include directive
2305  bool isInclusionDirective = sLine.Contains("\n#include") || sLine.BeginsWith("#include");
2306  if (isInclusionDirective) {
2307  SuspendAutoParsing autoParseRaii(this);
2308  indent = HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, sLine, compRes, &result);
2309  } else {
2310  indent = HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, sLine, compRes, &result);
2311  }
2312  }
2313  }
2314  if (result.isValid())
2315  RegisterTemporary(result);
2316  if (indent) {
2317  if (error)
2318  *error = kProcessing;
2319  return 0;
2320  }
2321  if (error) {
2322  switch (compRes) {
2323  case cling::Interpreter::kSuccess: *error = kNoError; break;
2324  case cling::Interpreter::kFailure: *error = kRecoverable; break;
2325  case cling::Interpreter::kMoreInputExpected: *error = kProcessing; break;
2326  }
2327  }
2328  if (compRes == cling::Interpreter::kSuccess
2329  && result.isValid()
2330  && !result.isVoid())
2331  {
2332  return result.simplisticCastAs<long>();
2333  }
2334  return 0;
2335 }
