2344 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2345 /// Add the given path to the list of directories in which the interpreter
2346 /// looks for include files. Only one path item can be specified at a
2347 /// time, i.e. "path1:path2" is NOT supported.
2348 
2349 void TCling::AddIncludePath(const char *path)
2350 {
2351  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2352  // Favorite source of annoyance: gSystem->AddIncludePath() needs "-I",
2353  // gCling->AddIncludePath() does not! Work around that inconsistency:
2354  if (path[0] == '-' && path[1] == 'I')
2355  path += 2;
2356 
2357  fInterpreter->AddIncludePath(path);
2358 }
2359 
2360 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2361 /// Visit all members over members, recursing over base classes.
2362 
2363 void TCling::InspectMembers(TMemberInspector& insp, const void* obj,
2364  const TClass* cl, Bool_t isTransient)
2365 {
2366  if (insp.GetObjectValidity() == TMemberInspector::kUnset) {
2367  insp.SetObjectValidity(obj ? TMemberInspector::kValidObjectGiven
2368  : TMemberInspector::kNoObjectGiven);
2369  }
2370 
2371  if (!cl || cl->GetCollectionProxy()) {
2372  // We do not need to investigate the content of the STL
2373  // collection, they are opaque to us (and details are
2374  // uninteresting).
2375  return;
2376  }
2377 
2378  static const TClassRef clRefString("std::string");
2379  if (clRefString == cl) {
2380  // We stream std::string without going through members..
2381  return;
2382  }
2383 
2384  if (TClassEdit::IsStdArray(cl->GetName())) {
2385  // We treat std arrays as C arrays
2386  return;
2387  }
2388 
2389  const char* cobj = (const char*) obj; // for ptr arithmetics
2390 
2391  // Treat the case of std::complex in a special manner. We want to enforce
2392  // the layout of a stl implementation independent class, which is the
2393  // complex as implemented in ROOT5.
2394 
2395  // A simple lambda to simplify the code
2396  auto inspInspect = [&] (ptrdiff_t offset){
2397  insp.Inspect(const_cast<TClass*>(cl), insp.GetParent(), "_real", cobj, isTransient);
2398  insp.Inspect(const_cast<TClass*>(cl), insp.GetParent(), "_imag", cobj + offset, isTransient);
2399  };
2400 
2401  auto complexType = TClassEdit::GetComplexType(cl->GetName());
2402  switch(complexType) {
2403  case TClassEdit::EComplexType::kNone:
2404  {
2405  break;
2406  }
2407  case TClassEdit::EComplexType::kFloat:
2408  {
2409  inspInspect(sizeof(float));
2410  return;
2411  }
2412  case TClassEdit::EComplexType::kDouble:
2413  {
2414  inspInspect(sizeof(double));
2415  return;
2416  }
2417  case TClassEdit::EComplexType::kInt:
2418  {
2419  inspInspect(sizeof(int));
2420  return;
2421  }
2422  case TClassEdit::EComplexType::kLong:
2423  {
2424  inspInspect(sizeof(long));
2425  return;
2426  }
2427  }
2428 
2429  static clang::PrintingPolicy
2430  printPol(fInterpreter->getCI()->getLangOpts());
2431  if (printPol.Indentation) {
2432  // not yet initialized
2433  printPol.Indentation = 0;
2434  printPol.SuppressInitializers = true;
2435  }
2436 
2437  const char* clname = cl->GetName();
2438  // Printf("Inspecting class %s\n", clname);
2439 
2440  const clang::ASTContext& astContext = fInterpreter->getCI()->getASTContext();
2441  const clang::Decl *scopeDecl = 0;
2442  const clang::Type *recordType = 0;
2443 
2444  if (cl->GetClassInfo()) {
2445  TClingClassInfo * clingCI = (TClingClassInfo *)cl->GetClassInfo();
2446  scopeDecl = clingCI->GetDecl();
2447  recordType = clingCI->GetType();
2448  } else {
2449  const cling::LookupHelper& lh = fInterpreter->getLookupHelper();
2450  // Diags will complain about private classes:
2451  scopeDecl = lh.findScope(clname, cling::LookupHelper::NoDiagnostics,
2452  &recordType);
2453  }
2454  if (!scopeDecl) {
2455  Error("InspectMembers", "Cannot find Decl for class %s", clname);
2456  return;
2457  }
2458  const clang::CXXRecordDecl* recordDecl
2459  = llvm::dyn_cast<const clang::CXXRecordDecl>(scopeDecl);
2460  if (!recordDecl) {
2461  Error("InspectMembers", "Cannot find Decl for class %s is not a CXXRecordDecl.", clname);
2462  return;
2463  }
2464 
2465  {
2466  // Force possible deserializations first. We need to have no pending
2467  // Transaction when passing control flow to the inspector below (ROOT-7779).
2468  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII deserRAII(fInterpreter);
2469 
2470  astContext.getASTRecordLayout(recordDecl);
2471 
2472  for (clang::RecordDecl::field_iterator iField = recordDecl->field_begin(),
2473  eField = recordDecl->field_end(); iField != eField; ++iField) {}
2474  }
2475 
2476  const clang::ASTRecordLayout& recLayout
2477  = astContext.getASTRecordLayout(recordDecl);
2478 
2479  // TVirtualCollectionProxy *proxy = cl->GetCollectionProxy();
2480  // if (proxy && ( proxy->GetProperties() & TVirtualCollectionProxy::kIsEmulated ) ) {
2481  // Error("InspectMembers","The TClass for %s has an emulated proxy but we are looking at a compiled version of the collection!\n",
2482  // cl->GetName());
2483  // }
2484  if (cl->Size() != recLayout.getSize().getQuantity()) {
2485  Error("InspectMembers","TClass and cling disagree on the size of the class %s, respectively %d %lld\n",
2486  cl->GetName(),cl->Size(),(Long64_t)recLayout.getSize().getQuantity());
2487  }
2488 
2489  unsigned iNField = 0;
2490  // iterate over fields
2491  // FieldDecls are non-static, else it would be a VarDecl.
2492  for (clang::RecordDecl::field_iterator iField = recordDecl->field_begin(),
2493  eField = recordDecl->field_end(); iField != eField;
2494  ++iField, ++iNField) {
2495 
2496 
2497  clang::QualType memberQT = iField->getType();
2498  if (recordType) {
2499  // if (we_need_to_do_the_subst_because_the_class_is_a_template_instance_of_double32_t)
2500  memberQT = ROOT::TMetaUtils::ReSubstTemplateArg(memberQT, recordType);
2501  }
2502  memberQT = cling::utils::Transform::GetPartiallyDesugaredType(astContext, memberQT, fNormalizedCtxt->GetConfig(), false /* fully qualify */);
2503  if (memberQT.isNull()) {
2504  std::string memberName;
2505  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(memberName);
2506  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
2507  printPol.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
2508  iField->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, printPol, true /*fqi*/);
2509  stream.flush();
2510  Error("InspectMembers",
2511  "Cannot retrieve QualType for member %s while inspecting class %s",
2512  memberName.c_str(), clname);
2513  continue; // skip member
2514  }
2515  const clang::Type* memType = memberQT.getTypePtr();
2516  if (!memType) {
2517  std::string memberName;
2518  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(memberName);
2519  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
2520  printPol.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
2521  iField->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, printPol, true /*fqi*/);
2522  stream.flush();
2523  Error("InspectMembers",
2524  "Cannot retrieve Type for member %s while inspecting class %s",
2525  memberName.c_str(), clname);
2526  continue; // skip member
2527  }
2528 
2529  const clang::Type* memNonPtrType = memType;
2530  Bool_t ispointer = false;
2531  if (memNonPtrType->isPointerType()) {
2532  ispointer = true;
2533  clang::QualType ptrQT
2534  = memNonPtrType->getAs<clang::PointerType>()->getPointeeType();
2535  if (recordType) {
2536  // if (we_need_to_do_the_subst_because_the_class_is_a_template_instance_of_double32_t)
2537  ptrQT = ROOT::TMetaUtils::ReSubstTemplateArg(ptrQT, recordType);
2538  }
2539  ptrQT = cling::utils::Transform::GetPartiallyDesugaredType(astContext, ptrQT, fNormalizedCtxt->GetConfig(), false /* fully qualify */);
2540  if (ptrQT.isNull()) {
2541  std::string memberName;
2542  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(memberName);
2543  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
2544  printPol.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
2545  iField->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, printPol, true /*fqi*/);
2546  stream.flush();
2547  Error("InspectMembers",
2548  "Cannot retrieve pointee Type for member %s while inspecting class %s",
2549  memberName.c_str(), clname);
2550  continue; // skip member
2551  }
2552  memNonPtrType = ptrQT.getTypePtr();
2553  }
2554 
2555  // assemble array size(s): "[12][4][]"
2556  llvm::SmallString<8> arraySize;
2557  const clang::ArrayType* arrType = memNonPtrType->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
2558  unsigned arrLevel = 0;
2559  bool haveErrorDueToArray = false;
2560  while (arrType) {
2561  ++arrLevel;
2562  arraySize += '[';
2563  const clang::ConstantArrayType* constArrType =
2564  clang::dyn_cast<clang::ConstantArrayType>(arrType);
2565  if (constArrType) {
2566  constArrType->getSize().toStringUnsigned(arraySize);
2567  }
2568  arraySize += ']';
2569  clang::QualType subArrQT = arrType->getElementType();
2570  if (subArrQT.isNull()) {
2571  std::string memberName;
2572  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(memberName);
2573  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
2574  printPol.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
2575  iField->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, printPol, true /*fqi*/);
2576  stream.flush();
2577  Error("InspectMembers",
2578  "Cannot retrieve QualType for array level %d (i.e. element type of %s) for member %s while inspecting class %s",
2579  arrLevel, subArrQT.getAsString(printPol).c_str(),
2580  memberName.c_str(), clname);
2581  haveErrorDueToArray = true;
2582  break;
2583  }
2584  arrType = subArrQT.getTypePtr()->getAsArrayTypeUnsafe();
2585  }
2586  if (haveErrorDueToArray) {
2587  continue; // skip member
2588  }
2589 
2590  // construct member name
2591  std::string fieldName;
2592  if (memType->isPointerType()) {
2593  fieldName = "*";
2594  }
2595 
2596  // Check if this field has a custom ioname, if not, just use the one of the decl
2597  std::string ioname(iField->getName());
2598  ROOT::TMetaUtils::ExtractAttrPropertyFromName(**iField,"ioname",ioname);
2599  fieldName += ioname;
2600  fieldName += arraySize;
2601 
2602  // get member offset
2603  // NOTE currently we do not support bitfield and do not support
2604  // member that are not aligned on 'bit' boundaries.
2605  clang::CharUnits offset(astContext.toCharUnitsFromBits(recLayout.getFieldOffset(iNField)));
2606  ptrdiff_t fieldOffset = offset.getQuantity();
2607 
2608  // R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__insp.GetParent(), "fBits[2]", fBits);
2609  // R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__insp.GetParent(), "fName", &fName);
2610  // R__insp.InspectMember(fName, "fName.");
2611  // R__insp.Inspect(R__cl, R__insp.GetParent(), "*fClass", &fClass);
2612 
2613  // If the class has a custom streamer and the type of the filed is a
2614  // private enum, struct or class, skip it.
2615  if (!insp.IsTreatingNonAccessibleTypes()){
2616  auto iFiledQtype = iField->getType();
2617  if (auto tagDecl = iFiledQtype->getAsTagDecl()){
2618  auto declAccess = tagDecl->getAccess();
2619  if (declAccess == AS_private || declAccess == AS_protected) {
2620  continue;
2621  }
2622  }
2623  }
2624 
2625  insp.Inspect(const_cast<TClass*>(cl), insp.GetParent(), fieldName.c_str(), cobj + fieldOffset, isTransient);
2626 
2627  if (!ispointer) {
2628  const clang::CXXRecordDecl* fieldRecDecl = memNonPtrType->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2629  if (fieldRecDecl) {
2630  // nested objects get an extra call to InspectMember
2631  // R__insp.InspectMember("FileStat_t", (void*)&fFileStat, "fFileStat.", false);
2632  std::string sFieldRecName;
2633  if (!ROOT::TMetaUtils::ExtractAttrPropertyFromName(*fieldRecDecl,"iotype",sFieldRecName)){
2634  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetNormalizedName(sFieldRecName,
2635  clang::QualType(memNonPtrType,0),
2636  *fInterpreter,
2637  *fNormalizedCtxt);
2638  }
2639 
2640  TDataMember* mbr = cl->GetDataMember(ioname.c_str());
2641  // if we can not find the member (which should not really happen),
2642  // let's consider it transient.
2643  Bool_t transient = isTransient || !mbr || !mbr->IsPersistent();
2644 
2645  insp.InspectMember(sFieldRecName.c_str(), cobj + fieldOffset,
2646  (fieldName + '.').c_str(), transient);
2647 
2648  }
2649  }
2650  } // loop over fields
2651 
2652  // inspect bases
2653  // TNamed::ShowMembers(R__insp);
2654  unsigned iNBase = 0;
2655  for (clang::CXXRecordDecl::base_class_const_iterator iBase
2656  = recordDecl->bases_begin(), eBase = recordDecl->bases_end();
2657  iBase != eBase; ++iBase, ++iNBase) {
2658  clang::QualType baseQT = iBase->getType();
2659  if (baseQT.isNull()) {
2660  Error("InspectMembers",
2661  "Cannot find QualType for base number %d while inspecting class %s",
2662  iNBase, clname);
2663  continue;
2664  }
2665  const clang::CXXRecordDecl* baseDecl
2666  = baseQT->getAsCXXRecordDecl();
2667  if (!baseDecl) {
2668  Error("InspectMembers",
2669  "Cannot find CXXRecordDecl for base number %d while inspecting class %s",
2670  iNBase, clname);
2671  continue;
2672  }
2673  TClass* baseCl=nullptr;
2674  std::string sBaseName;
2675  // Try with the DeclId
2676  std::vector<TClass*> foundClasses;
2677  TClass::GetClass(static_cast<DeclId_t>(baseDecl), foundClasses);
2678  if (foundClasses.size()==1){
2679  baseCl=foundClasses[0];
2680  } else {
2681  // Try with the normalised Name, as a fallback
2682  if (!baseCl){
2683  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetNormalizedName(sBaseName,
2684  baseQT,
2685  *fInterpreter,
2686  *fNormalizedCtxt);
2687  baseCl = TClass::GetClass(sBaseName.c_str());
2688  }
2689  }
2690 
2691  if (!baseCl){
2692  std::string qualNameForDiag;
2693  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetQualifiedName(qualNameForDiag, *baseDecl);
2694  Error("InspectMembers",
2695  "Cannot find TClass for base class %s", qualNameForDiag.c_str() );
2696  continue;
2697  }
2698 
2699  int64_t baseOffset;
2700  if (iBase->isVirtual()) {
2701  if (insp.GetObjectValidity() == TMemberInspector::kNoObjectGiven) {
2702  if (!isTransient) {
2703  Error("InspectMembers",
2704  "Base %s of class %s is virtual but no object provided",
2705  sBaseName.c_str(), clname);
2706  }
2707  baseOffset = TVirtualStreamerInfo::kNeedObjectForVirtualBaseClass;
2708  } else {
2709  // We have an object to determine the vbase offset.
2710  TClingClassInfo* ci = (TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo();
2711  TClingClassInfo* baseCi = (TClingClassInfo*)baseCl->GetClassInfo();
2712  if (ci && baseCi) {
2713  baseOffset = ci->GetBaseOffset(baseCi, const_cast<void*>(obj),
2714  true /*isDerivedObj*/);
2715  if (baseOffset == -1) {
2716  Error("InspectMembers",
2717  "Error calculating offset of virtual base %s of class %s",
2718  sBaseName.c_str(), clname);
2719  }
2720  } else {
2721  Error("InspectMembers",
2722  "Cannot calculate offset of virtual base %s of class %s",
2723  sBaseName.c_str(), clname);
2724  continue;
2725  }
2726  }
2727  } else {
2728  baseOffset = recLayout.getBaseClassOffset(baseDecl).getQuantity();
2729  }
2730  // TOFIX: baseCl can be null here!
2731  if (baseCl->IsLoaded()) {
2732  // For loaded class, CallShowMember will (especially for TObject)
2733  // call the virtual ShowMember rather than the class specific version
2734  // resulting in an infinite recursion.
2735  InspectMembers(insp, cobj + baseOffset, baseCl, isTransient);
2736  } else {
2737  baseCl->CallShowMembers(cobj + baseOffset,
2738  insp, isTransient);
2739  }
2740  } // loop over bases
2741 }

2760 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2761 /// Declare code to the interpreter, without any of the interpreter actions
2762 /// that could trigger a re-interpretation of the code. I.e. make cling
2763 /// behave like a compiler: no dynamic lookup, no input wrapping for
2764 /// subsequent execution, no automatic provision of declarations but just a
2765 /// plain #include.
2766 /// Returns true on success, false on failure.
2767 
2768 bool TCling::Declare(const char* code)
2769 {
2770  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
2771 
2772  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoLoadOff(this);
2773  SuspendAutoParsing autoParseRaii(this);
2774 
2775  bool oldDynLookup = fInterpreter->isDynamicLookupEnabled();
2776  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup(false);
2777  bool oldRawInput = fInterpreter->isRawInputEnabled();
2778  fInterpreter->enableRawInput(true);
2779 
2780  Bool_t ret = LoadText(code);
2781 
2782  fInterpreter->enableRawInput(oldRawInput);
2783  fInterpreter->enableDynamicLookup(oldDynLookup);
2784  return ret;
2785 }

2787 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2788 /// Enable the automatic loading of shared libraries when a class
2789 /// is used that is stored in a not yet loaded library. Uses the
2790 /// information stored in the class/library map (typically
2791 /// $ROOTSYS/etc/system.rootmap).
2792 
2793 void TCling::EnableAutoLoading()
2794 {
2795  if (fAllowLibLoad) {
2796  LoadLibraryMap();
2797  SetClassAutoloading(true);
2798  }
2799 }

2801 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2802 /// It calls a "fantom" method to synchronize user keyboard input
2803 /// and ROOT prompt line.

2810 // This static function is a hop of TCling::IsLibraryLoaded, which is taking a lock and calling
2811 // into this function. This is because we wanted to avoid a duplication in TCling::IsLoaded, which
2812 // was already taking a lock.
2813 static Bool_t s_IsLibraryLoaded(const char* libname, cling::Interpreter* fInterpreter)
2814 {
2815  // Check shared library.
2816  TString tLibName(libname);
2817  if (gSystem->FindDynamicLibrary(tLibName, kTRUE))
2818  return fInterpreter->getDynamicLibraryManager()->isLibraryLoaded(tLibName.Data());
2819  return false;
2820 }
2821 
2822 Bool_t TCling::IsLibraryLoaded(const char* libname) const
2823 {
2824  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2825  return s_IsLibraryLoaded(libname, fInterpreter);
2826 }

2828 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2829 /// Return true if ROOT has cxxmodules pcm for a given library name.
2830 // FIXME: We need to be able to support lazy loading of pcm generated by ACLiC.
2831 Bool_t TCling::HasPCMForLibrary(const char *libname) const
2832 {
2833  llvm::StringRef ModuleName(libname);
2834  ModuleName = llvm::sys::path::stem(ModuleName);
2835  ModuleName.consume_front("lib");
2836 
2837  clang::ModuleMap &moduleMap = fInterpreter->getCI()->getPreprocessor().getHeaderSearchInfo().getModuleMap();
2838  clang::Module *M = moduleMap.findModule(ModuleName);
2839  return M && !M->IsMissingRequirement && M->getASTFile();
2840 }
2841 
2842 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2843 /// Return true if the file has already been loaded by cint.
2844 /// We will try in this order:
2845 /// actual filename
2846 /// filename as a path relative to
2847 /// the include path
2848 /// the shared library path
2849 
2850 Bool_t TCling::IsLoaded(const char* filename) const
2851 {
2852  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
2853 
2854  //FIXME: if we use llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute all this can go away. See
2855  // cling::DynamicLibraryManager.
2856 
2857  std::string file_name = filename;
2858  size_t at = std::string::npos;
2859  while ((at = file_name.find("/./")) != std::string::npos)
2860  file_name.replace(at, 3, "/");
2861 
2862  std::string filesStr = "";
2863  llvm::raw_string_ostream filesOS(filesStr);
2864  clang::SourceManager &SM = fInterpreter->getCI()->getSourceManager();
2865  cling::ClangInternalState::printIncludedFiles(filesOS, SM);
2866  filesOS.flush();
2867 
2868  llvm::SmallVector<llvm::StringRef, 100> files;
2869  llvm::StringRef(filesStr).split(files, "\n");
2870 
2871  std::set<std::string> fileMap;
2872  // Fill fileMap; return early on exact match.
2873  for (llvm::SmallVector<llvm::StringRef, 100>::const_iterator
2874  iF = files.begin(), iE = files.end(); iF != iE; ++iF) {
2875  if ((*iF) == file_name.c_str()) return kTRUE; // exact match
2876  fileMap.insert(*iF);
2877  }
2878 
2879  if (fileMap.empty()) return kFALSE;
2880 
2881  // Check MacroPath.
2882  TString sFilename(file_name.c_str());
2883  if (gSystem->FindFile(TROOT::GetMacroPath(), sFilename, kReadPermission)
2884  && fileMap.count(sFilename.Data())) {
2885  return kTRUE;
2886  }
2887 
2888  // Check IncludePath.
2889  TString incPath = gSystem->GetIncludePath(); // of the form -Idir1 -Idir2 -Idir3
2890  incPath.Append(":").Prepend(" "); // to match " -I" (note leading ' ')
2891  incPath.ReplaceAll(" -I", ":"); // of form :dir1 :dir2:dir3
2892  while (incPath.Index(" :") != -1) {
2893  incPath.ReplaceAll(" :", ":");
2894  }
2895  incPath.Prepend(".:");
2896  sFilename = file_name.c_str();
2897  if (gSystem->FindFile(incPath, sFilename, kReadPermission)
2898  && fileMap.count(sFilename.Data())) {
2899  return kTRUE;
2900  }
2901 
2902  // Check shared library.
2903  if (s_IsLibraryLoaded(file_name.c_str(), fInterpreter))
2904  return kTRUE;
2905 
2906  //FIXME: We must use the cling::Interpreter::lookupFileOrLibrary iface.
2907  const clang::DirectoryLookup *CurDir = 0;
2908  clang::Preprocessor &PP = fInterpreter->getCI()->getPreprocessor();
2909  clang::HeaderSearch &HS = PP.getHeaderSearchInfo();
2910  const clang::FileEntry *FE = HS.LookupFile(file_name.c_str(),
2911  clang::SourceLocation(),
2912  /*isAngled*/ false,
2913  /*FromDir*/ 0, CurDir,
2914  clang::ArrayRef<std::pair<const clang::FileEntry *,
2915  const clang::DirectoryEntry *>>(),
2916  /*SearchPath*/ 0,
2917  /*RelativePath*/ 0,
2918  /*RequestingModule*/ 0,
2919  /*SuggestedModule*/ 0,
2920  /*IsMapped*/ 0,
2921  /*SkipCache*/ false,
2922  /*BuildSystemModule*/ false,
2923  /*OpenFile*/ false,
2924  /*CacheFail*/ false);
2925  if (FE && FE->isValid()) {
2926  // check in the source manager if the file is actually loaded
2927  clang::SourceManager &SM = fInterpreter->getCI()->getSourceManager();
2928  // this works only with header (and source) files...
2929  clang::FileID FID = SM.translateFile(FE);
2930  if (!FID.isInvalid() && FID.getHashValue() == 0)
2931  return kFALSE;
2932  else {
2933  clang::SrcMgr::SLocEntry SLocE = SM.getSLocEntry(FID);
2934  if (SLocE.isFile() && SLocE.getFile().getContentCache()->getRawBuffer() == 0)
2935  return kFALSE;
2936  if (!FID.isInvalid())
2937  return kTRUE;
2938  }
2939  // ...then check shared library again, but with full path now
2940  sFilename = FE->getName();
2941  if (gSystem->FindDynamicLibrary(sFilename, kTRUE)
2942  && fileMap.count(sFilename.Data())) {
2943  return kTRUE;
2944  }
2945  }
2946  return kFALSE;
2947 }
2948 
2949 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2950 
2951 void TCling::UpdateListOfLoadedSharedLibraries()
2952 {
2953 #if defined(R__WIN32) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
2954  HMODULE hModules[1024];
2955  void *hProcess;
2956  unsigned long cbModules;
2957  unsigned int i;
2958  hProcess = (void *)::GetCurrentProcess();
2959  ::EnumProcessModules(hProcess, hModules, sizeof(hModules), &cbModules);
2960  // start at 1 to skip the executable itself
2961  for (i = 1; i < (cbModules / sizeof(void *)); i++) {
2962  static const int bufsize = 260;
2963  wchar_t winname[bufsize];
2964  char posixname[bufsize];
2965  ::GetModuleFileNameExW(hProcess, hModules[i], winname, bufsize);
2966 #if defined(__CYGWIN__)
2967  cygwin_conv_path(CCP_WIN_W_TO_POSIX, winname, posixname, bufsize);
2968 #else
2969  std::wstring wpath = winname;
2970  std::replace(wpath.begin(), wpath.end(), '\\', '/');
2971  string path(wpath.begin(), wpath.end());
2972  strncpy(posixname, path.c_str(), bufsize);
2973 #endif
2974  if (!fSharedLibs.Contains(posixname)) {
2975  RegisterLoadedSharedLibrary(posixname);
2976  }
2977  }
2978 #elif defined(R__MACOSX)
2979  // fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo stores the *next* image index to look at
2980  uint32_t imageIndex = (uint32_t) (size_t) fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo;
2981 
2982  while (const mach_header* mh = _dyld_get_image_header(imageIndex)) {
2983  // Skip non-dylibs
2984  if (mh->filetype == MH_DYLIB) {
2985  if (const char* imageName = _dyld_get_image_name(imageIndex)) {
2986  RegisterLoadedSharedLibrary(imageName);
2987  }
2988  }
2989 
2990  ++imageIndex;
2991  }
2992  fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo = (void*)(size_t)imageIndex;
2993 #elif defined(R__LINUX)
2994  struct PointerNo4 {
2995  void* fSkip[3];
2996  void* fPtr;
2997  };
2998  struct LinkMap {
2999  void* fAddr;
3000  const char* fName;
3001  void* fLd;
3002  LinkMap* fNext;
3003  LinkMap* fPrev;
3004  };
3005  if (!fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo || fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo == (void*)(size_t)-1) {
3006  PointerNo4* procLinkMap = (PointerNo4*)dlopen(0, RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_GLOBAL);
3007  // 4th pointer of 4th pointer is the linkmap.
3008  // See http://syprog.blogspot.fr/2011/12/listing-loaded-shared-objects-in-linux.html
3009  LinkMap* linkMap = (LinkMap*) ((PointerNo4*)procLinkMap->fPtr)->fPtr;
3010  RegisterLoadedSharedLibrary(linkMap->fName);
3011  fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo = linkMap;
3012  // reduce use count of link map structure:
3013  dlclose(procLinkMap);
3014  }
3015 
3016  LinkMap* iDyLib = (LinkMap*)fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo;
3017  while (iDyLib->fNext) {
3018  iDyLib = iDyLib->fNext;
3019  RegisterLoadedSharedLibrary(iDyLib->fName);
3020  }
3021  fPrevLoadedDynLibInfo = iDyLib;
3022 #else
3023  Error("TCling::UpdateListOfLoadedSharedLibraries",
3024  "Platform not supported!");
3025 #endif
3026 }
3027 
3028 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3029 /// Register a new shared library name with the interpreter; add it to
3030 /// fSharedLibs.
3031 
3032 void TCling::RegisterLoadedSharedLibrary(const char* filename)
3033 {
3034  // Ignore NULL filenames, aka "the process".
3035  if (!filename) return;
3036 
3037  // Tell the interpreter that this library is available; all libraries can be
3038  // used to resolve symbols.
3039  cling::DynamicLibraryManager* DLM = fInterpreter->getDynamicLibraryManager();
3040  if (!DLM->isLibraryLoaded(filename)) {
3041  DLM->loadLibrary(filename, true /*permanent*/);
3042  }
3043 
3044 #if defined(R__MACOSX)
3045  // Check that this is not a system library
3046  auto lenFilename = strlen(filename);
3047  if (!strncmp(filename, "/usr/lib/system/", 16)
3048  || !strncmp(filename, "/usr/lib/libc++", 15)
3049  || !strncmp(filename, "/System/Library/Frameworks/", 27)
3050  || !strncmp(filename, "/System/Library/PrivateFrameworks/", 34)
3051  || !strncmp(filename, "/System/Library/CoreServices/", 29)
3052  || !strcmp(filename, "cl_kernels") // yepp, no directory
3053  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libSystem")
3054  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libstdc++")
3055  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libicucore")
3056  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libbsm")
3057  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libobjc")
3058  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libresolv")
3059  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libauto")
3060  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libcups")
3061  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libDiagnosticMessagesClient")
3062  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/liblangid")
3063  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libCRFSuite")
3064  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libpam")
3065  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libOpenScriptingUtil")
3066  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libextension")
3067  || strstr(filename, "/usr/lib/libAudioToolboxUtility")
3068  // "cannot link directly with dylib/framework, your binary is not an allowed client of
3069  // /Applications/Xcode-beta.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/MacOSX.platform/Developer/
3070  // SDKs/MacOSX.sdk/usr/lib/libAudioToolboxUtility.tbd for architecture x86_64
3071  || (lenFilename > 4 && !strcmp(filename + lenFilename - 4, ".tbd")))
3072  return;
3073 #elif defined(__CYGWIN__)
3074  // Check that this is not a system library
3075  static const int bufsize = 260;
3076  char posixwindir[bufsize];
3077  char *windir = getenv("WINDIR");
3078  if (windir)
3079  cygwin_conv_path(CCP_WIN_A_TO_POSIX, windir, posixwindir, bufsize);
3080  else
3081  snprintf(posixwindir, sizeof(posixwindir), "/Windows/");
3082  if (strstr(filename, posixwindir) ||
3083  strstr(filename, "/usr/bin/cyg"))
3084  return;
3085 #elif defined(R__WIN32)
3086  if (strstr(filename, "/Windows/"))
3087  return;
3088 #elif defined (R__LINUX)
3089  if (strstr(filename, "/ld-linux")
3090  || strstr(filename, "linux-gnu/")
3091  || strstr(filename, "/libstdc++.")
3092  || strstr(filename, "/libgcc")
3093  || strstr(filename, "/libc.")
3094  || strstr(filename, "/libdl.")
3095  || strstr(filename, "/libm."))
3096  return;
3097 #endif
3098  // Update string of available libraries.
3099  if (!fSharedLibs.IsNull()) {
3100  fSharedLibs.Append(" ");
3101  }
3102  fSharedLibs.Append(filename);
3103 }

3105 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3106 /// Load a library file in cling's memory.
3107 /// if 'system' is true, the library is never unloaded.
3108 /// Return 0 on success, -1 on failure.
3109 
3110 Int_t TCling::Load(const char* filename, Bool_t system)
3111 {
3112  if (!fAllowLibLoad) {
3113  Error("Load","Trying to load library (%s) from rootcling.",filename);
3114  return -1;
3115  }
3116 
3117  // Used to return 0 on success, 1 on duplicate, -1 on failure, -2 on "fatal".
3118  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
3119  cling::DynamicLibraryManager* DLM = fInterpreter->getDynamicLibraryManager();
3120  std::string canonLib = DLM->lookupLibrary(filename);
3121  cling::DynamicLibraryManager::LoadLibResult res
3122  = cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibNotFound;
3123  if (!canonLib.empty()) {
3124  if (system)
3125  res = DLM->loadLibrary(filename, system);
3126  else {
3127  // For the non system libs, we'd like to be able to unload them.
3128  // FIXME: Here we lose the information about kLoadLibAlreadyLoaded case.
3129  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult compRes;
3130  HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, Form(".L %s", canonLib.c_str()), compRes, /*cling::Value*/0);
3131  if (compRes == cling::Interpreter::kSuccess)
3132  res = cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibSuccess;
3133  }
3134  }
3135 
3136  if (res == cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibSuccess) {
3137  UpdateListOfLoadedSharedLibraries();
3138  }
3139  switch (res) {
3140  case cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibSuccess: return 0;
3141  case cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibAlreadyLoaded: return 1;
3142  default: break;
3143  };
3144  return -1;
3145 }

3167 Long_t TCling::ProcessLineSynch(const char* line, EErrorCode* error)

3179 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3180 /// Directly execute an executable statement (e.g. "func()", "3+5", etc.
3181 /// however not declarations, like "Int_t x;").
3182 
3183 Long_t TCling::Calc(const char* line, EErrorCode* error)
3184 {
3185 #ifdef R__WIN32
3186  // Test on ApplicationImp not being 0 is needed because only at end of
3187  // TApplication ctor the IsLineProcessing flag is set to 0, so before
3188  // we can not use it.
3189  if (gApplication && gApplication->GetApplicationImp()) {
3190  while (gROOT->IsLineProcessing() && !gApplication) {
3191  Warning("Calc", "waiting for cling thread to free");
3192  gSystem->Sleep(500);
3193  }
3194  gROOT->SetLineIsProcessing();
3195  }
3196 #endif // R__WIN32
3197  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
3198  if (error) {
3199  *error = TInterpreter::kNoError;
3200  }
3201  cling::Value valRef;
3202  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult cr = fInterpreter->evaluate(line, valRef);
3203  if (cr != cling::Interpreter::kSuccess) {
3204  // Failure in compilation.
3205  if (error) {
3206  // Note: Yes these codes are weird.
3207  *error = TInterpreter::kRecoverable;
3208  }
3209  return 0L;
3210  }
3211  if (!valRef.isValid()) {
3212  // Failure at runtime.
3213  if (error) {
3214  // Note: Yes these codes are weird.
3215  *error = TInterpreter::kDangerous;
3216  }
3217  return 0L;
3218  }
3219 
3220  if (valRef.isVoid()) {
3221  return 0;
3222  }
3223 
3224  RegisterTemporary(valRef);
3225 #ifdef R__WIN32
3226  if (gApplication && gApplication->GetApplicationImp()) {
3227  gROOT->SetLineHasBeenProcessed();
3228  }
3229 #endif // R__WIN32
3230  return valRef.simplisticCastAs<long>();
3231 }

3249 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3250 /// Helper function to increase the internal Cling count of transactions
3251 /// that change the AST.
3252 
3253 Bool_t TCling::HandleNewTransaction(const cling::Transaction &T)
3254 {
3255  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3256 
3257  if ((std::distance(T.decls_begin(), T.decls_end()) != 1)
3258  || T.deserialized_decls_begin() != T.deserialized_decls_end()
3259  || T.macros_begin() != T.macros_end()
3260  || ((!T.getFirstDecl().isNull()) && ((*T.getFirstDecl().begin()) != T.getWrapperFD()))) {
3261  fTransactionCount++;
3262  return true;
3263  }
3264  return false;
3265 }

3267 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3268 /// Delete object from cling symbol table so it can not be used anymore.
3269 /// cling objects are always on the heap.
3270 
3271 void TCling::RecursiveRemove(TObject* obj)
3272 {
3273  // NOTE: When replacing the mutex by a ReadWrite mutex, we **must**
3274  // put in place the Read/Write part here. Keeping the write lock
3275  // here is 'catasptrophic' for scaling as it means that ALL calls
3276  // to RecursiveRemove will take the write lock and performance
3277  // of many threads trying to access the write lock at the same
3278  // time is relatively bad.
3279  R__READ_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
3280  // Note that fgSetOfSpecials is supposed to be updated by TClingCallbacks::tryFindROOTSpecialInternal
3281  // (but isn't at the moment).
3282  if (obj->IsOnHeap() && fgSetOfSpecials && !((std::set<TObject*>*)fgSetOfSpecials)->empty()) {
3283  std::set<TObject*>::iterator iSpecial = ((std::set<TObject*>*)fgSetOfSpecials)->find(obj);
3284  if (iSpecial != ((std::set<TObject*>*)fgSetOfSpecials)->end()) {
3285  R__WRITE_LOCKGUARD(ROOT::gCoreMutex);
3286  DeleteGlobal(obj);
3287  ((std::set<TObject*>*)fgSetOfSpecials)->erase(iSpecial);
3288  }
3289  }
3290 }

3382 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3383 /// Undeclare obj called name.
3384 /// Returns 1 in case of success, 0 for failure.
3385 
3386 Int_t TCling::DeleteVariable(const char* name)
3387 {
3388 #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
3389 #if R__MUST_REVISIT(6,2)
3390  Warning("DeleteVariable","should do more that just reseting the value to zero");
3391 #endif
3392 #endif
3393 
3394  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3395  llvm::StringRef srName(name);
3396  const char* unscopedName = name;
3397  llvm::StringRef::size_type posScope = srName.rfind("::");
3398  const clang::DeclContext* declCtx = 0;
3399  if (posScope != llvm::StringRef::npos) {
3400  const cling::LookupHelper& lh = fInterpreter->getLookupHelper();
3401  const clang::Decl* scopeDecl
3402  = lh.findScope(srName.substr(0, posScope),
3403  cling::LookupHelper::WithDiagnostics);
3404  if (!scopeDecl) {
3405  Error("DeleteVariable", "Cannot find enclosing scope for variable %s",
3406  name);
3407  return 0;
3408  }
3409  declCtx = llvm::dyn_cast<clang::DeclContext>(scopeDecl);
3410  if (!declCtx) {
3411  Error("DeleteVariable",
3412  "Enclosing scope for variable %s is not a declaration context",
3413  name);
3414  return 0;
3415  }
3416  unscopedName += posScope + 2;
3417  }
3418  // Could trigger deserialization of decls.
3419  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII RAII(fInterpreter);
3420  clang::NamedDecl* nVarDecl
3421  = cling::utils::Lookup::Named(&fInterpreter->getSema(), unscopedName, declCtx);
3422  if (!nVarDecl) {
3423  Error("DeleteVariable", "Unknown variable %s", name);
3424  return 0;
3425  }
3426  clang::VarDecl* varDecl = llvm::dyn_cast<clang::VarDecl>(nVarDecl);
3427  if (!varDecl) {
3428  Error("DeleteVariable", "Entity %s is not a variable", name);
3429  return 0;
3430  }
3431 
3432  clang::QualType qType = varDecl->getType();
3433  const clang::Type* type = qType->getUnqualifiedDesugaredType();
3434  // Cannot set a reference's address to nullptr; the JIT can place it
3435  // into read-only memory (ROOT-7100).
3436  if (type->isPointerType()) {
3437  int** ppInt = (int**)fInterpreter->getAddressOfGlobal(GlobalDecl(varDecl));
3438  // set pointer to invalid.
3439  if (ppInt) *ppInt = 0;
3440  }
3441  return 1;
3442 }

3490 
3491 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3492 /// Check in what order the member of a tuple are layout.
3493 enum class ETupleOrdering {
3494  kAscending,
3495  kDescending,
3496  kUnexpected
3497 };
3498 
3499 struct AlternateTupleIntDoubleAsc
3500 {
3501  Int_t _0;
3502  Double_t _1;
3503 };
3504 
3505 struct AlternateTupleIntDoubleDes
3506 {
3507  Double_t _1;
3508  Int_t _0;
3509 };
3510 
3511 static ETupleOrdering IsTupleAscending()
3512 {
3513  std::tuple<int,double> value;
3514  AlternateTupleIntDoubleAsc asc;
3515  AlternateTupleIntDoubleDes des;
3516 
3517  size_t offset0 = ((char*)&(std::get<0>(value))) - ((char*)&value);
3518  size_t offset1 = ((char*)&(std::get<1>(value))) - ((char*)&value);
3519 
3520  size_t ascOffset0 = ((char*)&(asc._0)) - ((char*)&asc);
3521  size_t ascOffset1 = ((char*)&(asc._1)) - ((char*)&asc);
3522 
3523  size_t desOffset0 = ((char*)&(des._0)) - ((char*)&des);
3524  size_t desOffset1 = ((char*)&(des._1)) - ((char*)&des);
3525 
3526  if (offset0 == ascOffset0 && offset1 == ascOffset1) {
3527  return ETupleOrdering::kAscending;
3528  } else if (offset0 == desOffset0 && offset1 == desOffset1) {
3529  return ETupleOrdering::kDescending;
3530  } else {
3531  return ETupleOrdering::kUnexpected;
3532  }
3533 }
3534 
3535 std::string AlternateTuple(const char *classname)
3536 {
3537  TClassEdit::TSplitType tupleContent(classname);
3538  std::string alternateName = "TEmulatedTuple";
3539  alternateName.append( classname + 5 );
3540 
3541  std::string guard_name;
3542  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetCppName(guard_name,alternateName.c_str());
3543  std::ostringstream guard;
3544  guard << "ROOT_INTERNAL_TEmulated_";
3545  guard << guard_name;
3546 
3547  std::ostringstream alternateTuple;
3548  alternateTuple << "#ifndef " << guard.str() << "\n";
3549  alternateTuple << "#define " << guard.str() << "\n";
3550  alternateTuple << "namespace ROOT { namespace Internal {\n";
3551  alternateTuple << "template <class... Types> struct TEmulatedTuple;\n";
3552  alternateTuple << "template <> struct " << alternateName << " {\n";
3553 
3554  // This could also be a compile time choice ...
3555  switch(IsTupleAscending()) {
3556  case ETupleOrdering::kAscending: {
3557  unsigned int nMember = 0;
3558  auto iter = tupleContent.fElements.begin() + 1; // Skip the template name (tuple)
3559  auto theEnd = tupleContent.fElements.end() - 1; // skip the 'stars'.
3560  while (iter != theEnd) {
3561  alternateTuple << " " << *iter << " _" << nMember << ";\n";
3562  ++iter;
3563  ++nMember;
3564  }
3565  break;
3566  }
3567  case ETupleOrdering::kDescending: {
3568  unsigned int nMember = tupleContent.fElements.size() - 3;
3569  auto iter = tupleContent.fElements.rbegin() + 1; // Skip the template name (tuple)
3570  auto theEnd = tupleContent.fElements.rend() - 1; // skip the 'stars'.
3571  while (iter != theEnd) {
3572  alternateTuple << " " << *iter << " _" << nMember << ";\n";
3573  ++iter;
3574  --nMember;
3575  }
3576  break;
3577  }
3578  case ETupleOrdering::kUnexpected: {
3579  Fatal("TCling::SetClassInfo::AlternateTuple",
3580  "Layout of std::tuple on this platform is unexpected.");
3581  break;
3582  }
3583  }
3584 
3585  alternateTuple << "};\n";
3586  alternateTuple << "}}\n";
3587  alternateTuple << "#endif\n";
3588  if (!gCling->Declare(alternateTuple.str().c_str())) {
3589  Error("Load","Could not declare %s",alternateName.c_str());
3590  return "";
3591  }
3592  alternateName = "ROOT::Internal::" + alternateName;
3593  return alternateName;
3594 }
3595 
3596 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3597 /// Set pointer to the TClingClassInfo in TClass.
3598 /// If 'reload' is true, (attempt to) generate a new ClassInfo even if we
3599 /// already have one.
3600 
3601 void TCling::SetClassInfo(TClass* cl, Bool_t reload)
3602 {
3603  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3604  if (cl->fClassInfo && !reload) {
3605  return;
3606  }
3607  //Remove the decl_id from the DeclIdToTClass map
3608  TClingClassInfo* TClinginfo = (TClingClassInfo*) cl->fClassInfo;
3609  if (TClinginfo) {
3610  TClass::RemoveClassDeclId(TClinginfo->GetDeclId());
3611  }
3612  delete TClinginfo;
3613  cl->fClassInfo = 0;
3614  std::string name(cl->GetName());
3615 
3616  // Handle the special case of 'tuple' where we ignore the real implementation
3617  // details and just overlay a 'simpler'/'simplistic' version that is easy
3618  // for the I/O to understand and handle.
3619  if (!(fCxxModulesEnabled && IsFromRootCling()) && strncmp(cl->GetName(),"tuple<",strlen("tuple<"))==0) {
3620 
3621  name = AlternateTuple(cl->GetName());
3622 
3623  }
3624 
3625  TClingClassInfo* info = new TClingClassInfo(fInterpreter, name.c_str());
3626  if (!info->IsValid()) {
3627  if (cl->fState != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
3628  if (cl->fStreamerInfo->GetEntries() != 0) {
3629  cl->fState = TClass::kEmulated;
3630  } else {
3631  cl->fState = TClass::kForwardDeclared;
3632  }
3633  }
3634  delete info;
3635  return;
3636  }
3637  cl->fClassInfo = (ClassInfo_t*)info; // Note: We are transferring ownership here.
3638  // In case a class contains an external enum, the enum will be seen as a
3639  // class. We must detect this special case and make the class a Zombie.
3640  // Here we assume that a class has at least one method.
3641  // We can NOT call TClass::Property from here, because this method
3642  // assumes that the TClass is well formed to do a lot of information
3643  // caching. The method SetClassInfo (i.e. here) is usually called during
3644  // the building phase of the TClass, hence it is NOT well formed yet.
3645  Bool_t zombieCandidate = kFALSE;
3646  if (
3647  info->IsValid() &&
3648  !(info->Property() & (kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsNamespace))
3649  ) {
3650  zombieCandidate = kTRUE;
3651  }
3652  if (!info->IsLoaded()) {
3653  if (info->Property() & (kIsNamespace)) {
3654  // Namespaces can have info but no corresponding CINT dictionary
3655  // because they are auto-created if one of their contained
3656  // classes has a dictionary.
3657  zombieCandidate = kTRUE;
3658  }
3659  // this happens when no dictionary is available
3660  delete info;
3661  cl->fClassInfo = 0;
3662  }
3663  if (zombieCandidate && !cl->GetCollectionType()) {
3664  cl->MakeZombie();
3665  }
3666  // If we reach here, the info was valid (See early returns).
3667  if (cl->fState != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
3668  if (cl->fClassInfo) {
3669  cl->fState = TClass::kInterpreted;
3670  cl->ResetBit(TClass::kIsEmulation);
3671  } else {
3672 // if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(cl->GetName()) {
3673 // There will be an emulated collection proxy, is that the same?
3674 // cl->fState = TClass::kEmulated;
3675 // } else {
3676  if (cl->fStreamerInfo->GetEntries() != 0) {
3677  cl->fState = TClass::kEmulated;
3678  } else {
3679  cl->fState = TClass::kForwardDeclared;
3680  }
3681 // }
3682  }
3683  }
3684  if (cl->fClassInfo) {
3685  TClass::AddClassToDeclIdMap(((TClingClassInfo*)cl->fClassInfo)->GetDeclId(), cl);
3686  }
3687 }
3688 
3689 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3690 /// Checks if an entity with the specified name is defined in Cling.
3691 /// Returns kUnknown if the entity is not defined.
3692 /// Returns kWithClassDefInline if the entity exists and has a ClassDefInline
3693 /// Returns kKnown if the entity is defined.
3694 ///
3695 /// By default, structs, namespaces, classes, enums and unions are looked for.
3696 /// If the flag isClassOrNamespaceOnly is true, classes, structs and
3697 /// namespaces only are considered. I.e. if the name is an enum or a union,
3698 /// the returned value is false.
3699 ///
3700 /// In the case where the class is not loaded and belongs to a namespace
3701 /// or is nested, looking for the full class name is outputting a lots of
3702 /// (expected) error messages. Currently the only way to avoid this is to
3703 /// specifically check that each level of nesting is already loaded.
3704 /// In case of templates the idea is that everything between the outer
3705 /// '<' and '>' has to be skipped, e.g.: aap<pippo<noot>::klaas>::a_class
3706 
3707 TInterpreter::ECheckClassInfo
3708 TCling::CheckClassInfo(const char *name, Bool_t autoload, Bool_t isClassOrNamespaceOnly /* = kFALSE*/)
3709 {
3710  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3711  static const char *anonEnum = "anonymous enum ";
3712  static const int cmplen = strlen(anonEnum);
3713 
3714  if (0 == strncmp(name,anonEnum,cmplen)) {
3715  return kUnknown;
3716  }
3717 
3718  // Avoid the double search below in case the name is a fundamental type
3719  // or typedef to a fundamental type.
3720  THashTable *typeTable = dynamic_cast<THashTable*>( gROOT->GetListOfTypes() );
3721  TDataType *fundType = (TDataType *)typeTable->THashTable::FindObject( name );
3722 
3723  if (fundType && fundType->GetType() < TVirtualStreamerInfo::kObject
3724  && fundType->GetType() > 0) {
3725  // Fundamental type, no a class.
3726  return kUnknown;
3727  }
3728 
3729  // Migrated from within TClass::GetClass
3730  // If we want to know if a class or a namespace with this name exists in the
3731  // interpreter and this is an enum in the type system, before or after loading
3732  // according to the autoload function argument, return kUnknown.
3733  if (isClassOrNamespaceOnly && TEnum::GetEnum(name, autoload ? TEnum::kAutoload : TEnum::kNone))
3734  return kUnknown;
3735 
3736  const char *classname = name;
3737 
3738  int storeAutoload = SetClassAutoloading(autoload);
3739 
3740  // First we want to check whether the decl exist, but _without_
3741  // generating any template instantiation. However, the lookup
3742  // still will create a forward declaration of the class template instance
3743  // if it exist. In this case, the return value of findScope will still
3744  // be zero but the type will be initialized.
3745  // Note in the corresponding code in ROOT 5, CINT was not instantiating
3746  // this forward declaration.
3747  const cling::LookupHelper& lh = fInterpreter->getLookupHelper();
3748  const clang::Type *type = 0;
3749  const clang::Decl *decl
3750  = lh.findScope(classname,
3751  gDebug > 5 ? cling::LookupHelper::WithDiagnostics
3752  : cling::LookupHelper::NoDiagnostics,
3753  &type, /* intantiateTemplate= */ false );
3754  if (!decl) {
3755  std::string buf = TClassEdit::InsertStd(classname);
3756  decl = lh.findScope(buf,
3757  gDebug > 5 ? cling::LookupHelper::WithDiagnostics
3758  : cling::LookupHelper::NoDiagnostics,
3759  &type,false);
3760  }
3761 
3762  if (type) {
3763  // If decl==0 and the type is valid, then we have a forward declaration.
3764  if (!decl) {
3765  // If we have a forward declaration for a class template instantiation,
3766  // we want to ignore it if it was produced/induced by the call to
3767  // findScope, however we can not distinguish those from the
3768  // instantiation induce by 'soft' use (and thus also induce by the
3769  // same underlying code paths)
3770  // ['soft' use = use not requiring a complete definition]
3771  // So to reduce the amount of disruption to the existing code we
3772  // would just ignore those for STL collection, for which we really
3773  // need to have the compiled collection proxy (and thus the TClass
3774  // bootstrap).
3775  clang::ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl *tmpltDecl =
3776  llvm::dyn_cast_or_null<clang::ClassTemplateSpecializationDecl>
3777  (type->getAsCXXRecordDecl());
3778  if (tmpltDecl && !tmpltDecl->getPointOfInstantiation().isValid()) {
3779  // Since the point of instantiation is invalid, we 'guess' that
3780  // the 'instantiation' of the forwarded type appended in
3781  // findscope.
3782  if (ROOT::TMetaUtils::IsSTLCont(*tmpltDecl)) {
3783  // For STL Collection we return kUnknown.
3784  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3785  return kUnknown;
3786  }
3787  }
3788  }
3789  TClingClassInfo tci(fInterpreter, *type);
3790  if (!tci.IsValid()) {
3791  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3792  return kUnknown;
3793  }
3794  auto propertiesMask = isClassOrNamespaceOnly ? kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsNamespace :
3795  kIsClass | kIsStruct | kIsNamespace | kIsEnum | kIsUnion;
3796 
3797  if (tci.Property() & propertiesMask) {
3798  bool hasClassDefInline = false;
3799  if (isClassOrNamespaceOnly) {
3800  // We do not need to check for ClassDefInline when this is called from
3801  // TClass::Init, we only do it for the call from TClass::GetClass.
3802  auto hasDictionary = tci.GetMethod("Dictionary", "", false, 0, ROOT::kExactMatch);
3803  auto implLineFunc = tci.GetMethod("ImplFileLine", "", false, 0, ROOT::kExactMatch);
3804 
3805  if (hasDictionary.IsValid() && implLineFunc.IsValid()) {
3806  int lineNumber = 0;
3807  bool success = false;
3808  std::tie(success, lineNumber) =
3809  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetTrivialIntegralReturnValue(implLineFunc.GetMethodDecl(), *fInterpreter);
3810  hasClassDefInline = success && (lineNumber == -1);
3811  }
3812  }
3813 
3814  // fprintf(stderr,"CheckClassInfo: %s had dict=%d inline=%d\n",name,hasDictionary.IsValid()
3815  // , hasClassDefInline);
3816 
3817  // We are now sure that the entry is not in fact an autoload entry.
3818  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3819  if (hasClassDefInline)
3820  return kWithClassDefInline;
3821  else
3822  return kKnown;
3823  } else {
3824  // We are now sure that the entry is not in fact an autoload entry.
3825  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3826  return kUnknown;
3827  }
3828  }
3829 
3830  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3831  if (decl)
3832  return kKnown;
3833  else
3834  return kUnknown;
3835 
3836  // Setting up iterator part of TClingTypedefInfo is too slow.
3837  // Copy the lookup code instead:
3838  /*
3839  TClingTypedefInfo t(fInterpreter, name);
3840  if (t.IsValid() && !(t.Property() & kIsFundamental)) {
3841  delete[] classname;
3842  SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3843  return kTRUE;
3844  }
3845  */
3846 
3847 // const clang::Decl *decl = lh.findScope(name);
3848 // if (!decl) {
3849 // std::string buf = TClassEdit::InsertStd(name);
3850 // decl = lh.findScope(buf);
3851 // }
3852 
3853 // SetClassAutoloading(storeAutoload);
3854 // return (decl);
3855 }
3856 
3857 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3858 /// Return true if there is a class template by the given name ...
3859 
3860 Bool_t TCling::CheckClassTemplate(const char *name)
3861 {
3862  const cling::LookupHelper& lh = fInterpreter->getLookupHelper();
3863  const clang::Decl *decl
3864  = lh.findClassTemplate(name,
3865  gDebug > 5 ? cling::LookupHelper::WithDiagnostics
3866  : cling::LookupHelper::NoDiagnostics);
3867  if (!decl) {
3868  std::string strname = "std::";
3869  strname += name;
3870  decl = lh.findClassTemplate(strname,
3871  gDebug > 5 ? cling::LookupHelper::WithDiagnostics
3872  : cling::LookupHelper::NoDiagnostics);
3873  }
3874  return 0 != decl;
3875 }

3877 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3878 /// Create list of pointers to base class(es) for TClass cl.
3879 
3880 void TCling::CreateListOfBaseClasses(TClass *cl) const
3881 {
3882  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3883  if (cl->fBase) {
3884  return;
3885  }
3886  TClingClassInfo *tci = (TClingClassInfo *)cl->GetClassInfo();
3887  if (!tci) return;
3888  TClingBaseClassInfo t(fInterpreter, tci);
3889  TList *listOfBase = new TList;
3890  while (t.Next()) {
3891  // if name cannot be obtained no use to put in list
3892  if (t.IsValid() && t.Name()) {
3893  TClingBaseClassInfo *a = new TClingBaseClassInfo(t);
3894  listOfBase->Add(new TBaseClass((BaseClassInfo_t *)a, cl));
3895  }
3896  }
3897  // Now that is complete, publish it.
3898  cl->fBase = listOfBase;
3899 }

3901 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3902 /// Create list of pointers to enums for TClass cl.
3903 
3904 void TCling::LoadEnums(TListOfEnums& enumList) const
3905 {
3906  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3907 
3908  const Decl * D;
3909  TClass* cl = enumList.GetClass();
3910  if (cl) {
3911  D = ((TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo())->GetDecl();
3912  }
3913  else {
3914  D = fInterpreter->getCI()->getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
3915  }
3916  // Iterate on the decl of the class and get the enums.
3917  if (const clang::DeclContext* DC = dyn_cast<clang::DeclContext>(D)) {
3918  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII deserRAII(fInterpreter);
3919  // Collect all contexts of the namespace.
3920  llvm::SmallVector< DeclContext *, 4> allDeclContexts;
3921  const_cast< clang::DeclContext *>(DC)->collectAllContexts(allDeclContexts);
3922  for (llvm::SmallVector<DeclContext*, 4>::iterator declIter = allDeclContexts.begin(), declEnd = allDeclContexts.end();
3923  declIter != declEnd; ++declIter) {
3924  // Iterate on all decls for each context.
3925  for (clang::DeclContext::decl_iterator DI = (*declIter)->decls_begin(),
3926  DE = (*declIter)->decls_end(); DI != DE; ++DI) {
3927  if (const clang::EnumDecl* ED = dyn_cast<clang::EnumDecl>(*DI)) {
3928  // Get name of the enum type.
3929  std::string buf;
3930  PrintingPolicy Policy(ED->getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy());
3931  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(buf);
3932  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
3933  Policy.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
3934  ED->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, Policy, /*Qualified=*/false);
3935  stream.flush();
3936  // If the enum is unnamed we do not add it to the list of enums i.e unusable.
3937  if (!buf.empty()) {
3938  const char* name = buf.c_str();
3939  // Add the enum to the list of loaded enums.
3940  enumList.Get(ED, name);
3941  }
3942  }
3943  }
3944  }
3945  }
3946 }

3948 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3949 /// Create list of pointers to function templates for TClass cl.
3950 
3951 void TCling::LoadFunctionTemplates(TClass* cl) const
3952 {
3953  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
3954 
3955  const Decl * D;
3956  TListOfFunctionTemplates* funcTempList;
3957  if (cl) {
3958  D = ((TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo())->GetDecl();
3959  funcTempList = (TListOfFunctionTemplates*)cl->GetListOfFunctionTemplates(false);
3960  }
3961  else {
3962  D = fInterpreter->getCI()->getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
3963  funcTempList = (TListOfFunctionTemplates*)gROOT->GetListOfFunctionTemplates();
3964  }
3965  // Iterate on the decl of the class and get the enums.
3966  if (const clang::DeclContext* DC = dyn_cast<clang::DeclContext>(D)) {
3967  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII deserRAII(fInterpreter);
3968  // Collect all contexts of the namespace.
3969  llvm::SmallVector< DeclContext *, 4> allDeclContexts;
3970  const_cast< clang::DeclContext *>(DC)->collectAllContexts(allDeclContexts);
3971  for (llvm::SmallVector<DeclContext*, 4>::iterator declIter = allDeclContexts.begin(),
3972  declEnd = allDeclContexts.end(); declIter != declEnd; ++declIter) {
3973  // Iterate on all decls for each context.
3974  for (clang::DeclContext::decl_iterator DI = (*declIter)->decls_begin(),
3975  DE = (*declIter)->decls_end(); DI != DE; ++DI) {
3976  if (const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl* FTD = dyn_cast<clang::FunctionTemplateDecl>(*DI)) {
3977  funcTempList->Get(FTD);
3978  }
3979  }
3980  }
3981  }
3982 }

4050 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4051 /// Generate a TClass for the given class.
4052 /// Since the caller has already check the ClassInfo, let it give use the
4053 /// result (via the value of emulation) rather than recalculate it.
4054 
4055 TClass *TCling::GenerateTClass(const char *classname, Bool_t emulation, Bool_t silent /* = kFALSE */)
4056 {
4057 // For now the following line would lead to the (unwanted) instantiation
4058 // of class template. This could/would need to be resurrected only if
4059 // we re-introduce so sort of automatic instantiation. However this would
4060 // have to include carefull look at the template parameter to avoid
4061 // creating instance we can not really use (if the parameter are only forward
4062 // declaration or do not have all the necessary interfaces).
4063 
4064  // TClingClassInfo tci(fInterpreter, classname);
4065  // if (1 || !tci.IsValid()) {
4066 
4067  Version_t version = 1;
4068  if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(classname)) {
4069  version = TClass::GetClass("TVirtualStreamerInfo")->GetClassVersion();
4070  }
4071  TClass *cl = new TClass(classname, version, silent);
4072  if (emulation) {
4073  cl->SetBit(TClass::kIsEmulation);
4074  } else {
4075  // Set the class version if the class is versioned.
4076  // Note that we cannot just call CLASS::Class_Version() as we might not have
4077  // an execution engine (when invoked from rootcling).
4078 
4079  // Do not call cl->GetClassVersion(), it has side effects!
4080  Version_t oldvers = cl->fClassVersion;
4081  if (oldvers == version && cl->GetClassInfo()) {
4082  // We have a version and it might need an update.
4083  Version_t newvers = oldvers;
4084  TClingClassInfo* cli = (TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo();
4085  if (llvm::isa<clang::NamespaceDecl>(cli->GetDecl())) {
4086  // Namespaces don't have class versions.
4087  return cl;
4088  }
4089  TClingMethodInfo mi = cli->GetMethod("Class_Version", "", 0 /*poffset*/,
4090  ROOT::kExactMatch,
4091  TClingClassInfo::kInThisScope);
4092  if (!mi.IsValid()) {
4093  if (cl->TestBit(TClass::kIsTObject)) {
4094  Error("GenerateTClass",
4095  "Cannot find %s::Class_Version()! Class version might be wrong.",
4096  cl->GetName());
4097  }
4098  return cl;
4099  }
4100  newvers = ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetClassVersion(llvm::dyn_cast<clang::RecordDecl>(cli->GetDecl()),
4101  *fInterpreter);
4102  if (newvers == -1) {
4103  // Didn't manage to determine the class version from the AST.
4104  // Use runtime instead.
4105  if ((mi.Property() & kIsStatic)
4106  && !fInterpreter->isInSyntaxOnlyMode()) {
4107  // This better be a static function.
4108  TClingCallFunc callfunc(fInterpreter, *fNormalizedCtxt);
4109  callfunc.SetFunc(&mi);
4110  newvers = callfunc.ExecInt(0);
4111  } else {
4112  Error("GenerateTClass",
4113  "Cannot invoke %s::Class_Version()! Class version might be wrong.",
4114  cl->GetName());
4115  }
4116  }
4117  if (newvers != oldvers) {
4118  cl->fClassVersion = newvers;
4119  cl->fStreamerInfo->Expand(newvers + 2 + 10);
4120  }
4121  }
4122  }
4123 
4124  return cl;
4125 
4126 // } else {
4127 // return GenerateTClass(&tci,silent);
4128 // }
4129 }

4158  }
4159  }
4160  }
4161  }
4162  }
4163 }
4164 #endif
4165 
4166 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4167 /// Generate a TClass for the given class.
4168 
4169 TClass *TCling::GenerateTClass(ClassInfo_t *classinfo, Bool_t silent /* = kFALSE */)
4170 {
4171  TClingClassInfo *info = (TClingClassInfo*)classinfo;
4172  if (!info || !info->IsValid()) {
4173  Fatal("GenerateTClass","Requires a valid ClassInfo object");
4174  return 0;
4175  }
4176  // We are in the case where we have AST nodes for this class.
4177  TClass *cl = 0;
4178  std::string classname;
4179  info->FullName(classname,*fNormalizedCtxt); // Could we use Name()?
4180  if (TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(classname)) {
4181 #if 0
4182  Info("GenerateTClass","Will (try to) generate the compiled TClass for %s.",classname.c_str());
4183  // We need to build up the list of required headers, by
4184  // looking at each template arguments.
4185  TString includes;
4186  GenerateTClass_GatherInnerIncludes(fInterpreter,includes,info);
4187 
4188  if (0 == GenerateDictionary(classname.c_str(),includes)) {
4189  // 0 means success.
4190  cl = TClass::LoadClass(classnam.c_str(), silent);
4191  if (cl == 0) {
4192  Error("GenerateTClass","Even though the dictionary generation for %s seemed successful we can't find the TClass bootstrap!",classname.c_str());
4193  }
4194  }
4195 #endif
4196  if (cl == 0) {
4197  int version = TClass::GetClass("TVirtualStreamerInfo")->GetClassVersion();
4198  cl = new TClass(classinfo, version, 0, 0, -1, -1, silent);
4199  cl->SetBit(TClass::kIsEmulation);
4200  }
4201  } else {
4202  // For regular class, just create a TClass on the fly ...
4203  // Not quite useful yet, but that what CINT used to do anyway.
4204  cl = new TClass(classinfo, 1, 0, 0, -1, -1, silent);
4205  }
4206  // Add the new TClass to the map of declid and TClass*.
4207  if (cl) {
4208  TClass::AddClassToDeclIdMap(((TClingClassInfo*)classinfo)->GetDeclId(), cl);
4209  }
4210  return cl;
4211 }
4212 
4213 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4214 /// Generate the dictionary for the C++ classes listed in the first
4215 /// argument (in a semi-colon separated list).
4216 /// 'includes' contains a semi-colon separated list of file to
4217 /// #include in the dictionary.
4218 /// For example:
4219 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4220 /// gInterpreter->GenerateDictionary("vector<vector<float> >;list<vector<float> >","list;vector");
4221 /// ~~~
4222 /// or
4223 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4224 /// gInterpreter->GenerateDictionary("myclass","myclass.h;myhelper.h");
4225 /// ~~~
4226 
4227 Int_t TCling::GenerateDictionary(const char* classes, const char* includes /* = "" */, const char* /* options = 0 */)
4228 {
4229  if (classes == 0 || classes[0] == 0) {
4230  Error("TCling::GenerateDictionary", "Cannot generate dictionary without passing classes.");
4231  return 0;
4232  }
4233  // Split the input list
4234  std::vector<std::string> listClasses;
4235  for (
4236  const char* current = classes, *prev = classes;
4237  *current != 0;
4238  ++current
4239  ) {
4240  if (*current == ';') {
4241  listClasses.push_back(std::string(prev, current - prev));
4242  prev = current + 1;
4243  }
4244  else if (*(current + 1) == 0) {
4245  listClasses.push_back(std::string(prev, current + 1 - prev));
4246  prev = current + 1;
4247  }
4248  }
4249  std::vector<std::string> listIncludes;
4250  if (!includes)
4251  includes = "";
4252  for (
4253  const char* current = includes, *prev = includes;
4254  *current != 0;
4255  ++current
4256  ) {
4257  if (*current == ';') {
4258  listIncludes.push_back(std::string(prev, current - prev));
4259  prev = current + 1;
4260  }
4261  else if (*(current + 1) == 0) {
4262  listIncludes.push_back(std::string(prev, current + 1 - prev));
4263  prev = current + 1;
4264  }
4265  }
4266  // Generate the temporary dictionary file
4267  return !TCling_GenerateDictionary(listClasses, listIncludes,
4268  std::vector<std::string>(), std::vector<std::string>());
4269 }
4270 
4271 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4272 /// Return pointer to cling Decl of global/static variable that is located
4273 /// at the address given by addr.
4274 
4275 TInterpreter::DeclId_t TCling::GetDataMember(ClassInfo_t *opaque_cl, const char *name) const
4276 {
4277  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4278  DeclId_t d;
4279  TClingClassInfo *cl = (TClingClassInfo*)opaque_cl;
4280 
4281  if (cl) {
4282  d = cl->GetDataMember(name);
4283  // We check if the decl of the data member has an annotation which indicates
4284  // an ioname.
4285  // In case this is true, if the name requested is not the ioname, we
4286  // return 0, as if the member did not exist. In some sense we override
4287  // the information in the TClassInfo instance, isolating the typesystem in
4288  // TClass from the one in the AST.
4289  if (const ValueDecl* decl = (const ValueDecl*) d){
4290  std::string ioName;
4291  bool hasIoName = ROOT::TMetaUtils::ExtractAttrPropertyFromName(*decl,"ioname",ioName);
4292  if (hasIoName && ioName != name) return 0;
4293  }
4294  return d;
4295  }
4296  // We are looking up for something on the TU scope.
4297  // FIXME: We do not want to go through TClingClassInfo(fInterpreter) because of redundant deserializations. That
4298  // interface will actually construct iterators and walk over the decls on the global scope. In would return the first
4299  // occurrence of a decl with the looked up name. However, that's not what C++ lookup would do: if we want to switch
4300  // to a more complete C++ lookup interface we need sift through the found names and pick up the declarations which
4301  // are only fulfilling ROOT's understanding for a Data Member.
4302  // FIXME: We should probably deprecate the TClingClassInfo(fInterpreter) interface and replace it withe something
4303  // similar as below.
4304  using namespace clang;
4305  Sema& SemaR = fInterpreter->getSema();
4306  DeclarationName DName = &SemaR.Context.Idents.get(name);
4307 
4308  LookupResult R(SemaR, DName, SourceLocation(), Sema::LookupOrdinaryName,
4309  Sema::ForRedeclaration);
4310 
4311  // Could trigger deserialization of decls.
4312  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII RAII(fInterpreter);
4313  cling::utils::Lookup::Named(&SemaR, R);
4314 
4315  LookupResult::Filter F = R.makeFilter();
4316  // Filter the data-member looking decls.
4317  while (F.hasNext()) {
4318  NamedDecl *D = F.next();
4319  if (isa<VarDecl>(D) || isa<FieldDecl>(D) || isa<EnumConstantDecl>(D) ||
4320  isa<IndirectFieldDecl>(D))
4321  continue;
4322  F.erase();
4323  }
4324  F.done();
4325 
4326  if (R.isSingleResult())
4327  return R.getFoundDecl();
4328  return 0;
4329 }
4330 
4331 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4332 /// Return pointer to cling Decl of global/static variable that is located
4333 /// at the address given by addr.
4334 
4335 TInterpreter::DeclId_t TCling::GetEnum(TClass *cl, const char *name) const
4336 {
4337  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4338 
4339  const clang::Decl* possibleEnum = 0;
4340  // FInd the context of the decl.
4341  if (cl) {
4342  TClingClassInfo *cci = (TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo();
4343  if (cci) {
4344  const clang::DeclContext* dc = 0;
4345  if (const clang::Decl* D = cci->GetDecl()) {
4346  if (!(dc = dyn_cast<clang::NamespaceDecl>(D))) {
4347  dc = dyn_cast<clang::RecordDecl>(D);
4348  }
4349  }
4350  if (dc) {
4351  // If it is a data member enum.
4352  // Could trigger deserialization of decls.
4353  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII RAII(fInterpreter);
4354  possibleEnum = cling::utils::Lookup::Tag(&fInterpreter->getSema(), name, dc);
4355  } else {
4356  Error("TCling::GetEnum", "DeclContext not found for %s .\n", name);
4357  }
4358  }
4359  } else {
4360  // If it is a global enum.
4361  // Could trigger deserialization of decls.
4362  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII RAII(fInterpreter);
4363  possibleEnum = cling::utils::Lookup::Tag(&fInterpreter->getSema(), name);
4364  }
4365  if (possibleEnum && (possibleEnum != (clang::Decl*)-1)
4366  && isa<clang::EnumDecl>(possibleEnum)) {
4367  return possibleEnum;
4368  }
4369  return 0;
4370 }
4371 
4372 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4373 /// Return pointer to cling DeclId for a global value
4374 
4375 TInterpreter::DeclId_t TCling::GetDeclId( const llvm::GlobalValue *gv ) const
4376 {
4377  if (!gv) return 0;
4378 
4379  llvm::StringRef mangled_name = gv->getName();
4380 
4381  int err = 0;
4382  char* demangled_name_c = TClassEdit::DemangleName(mangled_name.str().c_str(), err);
4383  if (err) {
4384  if (err == -2) {
4385  // It might simply be an unmangled global name.
4386  DeclId_t d;
4387  TClingClassInfo gcl(fInterpreter);
4388  d = gcl.GetDataMember(mangled_name.str().c_str());
4389  return d;
4390  }
4391  return 0;
4392  }
4393 
4394  std::string scopename(demangled_name_c);
4395  free(demangled_name_c);
4396 
4397  //
4398  // Separate out the class or namespace part of the
4399  // function name.
4400  //
4401  std::string dataname;
4402 
4403  if (!strncmp(scopename.c_str(), "typeinfo for ", sizeof("typeinfo for ")-1)) {
4404  scopename.erase(0, sizeof("typeinfo for ")-1);
4405  } else if (!strncmp(scopename.c_str(), "vtable for ", sizeof("vtable for ")-1)) {
4406  scopename.erase(0, sizeof("vtable for ")-1);
4407  } else {
4408  // See if it is a function
4409  std::string::size_type pos = scopename.rfind('(');
4410  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
4411  return 0;
4412  }
4413  // Separate the scope and member name
4414  pos = scopename.rfind(':');
4415  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
4416  if ((pos != 0) && (scopename[pos-1] == ':')) {
4417  dataname = scopename.substr(pos+1);
4418  scopename.erase(pos-1);
4419  }
4420  } else {
4421  scopename.clear();
4422  dataname = scopename;
4423  }
4424  }
4425  //fprintf(stderr, "name: '%s'\n", name.c_str());
4426  // Now we have the class or namespace name, so do the lookup.
4427 
4428 
4429  DeclId_t d;
4430  if (scopename.size()) {
4431  TClingClassInfo cl(fInterpreter,scopename.c_str());
4432  d = cl.GetDataMember(dataname.c_str());
4433  }
4434  else {
4435  TClingClassInfo gcl(fInterpreter);
4436  d = gcl.GetDataMember(dataname.c_str());
4437  }
4438  return d;
4439 }

4460 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4461 /// Return the cling mangled name for a method of a class with parameters
4462 /// params (params is a string of actual arguments, not formal ones). If the
4463 /// class is 0 the global function list will be searched.
4464 
4465 TString TCling::GetMangledName(TClass* cl, const char* method,
4466  const char* params, Bool_t objectIsConst /* = kFALSE */)
4467 {
4468  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4469  TClingCallFunc func(fInterpreter,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4470  if (cl) {
4471  Long_t offset;
4472  func.SetFunc((TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo(), method, params, objectIsConst,
4473  &offset);
4474  }
4475  else {
4476  TClingClassInfo gcl(fInterpreter);
4477  Long_t offset;
4478  func.SetFunc(&gcl, method, params, &offset);
4479  }
4480  TClingMethodInfo* mi = (TClingMethodInfo*) func.FactoryMethod();
4481  if (!mi) return "";
4482  TString mangled_name( mi->GetMangledName() );
4483  delete mi;
4484  return mangled_name;
4485 }

4548 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4549 /// Insert overloads of name in cl to res.
4550 
4551 void TCling::GetFunctionOverloads(ClassInfo_t *cl, const char *funcname,
4552  std::vector<DeclId_t>& res) const
4553 {
4554  clang::Sema& S = fInterpreter->getSema();
4555  clang::ASTContext& Ctx = S.Context;
4556  const clang::Decl* CtxDecl
4557  = cl ? (const clang::Decl*)((TClingClassInfo*)cl)->GetDeclId():
4558  Ctx.getTranslationUnitDecl();
4559  auto RecDecl = llvm::dyn_cast<const clang::RecordDecl>(CtxDecl);
4560  const clang::DeclContext* DeclCtx = RecDecl;
4561 
4562  if (!DeclCtx)
4563  DeclCtx = dyn_cast<clang::NamespaceDecl>(CtxDecl);
4564  if (!DeclCtx) return;
4565 
4566  clang::DeclarationName DName;
4567  // The DeclarationName is funcname, unless it's a ctor or dtor.
4568  // FIXME: or operator or conversion! See enum clang::DeclarationName::NameKind.
4569 
4570  if (RecDecl) {
4571  if (RecDecl->getNameAsString() == funcname) {
4572  clang::QualType QT = Ctx.getTypeDeclType(RecDecl);
4573  DName = Ctx.DeclarationNames.getCXXConstructorName(Ctx.getCanonicalType(QT));
4574  } else if (funcname[0] == '~' && RecDecl->getNameAsString() == funcname + 1) {
4575  clang::QualType QT = Ctx.getTypeDeclType(RecDecl);
4576  DName = Ctx.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(Ctx.getCanonicalType(QT));
4577  } else {
4578  DName = &Ctx.Idents.get(funcname);
4579  }
4580  } else {
4581  DName = &Ctx.Idents.get(funcname);
4582  }
4583 
4584  clang::LookupResult R(S, DName, clang::SourceLocation(),
4585  Sema::LookupOrdinaryName, clang::Sema::ForRedeclaration);
4586  S.LookupQualifiedName(R, const_cast<DeclContext*>(DeclCtx));
4587  if (R.empty()) return;
4588  R.resolveKind();
4589  res.reserve(res.size() + (R.end() - R.begin()));
4590  for (clang::LookupResult::iterator IR = R.begin(), ER = R.end();
4591  IR != ER; ++IR) {
4592  if (const clang::FunctionDecl* FD
4593  = llvm::dyn_cast<const clang::FunctionDecl>(*IR)) {
4594  if (!FD->getDescribedFunctionTemplate()) {
4595  res.push_back(FD);
4596  }
4597  }
4598  }
4599 }

4689 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4690 /// The 'name' is known to the interpreter, this function returns
4691 /// the internal version of this name (usually just resolving typedefs)
4692 /// This is used in particular to synchronize between the name used
4693 /// by rootcling and by the run-time environment (TClass)
4694 /// Return 0 if the name is not known.
4695 
4696 void TCling::GetInterpreterTypeName(const char* name, std::string &output, Bool_t full)
4697 {
4698  output.clear();
4699 
4700  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
4701 
4702  TClingClassInfo cl(fInterpreter, name);
4703  if (!cl.IsValid()) {
4704  return ;
4705  }
4706  if (full) {
4707  cl.FullName(output,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4708  return;
4709  }
4710  // Well well well, for backward compatibility we need to act a bit too
4711  // much like CINT.
4712  TClassEdit::TSplitType splitname( cl.Name(), TClassEdit::kDropStd );
4713  splitname.ShortType(output, TClassEdit::kDropStd );
4714 
4715  return;
4716 }

4718 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4719 /// Execute a global function with arguments params.
4720 ///
4721 /// FIXME: The cint-based version of this code does not check if the
4722 /// SetFunc() call works, and does not do any real checking
4723 /// for errors from the Exec() call. It did fetch the most
4724 /// recent cint security error and return that in error, but
4725 /// this does not really translate well to cling/clang. We
4726 /// should enhance these interfaces so that we can report
4727 /// compilation and runtime errors properly.
4728 
4729 void TCling::Execute(const char* function, const char* params, int* error)
4730 {
4731  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
4732  if (error) {
4733  *error = TInterpreter::kNoError;
4734  }
4735  TClingClassInfo cl(fInterpreter);
4736  Long_t offset = 0L;
4737  TClingCallFunc func(fInterpreter,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4738  func.SetFunc(&cl, function, params, &offset);
4739  func.Exec(0);
4740 }
4741 
4742 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4743 /// Execute a method from class cl with arguments params.
4744 ///
4745 /// FIXME: The cint-based version of this code does not check if the
4746 /// SetFunc() call works, and does not do any real checking
4747 /// for errors from the Exec() call. It did fetch the most
4748 /// recent cint security error and return that in error, but
4749 /// this does not really translate well to cling/clang. We
4750 /// should enhance these interfaces so that we can report
4751 /// compilation and runtime errors properly.
4752 
4753 void TCling::Execute(TObject* obj, TClass* cl, const char* method,
4754  const char* params, Bool_t objectIsConst, int* error)
4755 {
4756  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
4757  if (error) {
4758  *error = TInterpreter::kNoError;
4759  }
4760  // If the actual class of this object inherits 2nd (or more) from TObject,
4761  // 'obj' is unlikely to be the start of the object (as described by IsA()),
4762  // hence gInterpreter->Execute will improperly correct the offset.
4763  void* addr = cl->DynamicCast(TObject::Class(), obj, kFALSE);
4764  Long_t offset = 0L;
4765  TClingCallFunc func(fInterpreter,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4766  func.SetFunc((TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo(), method, params, objectIsConst, &offset);
4767  void* address = (void*)((Long_t)addr + offset);
4768  func.Exec(address);
4769 }
