4771 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4772 
4773 void TCling::Execute(TObject* obj, TClass* cl, const char* method,
4774  const char* params, int* error)
4775 {
4776  Execute(obj,cl,method,params,false,error);
4777 }
4778 
4779 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4780 /// Execute a method from class cl with the arguments in array params
4781 /// (params[0] ... params[n] = array of TObjString parameters).
4782 /// Convert the TObjArray array of TObjString parameters to a character
4783 /// string of comma separated parameters.
4784 /// The parameters of type 'char' are enclosed in double quotes and all
4785 /// internal quotes are escaped.
4786 
4787 void TCling::Execute(TObject* obj, TClass* cl, TMethod* method,
4788  TObjArray* params, int* error)
4789 {
4790  if (!method) {
4791  Error("Execute", "No method was defined");
4792  return;
4793  }
4794  TList* argList = method->GetListOfMethodArgs();
4795  // Check number of actual parameters against of expected formal ones
4796 
4797  Int_t nparms = argList->LastIndex() + 1;
4798  Int_t argc = params ? params->GetEntries() : 0;
4799 
4800  if (argc > nparms) {
4801  Error("Execute","Too many parameters to call %s, got %d but expected at most %d.",method->GetName(),argc,nparms);
4802  return;
4803  }
4804  if (nparms != argc) {
4805  // Let's see if the 'missing' argument are all defaulted.
4806  // if nparms==0 then either we stopped earlier either argc is also zero and we can't reach here.
4807  assert(nparms > 0);
4808 
4809  TMethodArg *arg = (TMethodArg *) argList->At( 0 );
4810  if (arg && arg->GetDefault() && arg->GetDefault()[0]) {
4811  // There is a default value for the first missing
4812  // argument, so we are fine.
4813  } else {
4814  Int_t firstDefault = -1;
4815  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nparms; i ++) {
4816  arg = (TMethodArg *) argList->At( i );
4817  if (arg && arg->GetDefault() && arg->GetDefault()[0]) {
4818  firstDefault = i;
4819  break;
4820  }
4821  }
4822  if (firstDefault >= 0) {
4823  Error("Execute","Too few arguments to call %s, got only %d but expected at least %d and at most %d.",method->GetName(),argc,firstDefault,nparms);
4824  } else {
4825  Error("Execute","Too few arguments to call %s, got only %d but expected %d.",method->GetName(),argc,nparms);
4826  }
4827  return;
4828  }
4829  }
4830 
4831  const char* listpar = "";
4832  TString complete(10);
4833  if (params) {
4834  // Create a character string of parameters from TObjArray
4835  TIter next(params);
4836  for (Int_t i = 0; i < argc; i ++) {
4837  TMethodArg* arg = (TMethodArg*) argList->At(i);
4838  TClingTypeInfo type(fInterpreter, arg->GetFullTypeName());
4839  TObjString* nxtpar = (TObjString*) next();
4840  if (i) {
4841  complete += ',';
4842  }
4843  if (strstr(type.TrueName(*fNormalizedCtxt), "char")) {
4844  TString chpar('\"');
4845  chpar += (nxtpar->String()).ReplaceAll("\"", "\\\"");
4846  // At this point we have to check if string contains \\"
4847  // and apply some more sophisticated parser. Not implemented yet!
4848  complete += chpar;
4849  complete += '\"';
4850  }
4851  else {
4852  complete += nxtpar->String();
4853  }
4854  }
4855  listpar = complete.Data();
4856  }
4857 
4858  // And now execute it.
4859  R__LOCKGUARD_CLING(gInterpreterMutex);
4860  if (error) {
4861  *error = TInterpreter::kNoError;
4862  }
4863  // If the actual class of this object inherits 2nd (or more) from TObject,
4864  // 'obj' is unlikely to be the start of the object (as described by IsA()),
4865  // hence gInterpreter->Execute will improperly correct the offset.
4866  void* addr = cl->DynamicCast(TObject::Class(), obj, kFALSE);
4867  TClingCallFunc func(fInterpreter,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4868  TClingMethodInfo *minfo = (TClingMethodInfo*)method->fInfo;
4869  func.Init(*minfo);
4870  func.SetArgs(listpar);
4871  // Now calculate the 'this' pointer offset for the method
4872  // when starting from the class described by cl.
4873  const CXXMethodDecl * mdecl = dyn_cast<CXXMethodDecl>(minfo->GetMethodDecl());
4874  Long_t offset = ((TClingClassInfo*)cl->GetClassInfo())->GetOffset(mdecl);
4875  void* address = (void*)((Long_t)addr + offset);
4876  func.Exec(address);
4877 }

4882  const void* args[] /*=0*/,
4883  int nargs /*=0*/,
4884  void* ret/*= 0*/) const
4885 {
4886  if (!method) {
4887  Error("ExecuteWithArgsAndReturn", "No method was defined");
4888  return;
4889  }
4890 
4891  TClingMethodInfo* minfo = (TClingMethodInfo*) method->fInfo;
4892  TClingCallFunc func(*minfo,*fNormalizedCtxt);
4893  func.ExecWithArgsAndReturn(address, args, nargs, ret);
4894 }

4918 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4919 /// Return the file name of the currently interpreted file,
4920 /// included or not. Example to illustrate the difference between
4921 /// GetCurrentMacroName() and GetTopLevelMacroName():
4922 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4923 /// void inclfile() {
4924 /// std::cout << "In inclfile.C" << std::endl;
4925 /// std::cout << " TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() returns " <<
4926 /// TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() << std::endl;
4927 /// std::cout << " TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() returns " <<
4928 /// TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() << std::endl;
4929 /// }
4930 /// ~~~
4931 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4932 /// void mymacro() {
4933 /// std::cout << "In mymacro.C" << std::endl;
4934 /// std::cout << " TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() returns " <<
4935 /// TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() << std::endl;
4936 /// std::cout << " TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() returns " <<
4937 /// TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() << std::endl;
4938 /// std::cout << " Now calling inclfile..." << std::endl;
4939 /// gInterpreter->ProcessLine(".x inclfile.C");;
4940 /// }
4941 /// ~~~
4942 /// Running mymacro.C will print:
4943 ///
4944 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4945 /// root [0] .x mymacro.C
4946 /// ~~~
4947 /// In mymacro.C
4948 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4949 /// TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() returns ./mymacro.C
4950 /// TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() returns ./mymacro.C
4951 /// ~~~
4952 /// Now calling inclfile...
4953 /// In inclfile.h
4954 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
4955 /// TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() returns inclfile.C
4956 /// TCling::GetTopLevelMacroName() returns ./mymacro.C
4957 /// ~~~
4958 
4959 const char* TCling::GetCurrentMacroName() const
4960 {
4961 #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
4962 #if R__MUST_REVISIT(6,0)
4963  Warning("GetCurrentMacroName", "Must change return type!");
4964 #endif
4965 #endif
4966  return fCurExecutingMacros.back();
4967 }

4969 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
4970 /// Return the absolute type of typeDesc.
4971 /// E.g.: typeDesc = "class TNamed**", returns "TNamed".
4972 /// You need to use the result immediately before it is being overwritten.
4973 
4974 const char* TCling::TypeName(const char* typeDesc)
4975 {
4976  TTHREAD_TLS(char*) t = 0;
4977  TTHREAD_TLS(unsigned int) tlen = 0;
4978 
4979  unsigned int dlen = strlen(typeDesc);
4980  if (dlen > tlen) {
4981  delete[] t;
4982  t = new char[dlen + 1];
4983  tlen = dlen;
4984  }
4985  const char* s, *template_start;
4986  if (!strstr(typeDesc, "(*)(")) {
4987  s = strchr(typeDesc, ' ');
4988  template_start = strchr(typeDesc, '<');
4989  if (!strcmp(typeDesc, "long long")) {
4990  strlcpy(t, typeDesc, dlen + 1);
4991  }
4992  else if (!strncmp(typeDesc, "unsigned ", s + 1 - typeDesc)) {
4993  strlcpy(t, typeDesc, dlen + 1);
4994  }
4995  // s is the position of the second 'word' (if any)
4996  // except in the case of templates where there will be a space
4997  // just before any closing '>': eg.
4998  // TObj<std::vector<UShort_t,__malloc_alloc_template<0> > >*
4999  else if (s && (template_start == 0 || (s < template_start))) {
5000  strlcpy(t, s + 1, dlen + 1);
5001  }
5002  else {
5003  strlcpy(t, typeDesc, dlen + 1);
5004  }
5005  }
5006  else {
5007  strlcpy(t, typeDesc, dlen + 1);
5008  }
5009  int l = strlen(t);
5010  while (l > 0 && (t[l - 1] == '*' || t[l - 1] == '&')) {
5011  t[--l] = 0;
5012  }
5013  return t;
5014 }
5015 
5016 static bool requiresRootMap(const char* rootmapfile, cling::Interpreter* interp)
5017 {
5018  if (!rootmapfile || !*rootmapfile)
5019  return true;
5020 
5021  llvm::StringRef moduleName = llvm::sys::path::filename(rootmapfile);
5022  moduleName.consume_front("lib");
5023  moduleName.consume_back(".rootmap");
5024 
5025  Module *M = interp->getCI()->getPreprocessor().getHeaderSearchInfo().lookupModule(moduleName);
5026 
5027  return !(M && interp->getSema().isModuleVisible(M));
5028 }
5029 
5030 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5031 /// Read and parse a rootmapfile in its new format, and return 0 in case of
5032 /// success, -1 if the file has already been read, and -3 in case its format
5033 /// is the old one (e.g. containing "Library.ClassName"), -4 in case of syntax
5034 /// error.
5035 
5036 int TCling::ReadRootmapFile(const char *rootmapfile, TUniqueString *uniqueString)
5037 {
5038  // For "class ", "namespace ", "typedef ", "header ", "enum ", "var " respectively
5039  const std::map<char, unsigned int> keyLenMap = {{'c',6},{'n',10},{'t',8},{'h',7},{'e',5},{'v',4}};
5040 
5041  if (rootmapfile && *rootmapfile) {
5042  std::string rootmapfileNoBackslash(rootmapfile);
5043 #ifdef _MSC_VER
5044  std::replace(rootmapfileNoBackslash.begin(), rootmapfileNoBackslash.end(), '\\', '/');
5045 #endif
5046  // Add content of a specific rootmap file
5047  if (fRootmapFiles->FindObject(rootmapfileNoBackslash.c_str()))
5048  return -1;
5049 
5050  if (uniqueString)
5051  uniqueString->Append(std::string("\n#line 1 \"Forward declarations from ") + rootmapfileNoBackslash + "\"\n");
5052 
5053  std::ifstream file(rootmapfileNoBackslash);
5054  std::string line; line.reserve(200);
5055  std::string lib_name; line.reserve(100);
5056  bool newFormat=false;
5057  while (getline(file, line, '\n')) {
5058  if (!newFormat &&
5059  (line.compare(0, 8, "Library.") == 0 || line.compare(0, 8, "Declare.") == 0)) {
5060  file.close();
5061  return -3; // old format
5062  }
5063  newFormat=true;
5064 
5065  if (line.compare(0, 9, "{ decls }") == 0 && requiresRootMap(rootmapfile, fInterpreter)) {
5066  // forward declarations
5067 
5068  while (getline(file, line, '\n')) {
5069  if (line[0] == '[') break;
5070  if (!uniqueString) {
5071  Error("ReadRootmapFile", "Cannot handle \"{ decls }\" sections in custom rootmap file %s",
5072  rootmapfileNoBackslash.c_str());
5073  return -4;
5074  }
5075  uniqueString->Append(line);
5076  }
5077  }
5078  const char firstChar=line[0];
5079  if (firstChar == '[') {
5080  // new section (library)
5081  auto brpos = line.find(']');
5082  if (brpos == string::npos) continue;
5083  lib_name = line.substr(1, brpos-1);
5084  size_t nspaces = 0;
5085  while( lib_name[nspaces] == ' ' ) ++nspaces;
5086  if (nspaces) lib_name.replace(0, nspaces, "");
5087  if (gDebug > 3) {
5088  TString lib_nameTstr(lib_name.c_str());
5089  TObjArray* tokens = lib_nameTstr.Tokenize(" ");
5090  const char* lib = ((TObjString *)tokens->At(0))->GetName();
5091  const char* wlib = gSystem->DynamicPathName(lib, kTRUE);
5092  if (wlib) {
5093  Info("ReadRootmapFile", "new section for %s", lib_nameTstr.Data());
5094  }
5095  else {
5096  Info("ReadRootmapFile", "section for %s (library does not exist)", lib_nameTstr.Data());
5097  }
5098  delete[] wlib;
5099  delete tokens;
5100  }
5101  }
5102  else {
5103  auto keyLenIt = keyLenMap.find(firstChar);
5104  if (keyLenIt == keyLenMap.end()) continue;
5105  unsigned int keyLen = keyLenIt->second;
5106  // Do not make a copy, just start after the key
5107  const char *keyname = line.c_str()+keyLen;
5108  if (gDebug > 6)
5109  Info("ReadRootmapFile", "class %s in %s", keyname, lib_name.c_str());
5110  TEnvRec* isThere = fMapfile->Lookup(keyname);
5111  if (isThere){
5112  if(lib_name != isThere->GetValue()){ // the same key for two different libs
5113  if (firstChar == 'n') {
5114  if (gDebug > 3)
5115  Info("ReadRootmapFile", "namespace %s found in %s is already in %s",
5116  keyname, lib_name.c_str(), isThere->GetValue());
5117  } else if (firstChar == 'h'){ // it is a header: add the libname to the list of libs to be loaded.
5118  lib_name+=" ";
5119  lib_name+=isThere->GetValue();
5120  fMapfile->SetValue(keyname, lib_name.c_str());
5121  }
5122  else if (!TClassEdit::IsSTLCont(keyname)) {
5123  Warning("ReadRootmapFile", "%s %s found in %s is already in %s", line.substr(0, keyLen).c_str(),
5124  keyname, lib_name.c_str(), isThere->GetValue());
5125  }
5126  } else { // the same key for the same lib
5127  if (gDebug > 3)
5128  Info("ReadRootmapFile","Key %s was already defined for %s", keyname, lib_name.c_str());
5129  }
5130 
5131  } else {
5132  fMapfile->SetValue(keyname, lib_name.c_str());
5133  }
5134  }
5135  }
5136  file.close();
5137  }
5138 
5139  return 0;
5140 }
5141 
5142 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5143 /// Create a resource table and read the (possibly) three resource files, i.e
5144 /// $ROOTSYS/etc/system<name> (or ROOTETCDIR/system<name>), $HOME/<name> and
5145 /// ./<name>. ROOT always reads ".rootrc" (in TROOT::InitSystem()). You can
5146 /// read additional user defined resource files by creating additional TEnv
5147 /// objects. By setting the shell variable ROOTENV_NO_HOME=1 the reading of
5148 /// the $HOME/<name> resource file will be skipped. This might be useful in
5149 /// case the home directory resides on an automounted remote file system
5150 /// and one wants to avoid the file system from being mounted.
5151 
5152 void TCling::InitRootmapFile(const char *name)
5153 {
5154  Bool_t ignore = fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(kFALSE);
5155 
5156  fMapfile->SetRcName(name);
5157 
5158  TString sname = "system";
5159  sname += name;
5160  char *s = gSystem->ConcatFileName(TROOT::GetEtcDir(), sname);
5161 
5162  Int_t ret = ReadRootmapFile(s);
5163  if (ret == -3) // old format
5164  fMapfile->ReadFile(s, kEnvGlobal);
5165  delete [] s;
5166  if (!gSystem->Getenv("ROOTENV_NO_HOME")) {
5167  s = gSystem->ConcatFileName(gSystem->HomeDirectory(), name);
5168  ret = ReadRootmapFile(s);
5169  if (ret == -3) // old format
5170  fMapfile->ReadFile(s, kEnvUser);
5171  delete [] s;
5172  if (strcmp(gSystem->HomeDirectory(), gSystem->WorkingDirectory())) {
5173  ret = ReadRootmapFile(name);
5174  if (ret == -3) // old format
5175  fMapfile->ReadFile(name, kEnvLocal);
5176  }
5177  } else {
5178  ret = ReadRootmapFile(name);
5179  if (ret == -3) // old format
5180  fMapfile->ReadFile(name, kEnvLocal);
5181  }
5182  fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(ignore);
5183 }
5184 
5185 
5186 namespace {
5187  using namespace clang;
5188 
5189  class ExtVisibleStorageAdder: public RecursiveASTVisitor<ExtVisibleStorageAdder>{
5190  // This class is to be considered an helper for autoloading.
5191  // It is a recursive visitor is used to inspect namespaces coming from
5192  // forward declarations in rootmaps and to set the external visible
5193  // storage flag for them.
5194  public:
5195  ExtVisibleStorageAdder(std::unordered_set<const NamespaceDecl*>& nsSet): fNSSet(nsSet) {};
5196  bool VisitNamespaceDecl(NamespaceDecl* nsDecl) {
5197  // We want to enable the external lookup for this namespace
5198  // because it may shadow the lookup of other names contained
5199  // in that namespace
5200 
5201  nsDecl->setHasExternalVisibleStorage();
5202  fNSSet.insert(nsDecl);
5203  return true;
5204  }
5205  private:
5206  std::unordered_set<const NamespaceDecl*>& fNSSet;
5207 
5208  };
5209 }
5210 
5211 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5212 /// Load map between class and library. If rootmapfile is specified a
5213 /// specific rootmap file can be added (typically used by ACLiC).
5214 /// In case of error -1 is returned, 0 otherwise.
5215 /// The interpreter uses this information to automatically load the shared
5216 /// library for a class (autoload mechanism), see the AutoLoad() methods below.
5217 
5218 Int_t TCling::LoadLibraryMap(const char* rootmapfile)
5219 {
5220  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5221  // open the [system].rootmap files
5222  if (!fMapfile) {
5223  fMapfile = new TEnv();
5224  fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(kTRUE);
5225 // fMapNamespaces = new THashTable();
5226 // fMapNamespaces->SetOwner();
5227  fRootmapFiles = new TObjArray;
5228  fRootmapFiles->SetOwner();
5229  InitRootmapFile(".rootmap");
5230  }
5231  bool needsRootMap = true;
5232  if (rootmapfile && *rootmapfile)
5233  needsRootMap = requiresRootMap(rootmapfile, fInterpreter);
5234 
5235  // Prepare a list of all forward declarations for cling
5236  // For some experiments it is easily as big as 500k characters. To be on the
5237  // safe side, we go for 1M.
5238  TUniqueString uniqueString(1048576);
5239 
5240  // Load all rootmap files in the dynamic load path ((DY)LD_LIBRARY_PATH, etc.).
5241  // A rootmap file must end with the string ".rootmap".
5242  TString ldpath = gSystem->GetDynamicPath();
5243  if (ldpath != fRootmapLoadPath) {
5244  fRootmapLoadPath = ldpath;
5245 #ifdef WIN32
5246  TObjArray* paths = ldpath.Tokenize(";");
5247 #else
5248  TObjArray* paths = ldpath.Tokenize(":");
5249 #endif
5250  TString d;
5251  for (Int_t i = 0; i < paths->GetEntriesFast(); i++) {
5252  d = ((TObjString *)paths->At(i))->GetString();
5253  // check if directory already scanned
5254  Int_t skip = 0;
5255  for (Int_t j = 0; j < i; j++) {
5256  TString pd = ((TObjString *)paths->At(j))->GetString();
5257  if (pd == d) {
5258  skip++;
5259  break;
5260  }
5261  }
5262  if (!skip) {
5263  void* dirp = gSystem->OpenDirectory(d);
5264  if (dirp) {
5265  if (gDebug > 3) {
5266  Info("LoadLibraryMap", "%s", d.Data());
5267  }
5268  const char* f1;
5269  while ((f1 = gSystem->GetDirEntry(dirp))) {
5270  TString f = f1;
5271  if (f.EndsWith(".rootmap")) {
5272  TString p;
5273  p = d + "/" + f;
5274  if (!gSystem->AccessPathName(p, kReadPermission)) {
5275  if (!fRootmapFiles->FindObject(f) && f != ".rootmap") {
5276  if (gDebug > 4) {
5277  Info("LoadLibraryMap", " rootmap file: %s", p.Data());
5278  }
5279  Int_t ret;
5280  if (needsRootMap)
5281  ret = ReadRootmapFile(p,&uniqueString);
5282  else
5283  ret = ReadRootmapFile(p);
5284 
5285  if (ret == 0)
5286  fRootmapFiles->Add(new TNamed(gSystem->BaseName(f), p.Data()));
5287  if (ret == -3) {
5288  // old format
5289  fMapfile->ReadFile(p, kEnvGlobal);
5290  fRootmapFiles->Add(new TNamed(f, p));
5291  }
5292  }
5293  // else {
5294  // fprintf(stderr,"Reject %s because %s is already there\n",p.Data(),f.Data());
5295  // fRootmapFiles->FindObject(f)->ls();
5296  // }
5297  }
5298  }
5299  if (f.BeginsWith("rootmap")) {
5300  TString p;
5301  p = d + "/" + f;
5302  FileStat_t stat;
5303  if (gSystem->GetPathInfo(p, stat) == 0 && R_ISREG(stat.fMode)) {
5304  Warning("LoadLibraryMap", "please rename %s to end with \".rootmap\"", p.Data());
5305  }
5306  }
5307  }
5308  }
5309  gSystem->FreeDirectory(dirp);
5310  }
5311  }
5312  delete paths;
5313  if (fMapfile->GetTable() && !fMapfile->GetTable()->GetEntries()) {
5314  return -1;
5315  }
5316  }
5317  if (rootmapfile && *rootmapfile) {
5318  Int_t res;
5319  if (needsRootMap)
5320  res = ReadRootmapFile(rootmapfile, &uniqueString);
5321  else
5322  res = ReadRootmapFile(rootmapfile);
5323  if (res == 0) {
5324  //TString p = gSystem->ConcatFileName(gSystem->pwd(), rootmapfile);
5325  //fRootmapFiles->Add(new TNamed(gSystem->BaseName(rootmapfile), p.Data()));
5326  fRootmapFiles->Add(new TNamed(gSystem->BaseName(rootmapfile), rootmapfile));
5327  }
5328  else if (res == -3) {
5329  // old format
5330  Bool_t ignore = fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(kFALSE);
5331  fMapfile->ReadFile(rootmapfile, kEnvGlobal);
5332  fRootmapFiles->Add(new TNamed(gSystem->BaseName(rootmapfile), rootmapfile));
5333  fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(ignore);
5334  }
5335  }
5336  TEnvRec* rec;
5337  TIter next(fMapfile->GetTable());
5338  while ((rec = (TEnvRec*) next())) {
5339  TString cls = rec->GetName();
5340  if (!strncmp(cls.Data(), "Library.", 8) && cls.Length() > 8) {
5341  // get the first lib from the list of lib and dependent libs
5342  TString libs = rec->GetValue();
5343  if (libs == "") {
5344  continue;
5345  }
5346  TString delim(" ");
5347  TObjArray* tokens = libs.Tokenize(delim);
5348  const char* lib = ((TObjString*)tokens->At(0))->GetName();
5349  // convert "@@" to "::", we used "@@" because TEnv
5350  // considers "::" a terminator
5351  cls.Remove(0, 8);
5352  cls.ReplaceAll("@@", "::");
5353  // convert "-" to " ", since class names may have
5354  // blanks and TEnv considers a blank a terminator
5355  cls.ReplaceAll("-", " ");
5356  if (gDebug > 6) {
5357  const char* wlib = gSystem->DynamicPathName(lib, kTRUE);
5358  if (wlib) {
5359  Info("LoadLibraryMap", "class %s in %s", cls.Data(), wlib);
5360  }
5361  else {
5362  Info("LoadLibraryMap", "class %s in %s (library does not exist)", cls.Data(), lib);
5363  }
5364  delete[] wlib;
5365  }
5366  // Fill in the namespace candidate list
5367 // Ssiz_t last = cls.Last(':');
5368 // if (last != kNPOS) {
5369 // // Please note that the funny op overload does substring.
5370 // TString namespaceCand = cls(0, last - 1);
5371 // // This is a reference to a substring that lives in fMapfile
5372 // if (!fMapNamespaces->FindObject(namespaceCand.Data()))
5373 // fMapNamespaces->Add(new TNamed(namespaceCand.Data(), ""));
5374 // }
5375  delete tokens;
5376  }
5377  else if (!strncmp(cls.Data(), "Declare.", 8) && cls.Length() > 8) {
5378  cls.Remove(0, 8);
5379  // convert "-" to " ", since class names may have
5380  // blanks and TEnv considers a blank a terminator
5381  cls.ReplaceAll("-", " ");
5382  fInterpreter->declare(cls.Data());
5383  }
5384  }
5385 
5386  // Process the forward declarations collected
5387  cling::Transaction* T = nullptr;
5388  auto compRes= fInterpreter->declare(uniqueString.Data(), &T);
5389  assert(cling::Interpreter::kSuccess == compRes && "A declaration in a rootmap could not be compiled");
5390 
5391  if (compRes!=cling::Interpreter::kSuccess){
5392  Warning("LoadLibraryMap",
5393  "Problems in %s declaring '%s' were encountered.", rootmapfile, uniqueString.Data()) ;
5394  }
5395 
5396  if (T){
5397  ExtVisibleStorageAdder evsAdder(fNSFromRootmaps);
5398  for (auto declIt = T->decls_begin(); declIt < T->decls_end(); ++declIt) {
5399  if (declIt->m_DGR.isSingleDecl()) {
5400  if (Decl* D = declIt->m_DGR.getSingleDecl()) {
5401  if (NamespaceDecl* NSD = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(D)) {
5402  evsAdder.TraverseDecl(NSD);
5403  }
5404  }
5405  }
5406  }
5407  }
5408 
5409  // clear duplicates
5410 
5411  return 0;
5412 }
5413 
5414 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5415 /// Scan again along the dynamic path for library maps. Entries for the loaded
5416 /// shared libraries are unloaded first. This can be useful after reseting
5417 /// the dynamic path through TSystem::SetDynamicPath()
5418 /// In case of error -1 is returned, 0 otherwise.
5419 
5420 Int_t TCling::RescanLibraryMap()
5421 {
5422  UnloadAllSharedLibraryMaps();
5423  LoadLibraryMap();
5424  return 0;
5425 }
5426 
5427 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5428 /// Reload the library map entries coming from all the loaded shared libraries,
5429 /// after first unloading the current ones.
5430 /// In case of error -1 is returned, 0 otherwise.
5431 
5432 Int_t TCling::ReloadAllSharedLibraryMaps()
5433 {
5434  const TString sharedLibLStr = GetSharedLibs();
5435  const TObjArray* sharedLibL = sharedLibLStr.Tokenize(" ");
5436  const Int_t nrSharedLibs = sharedLibL->GetEntriesFast();
5437  for (Int_t ilib = 0; ilib < nrSharedLibs; ilib++) {
5438  const TString sharedLibStr = ((TObjString*)sharedLibL->At(ilib))->GetString();
5439  const TString sharedLibBaseStr = gSystem->BaseName(sharedLibStr);
5440  const Int_t ret = UnloadLibraryMap(sharedLibBaseStr);
5441  if (ret < 0) {
5442  continue;
5443  }
5444  TString rootMapBaseStr = sharedLibBaseStr;
5445  if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".dll")) {
5446  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".dll", "");
5447  }
5448  else if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".DLL")) {
5449  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".DLL", "");
5450  }
5451  else if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".so")) {
5452  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".so", "");
5453  }
5454  else if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".sl")) {
5455  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".sl", "");
5456  }
5457  else if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".dl")) {
5458  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".dl", "");
5459  }
5460  else if (sharedLibBaseStr.EndsWith(".a")) {
5461  rootMapBaseStr.ReplaceAll(".a", "");
5462  }
5463  else {
5464  Error("ReloadAllSharedLibraryMaps", "Unknown library type %s", sharedLibBaseStr.Data());
5465  delete sharedLibL;
5466  return -1;
5467  }
5468  rootMapBaseStr += ".rootmap";
5469  const char* rootMap = gSystem->Which(gSystem->GetDynamicPath(), rootMapBaseStr);
5470  if (!rootMap) {
5471  Error("ReloadAllSharedLibraryMaps", "Could not find rootmap %s in path", rootMapBaseStr.Data());
5472  delete[] rootMap;
5473  delete sharedLibL;
5474  return -1;
5475  }
5476  const Int_t status = LoadLibraryMap(rootMap);
5477  if (status < 0) {
5478  Error("ReloadAllSharedLibraryMaps", "Error loading map %s", rootMap);
5479  delete[] rootMap;
5480  delete sharedLibL;
5481  return -1;
5482  }
5483  delete[] rootMap;
5484  }
5485  delete sharedLibL;
5486  return 0;
5487 }
5488 
5489 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5490 /// Unload the library map entries coming from all the loaded shared libraries.
5491 /// Returns 0 if succesful
5492 
5493 Int_t TCling::UnloadAllSharedLibraryMaps()
5494 {
5495  const TString sharedLibLStr = GetSharedLibs();
5496  const TObjArray* sharedLibL = sharedLibLStr.Tokenize(" ");
5497  for (Int_t ilib = 0; ilib < sharedLibL->GetEntriesFast(); ilib++) {
5498  const TString sharedLibStr = ((TObjString*)sharedLibL->At(ilib))->GetString();
5499  const TString sharedLibBaseStr = gSystem->BaseName(sharedLibStr);
5500  UnloadLibraryMap(sharedLibBaseStr);
5501  }
5502  delete sharedLibL;
5503  return 0;
5504 }
5505 
5506 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5507 /// Unload library map entries coming from the specified library.
5508 /// Returns -1 in case no entries for the specified library were found,
5509 /// 0 otherwise.
5510 
5511 Int_t TCling::UnloadLibraryMap(const char* library)
5512 {
5513  if (!fMapfile || !library || !*library) {
5514  return 0;
5515  }
5516  TString libname(library);
5517  Ssiz_t idx = libname.Last('.');
5518  if (idx != kNPOS) {
5519  libname.Remove(idx);
5520  }
5521  size_t len = libname.Length();
5522  TEnvRec *rec;
5523  TIter next(fMapfile->GetTable());
5524  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5525  Int_t ret = 0;
5526  while ((rec = (TEnvRec *) next())) {
5527  TString cls = rec->GetName();
5528  if (cls.Length() > 2) {
5529  // get the first lib from the list of lib and dependent libs
5530  TString libs = rec->GetValue();
5531  if (libs == "") {
5532  continue;
5533  }
5534  TString delim(" ");
5535  TObjArray* tokens = libs.Tokenize(delim);
5536  const char* lib = ((TObjString *)tokens->At(0))->GetName();
5537  if (!strncmp(cls.Data(), "Library.", 8) && cls.Length() > 8) {
5538  // convert "@@" to "::", we used "@@" because TEnv
5539  // considers "::" a terminator
5540  cls.Remove(0, 8);
5541  cls.ReplaceAll("@@", "::");
5542  // convert "-" to " ", since class names may have
5543  // blanks and TEnv considers a blank a terminator
5544  cls.ReplaceAll("-", " ");
5545  }
5546  if (!strncmp(lib, libname.Data(), len)) {
5547  if (fMapfile->GetTable()->Remove(rec) == 0) {
5548  Error("UnloadLibraryMap", "entry for <%s, %s> not found in library map table", cls.Data(), lib);
5549  ret = -1;
5550  }
5551  }
5552  delete tokens;
5553  }
5554  }
5555  if (ret >= 0) {
5556  TString library_rootmap(library);
5557  if (!library_rootmap.EndsWith(".rootmap"))
5558  library_rootmap.Append(".rootmap");
5559  TNamed* mfile = 0;
5560  while ((mfile = (TNamed *)fRootmapFiles->FindObject(library_rootmap))) {
5561  fRootmapFiles->Remove(mfile);
5562  delete mfile;
5563  }
5564  fRootmapFiles->Compress();
5565  }
5566  return ret;
5567 }
5568 
5569 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5570 /// Register the autoloading information for a class.
5571 /// libs is a space separated list of libraries.
5572 
5573 Int_t TCling::SetClassSharedLibs(const char *cls, const char *libs)
5574 {
5575  if (!cls || !*cls)
5576  return 0;
5577 
5578  TString key = TString("Library.") + cls;
5579  // convert "::" to "@@", we used "@@" because TEnv
5580  // considers "::" a terminator
5581  key.ReplaceAll("::", "@@");
5582  // convert "-" to " ", since class names may have
5583  // blanks and TEnv considers a blank a terminator
5584  key.ReplaceAll(" ", "-");
5585 
5586  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5587  if (!fMapfile) {
5588  fMapfile = new TEnv();
5589  fMapfile->IgnoreDuplicates(kTRUE);
5590 // fMapNamespaces = new THashTable();
5591 // fMapNamespaces->SetOwner();
5592 
5593  fRootmapFiles = new TObjArray;
5594  fRootmapFiles->SetOwner();
5595 
5596  InitRootmapFile(".rootmap");
5597  }
5598  //fMapfile->SetValue(key, libs);
5599  fMapfile->SetValue(cls, libs);
5600  return 1;
5601 }

5603 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5604 /// Demangle the name (from the typeinfo) and then request the class
5605 /// via the usual name based interface (TClass::GetClass).
5606 
5607 TClass *TCling::GetClass(const std::type_info& typeinfo, Bool_t load) const
5608 {
5609  int err = 0;
5610  char* demangled_name = TClassEdit::DemangleTypeIdName(typeinfo, err);
5611  if (err) return 0;
5612  TClass* theClass = TClass::GetClass(demangled_name, load, kTRUE);
5613  free(demangled_name);
5614  return theClass;
5615 }
5616 
5617 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5618 /// Load library containing the specified class. Returns 0 in case of error
5619 /// and 1 in case if success.
5620 
5621 Int_t TCling::AutoLoad(const std::type_info& typeinfo, Bool_t knowDictNotLoaded /* = kFALSE */)
5622 {
5623  int err = 0;
5624  char* demangled_name_c = TClassEdit::DemangleTypeIdName(typeinfo, err);
5625  if (err) {
5626  return 0;
5627  }
5628 
5629  std::string demangled_name(demangled_name_c);
5630  free(demangled_name_c);
5631 
5632  // AutoLoad expects (because TClass::GetClass already prepares it that way) a
5633  // shortened name.
5634  TClassEdit::TSplitType splitname( demangled_name.c_str(), (TClassEdit::EModType)(TClassEdit::kLong64 | TClassEdit::kDropStd) );
5635  splitname.ShortType(demangled_name, TClassEdit::kDropStlDefault | TClassEdit::kDropStd);
5636 
5637  // No need to worry about typedef, they aren't any ... but there are
5638  // inlined namespaces ...
5639 
5640  Int_t result = AutoLoad(demangled_name.c_str());
5641  if (result == 0) {
5642  demangled_name = TClassEdit::GetLong64_Name(demangled_name);
5643  result = AutoLoad(demangled_name.c_str(), knowDictNotLoaded);
5644  }
5645 
5646  return result;
5647 }
5648 
5649 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5650 /// Load library containing the specified class. Returns 0 in case of error
5651 /// and 1 in case if success.
5652 
5653 Int_t TCling::AutoLoad(const char *cls, Bool_t knowDictNotLoaded /* = kFALSE */)
5654 {
5655  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5656 
5657  if (!knowDictNotLoaded && gClassTable->GetDictNorm(cls)) {
5658  // The library is already loaded as the class's dictionary is known.
5659  // Return success.
5660  // Note: the name (cls) is expected to be normalized as it comes either
5661  // from a callbacks (that can/should calculate the normalized name from the
5662  // decl) or from TClass::GetClass (which does also calculate the normalized
5663  // name).
5664  return 1;
5665  }
5666 
5667  if (gDebug > 2) {
5668  Info("TCling::AutoLoad",
5669  "Trying to autoload for %s", cls);
5670  }
5671 
5672  Int_t status = 0;
5673  if (!gROOT || !gInterpreter || gROOT->TestBit(TObject::kInvalidObject)) {
5674  if (gDebug > 2) {
5675  Info("TCling::AutoLoad",
5676  "Disabled due to gROOT or gInterpreter being invalid/not ready (the class name is %s)", cls);
5677  }
5678  return status;
5679  }
5680  if (!fAllowLibLoad) {
5681  // Never load any library from rootcling/genreflex.
5682  if (gDebug > 2) {
5683  Info("TCling::AutoLoad",
5684  "Explicitly disabled (the class name is %s)", cls);
5685  }
5686  return 0;
5687  }
5688  // Prevent the recursion when the library dictionary are loaded.
5689  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoLoadOff(this);
5690  // Try using externally provided callback first.
5691  if (fAutoLoadCallBack) {
5692  int success = (*(AutoLoadCallBack_t)fAutoLoadCallBack)(cls);
5693  if (success)
5694  return success;
5695  }
5696  // lookup class to find list of dependent libraries
5697  TString deplibs = GetClassSharedLibs(cls);
5698  if (!deplibs.IsNull()) {
5699  TString delim(" ");
5700  TObjArray* tokens = deplibs.Tokenize(delim);
5701  for (Int_t i = (tokens->GetEntriesFast() - 1); i > 0; --i) {
5702  const char* deplib = ((TObjString*)tokens->At(i))->GetName();
5703  if (gROOT->LoadClass(cls, deplib) == 0) {
5704  if (gDebug > 0) {
5705  Info("TCling::AutoLoad",
5706  "loaded dependent library %s for %s", deplib, cls);
5707  }
5708  }
5709  else {
5710  Error("TCling::AutoLoad",
5711  "failure loading dependent library %s for %s",
5712  deplib, cls);
5713  }
5714  }
5715  const char* lib = ((TObjString*)tokens->At(0))->GetName();
5716  if (lib && lib[0]) {
5717  if (gROOT->LoadClass(cls, lib) == 0) {
5718  if (gDebug > 0) {
5719  Info("TCling::AutoLoad",
5720  "loaded library %s for %s", lib, cls);
5721  }
5722  status = 1;
5723  }
5724  else {
5725  Error("TCling::AutoLoad",
5726  "failure loading library %s for %s", lib, cls);
5727  }
5728  }
5729  delete tokens;
5730  }
5731 
5732  return status;
5733 }
5734 
5735 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5736 /// Parse the payload or header.
5737 
5738 static cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult ExecAutoParse(const char *what,
5739  Bool_t header,
5740  cling::Interpreter *interpreter)
5741 {
5742  std::string code = gNonInterpreterClassDef ;
5743  if (!header) {
5744  // This is the complete header file content and not the
5745  // name of a header.
5746  code += what;
5747 
5748  } else {
5749  code += ("#include \"");
5750  code += what;
5751  code += "\"\n";
5752  }
5753  code += ("#ifdef __ROOTCLING__\n"
5754  "#undef __ROOTCLING__\n"
5755  + gInterpreterClassDef +
5756  "#endif");
5757 
5758  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult cr;
5759  {
5760  // scope within which diagnostics are de-activated
5761  // For now we disable diagnostics because we saw them already at
5762  // dictionary generation time. That won't be an issue with the PCMs.
5763 
5764  Sema &SemaR = interpreter->getSema();
5765  ROOT::Internal::ParsingStateRAII parsingStateRAII(interpreter->getParser(), SemaR);
5766  clangDiagSuppr diagSuppr(SemaR.getDiagnostics());
5767 
5768  #if defined(R__MUST_REVISIT)
5769  #if R__MUST_REVISIT(6,2)
5770  Warning("TCling::RegisterModule","Diagnostics suppression should be gone by now.");
5771  #endif
5772  #endif
5773 
5774  cr = interpreter->parseForModule(code);
5775  }
5776  return cr;
5777 }
5778 
5779 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5780 /// Helper routine for TCling::AutoParse implementing the actual call to the
5781 /// parser and looping over template parameters (if
5782 /// any) and when they don't have a registered header to autoparse,
5783 /// recurse over their template parameters.
5784 ///
5785 /// Returns the number of header parsed.
5786 
5787 UInt_t TCling::AutoParseImplRecurse(const char *cls, bool topLevel)
5788 {
5789  // We assume the lock has already been taken.
5790  // R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5791 
5792  Int_t nHheadersParsed = 0;
5793  unsigned long offset = 0;
5794  if (strncmp(cls, "const ", 6) == 0) {
5795  offset = 6;
5796  }
5797 
5798  // Loop on the possible autoparse keys
5799  bool skipFirstEntry = false;
5800  std::vector<std::string> autoparseKeys;
5801  if (strchr(cls, '<')) {
5802  int nestedLoc = 0;
5803  TClassEdit::GetSplit(cls + offset, autoparseKeys, nestedLoc, TClassEdit::kDropTrailStar);
5804  // Check if we can skip the name of the template in the autoparses
5805  // Take all the scopes one by one. If all of them are in the AST, we do not
5806  // need to autoparse for that particular template.
5807  if (!autoparseKeys.empty() && !autoparseKeys[0].empty()) {
5808  // autoparseKeys[0] is empty when the input is not a template instance.
5809  // The case strchr(cls, '<') != 0 but still not a template instance can
5810  // happens 'just' for string (GetSplit replaces the template by the short name
5811  // and then use that for thew splitting)
5812  TString templateName(autoparseKeys[0]);
5813  auto tokens = templateName.Tokenize("::");
5814  clang::NamedDecl* previousScopeAsNamedDecl = nullptr;
5815  clang::DeclContext* previousScopeAsContext = fInterpreter->getCI()->getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
5816  if (TClassEdit::IsStdClass(cls + offset))
5817  previousScopeAsContext = fInterpreter->getSema().getStdNamespace();
5818  auto nTokens = tokens->GetEntries();
5819  for (Int_t tk = 0; tk < nTokens; ++tk) {
5820  auto scopeObj = tokens->UncheckedAt(tk);
5821  auto scopeName = ((TObjString*) scopeObj)->String().Data();
5822  previousScopeAsNamedDecl = cling::utils::Lookup::Named(&fInterpreter->getSema(), scopeName, previousScopeAsContext);
5823  // Check if we have multiple nodes in the AST with this name
5824  if ((clang::NamedDecl*)-1 == previousScopeAsNamedDecl) break;
5825  previousScopeAsContext = llvm::dyn_cast_or_null<clang::DeclContext>(previousScopeAsNamedDecl);
5826  if (!previousScopeAsContext) break; // this is not a context
5827  }
5828  delete tokens;
5829  // Now, let's check if the last scope, the template, has a definition, i.e. it's not a fwd decl
5830  if ((clang::NamedDecl*)-1 != previousScopeAsNamedDecl) {
5831  if (auto templateDecl = llvm::dyn_cast_or_null<clang::ClassTemplateDecl>(previousScopeAsNamedDecl)) {
5832  if (auto templatedDecl = templateDecl->getTemplatedDecl()) {
5833  skipFirstEntry = templatedDecl->hasDefinition();
5834  }
5835  }
5836  }
5837 
5838  }
5839  }
5840  if (topLevel) autoparseKeys.emplace_back(cls);
5841 
5842  for (const auto & apKeyStr : autoparseKeys) {
5843  if (skipFirstEntry) {
5844  skipFirstEntry=false;
5845  continue;
5846  }
5847  if (apKeyStr.empty()) continue;
5848  const char *apKey = apKeyStr.c_str();
5849  std::size_t normNameHash(fStringHashFunction(apKey));
5850  // If the class was not looked up
5851  if (gDebug > 1) {
5852  Info("TCling::AutoParse",
5853  "Starting autoparse for %s\n", apKey);
5854  }
5855  if (fLookedUpClasses.insert(normNameHash).second) {
5856  auto const &iter = fClassesHeadersMap.find(normNameHash);
5857  if (iter != fClassesHeadersMap.end()) {
5858  const cling::Transaction *T = fInterpreter->getCurrentTransaction();
5859  fTransactionHeadersMap.insert({T,normNameHash});
5860  auto const &hNamesPtrs = iter->second;
5861  if (gDebug > 1) {
5862  Info("TCling::AutoParse",
5863  "We can proceed for %s. We have %s headers.", apKey, std::to_string(hNamesPtrs.size()).c_str());
5864  }
5865  for (auto & hName : hNamesPtrs) {
5866  if (fParsedPayloadsAddresses.count(hName) == 1) continue;
5867  if (0 != fPayloads.count(normNameHash)) {
5868  float initRSSval=0.f, initVSIZEval=0.f;
5869  (void) initRSSval; // Avoid unused var warning
5870  (void) initVSIZEval;
5871  if (gDebug > 0) {
5872  Info("AutoParse",
5873  "Parsing full payload for %s", apKey);
5874  ProcInfo_t info;
5875  gSystem->GetProcInfo(&info);
5876  initRSSval = 1e-3*info.fMemResident;
5877  initVSIZEval = 1e-3*info.fMemVirtual;
5878  }
5879  auto cRes = ExecAutoParse(hName, kFALSE, fInterpreter);
5880  if (cRes != cling::Interpreter::kSuccess) {
5881  if (hName[0] == '\n')
5882  Error("AutoParse", "Error parsing payload code for class %s with content:\n%s", apKey, hName);
5883  } else {
5884  fParsedPayloadsAddresses.insert(hName);
5885  nHheadersParsed++;
5886  if (gDebug > 0){
5887  ProcInfo_t info;
5888  gSystem->GetProcInfo(&info);
5889  float endRSSval = 1e-3*info.fMemResident;
5890  float endVSIZEval = 1e-3*info.fMemVirtual;
5891  Info("Autoparse", ">>> RSS key %s - before %.3f MB - after %.3f MB - delta %.3f MB", apKey, initRSSval, endRSSval, endRSSval-initRSSval);
5892  Info("Autoparse", ">>> VSIZE key %s - before %.3f MB - after %.3f MB - delta %.3f MB", apKey, initVSIZEval, endVSIZEval, endVSIZEval-initVSIZEval);
5893  }
5894  }
5895  } else if (!IsLoaded(hName)) {
5896  if (gDebug > 0) {
5897  Info("AutoParse",
5898  "Parsing single header %s", hName);
5899  }
5900  auto cRes = ExecAutoParse(hName, kTRUE, fInterpreter);
5901  if (cRes != cling::Interpreter::kSuccess) {
5902  Error("AutoParse", "Error parsing headerfile %s for class %s.", hName, apKey);
5903  } else {
5904  nHheadersParsed++;
5905  }
5906  }
5907  }
5908  }
5909  else {
5910  // There is no header registered for this class, if this a
5911  // template, it will be instantiated if/when it is requested
5912  // and if we do no load/parse its components we might end up
5913  // not using an eventual specialization.
5914  if (strchr(apKey, '<')) {
5915  nHheadersParsed += AutoParseImplRecurse(apKey, false);
5916  }
5917  }
5918  }
5919  }
5920 
5921  return nHheadersParsed;
5922 
5923 }
5924 
5925 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5926 /// Parse the headers relative to the class
5927 /// Returns 1 in case of success, 0 in case of failure
5928 
5929 Int_t TCling::AutoParse(const char *cls)
5930 {
5931  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
5932 
5933  if (!fHeaderParsingOnDemand || fIsAutoParsingSuspended) {
5934  if (fClingCallbacks->IsAutoloadingEnabled()) {
5935  return AutoLoad(cls);
5936  } else {
5937  return 0;
5938  }
5939  }
5940 
5941  if (gDebug > 1) {
5942  Info("TCling::AutoParse",
5943  "Trying to autoparse for %s", cls);
5944  }
5945 
5946  // The catalogue of headers is in the dictionary
5947  if (fClingCallbacks->IsAutoloadingEnabled()
5948  && !gClassTable->GetDictNorm(cls)) {
5949  // Need RAII against recursive (dictionary payload) parsing (ROOT-8445).
5950  ROOT::Internal::ParsingStateRAII parsingStateRAII(fInterpreter->getParser(),
5951  fInterpreter->getSema());
5952  AutoLoad(cls, true /*knowDictNotLoaded*/);
5953  }
5954 
5955  // Prevent the recursion when the library dictionary are loaded.
5956  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoLoadOff(this);
5957 
5958  // No recursive header parsing on demand; we require headers to be standalone.
5959  SuspendAutoParsing autoParseRAII(this);
5960 
5961  Int_t nHheadersParsed = AutoParseImplRecurse(cls,/*topLevel=*/ true);
5962 
5963  if (nHheadersParsed != 0) {
5964  while (!fClassesToUpdate.empty()) {
5965  TClass *oldcl = fClassesToUpdate.back().first;
5966  if (oldcl->GetState() != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
5967  // if (gDebug > 2) Info("RegisterModule", "Forcing TClass init for %s", oldcl->GetName());
5968  DictFuncPtr_t dict = fClassesToUpdate.back().second;
5969  fClassesToUpdate.pop_back();
5970  // Calling func could manipulate the list so, let maintain the list
5971  // then call the dictionary function.
5972  TClass *ncl = dict();
5973  if (ncl) ncl->PostLoadCheck();
5974  } else {
5975  fClassesToUpdate.pop_back();
5976  }
5977  }
5978  }
5979 
5980  return nHheadersParsed > 0 ? 1 : 0;
5981 }
5982 
5983 // This is a function which gets callback from cling when DynamicLibraryManager->loadLibrary failed for some reason.
5984 // Try to solve the problem by autoloading. Return true when autoloading success, return
5985 // false if not.
5986 bool TCling::LibraryLoadingFailed(const std::string& errmessage, const std::string& libStem, bool permanent, bool resolved)
5987 {
5988  StringRef errMsg(errmessage);
5989  if (errMsg.contains("undefined symbol: ")) {
5990  // This branch is taken when the callback was from DynamicLibraryManager::loadLibrary
5991  std::string mangled_name = std::string(errMsg.split("undefined symbol: ").second);
5992  void* res = ((TCling*)gCling)->LazyFunctionCreatorAutoload(mangled_name);
5993  cling::DynamicLibraryManager* DLM = fInterpreter->getDynamicLibraryManager();
5994  if (res && DLM && (DLM->loadLibrary(libStem, permanent, resolved) == cling::DynamicLibraryManager::kLoadLibSuccess))
5995  // Return success when LazyFunctionCreatorAutoload could find mangled_name
5996  return true;
5997  } else {
5998  // The callback is from IncrementalExecutor::diagnoseUnresolvedSymbols
5999  if ( ((TCling*)gCling)->LazyFunctionCreatorAutoload(errmessage))
6000  return true;
6001  }
6002 
6003  return false;
6004 }
6005 
6006 // This is a GNU implementation of hash used in bloom filter!
6007 static uint32_t GNUHash(StringRef S) {
6008  uint32_t H = 5381;
6009  for (uint8_t C : S)
6010  H = (H << 5) + H + C;
6011  return H;
6012 }
6013 
6014 static StringRef GetGnuHashSection(llvm::object::ObjectFile *file) {
6015  for (auto S : file->sections()) {
6016  StringRef name;
6017  S.getName(name);
6018  if (name == ".gnu.hash") {
6019  StringRef content;
6020  S.getContents(content);
6021  return content;
6022  }
6023  }
6024  return "";
6025 }
6026 
6027 // Bloom filter. See https://blogs.oracle.com/solaris/gnu-hash-elf-sections-v2
6028 // for detailed desctiption. In short, there is a .gnu.hash section in so files which contains
6029 // bloomfilter hash value that we can compare with our mangled_name hash. This is a false positive
6030 // probability data structure and enables us to skip libraries which doesn't contain mangled_name definition!
6031 // PE and Mach-O files doesn't have .gnu.hash bloomfilter section, so this is a specific optimization for ELF.
6032 // This is fine because performance critical part (data centers) are running on Linux :)
6033 static bool LookupBloomFilter(llvm::object::ObjectFile *soFile, uint32_t hash) {
6034  const int bits = 64;
6035 
6036  StringRef contents = GetGnuHashSection(soFile);
6037  if (contents.size() < 16)
6038  // We need to search if the library doesn't have .gnu.hash section!
6039  return true;
6040  const char* hashContent = contents.data();
6041 
6042  // See https://flapenguin.me/2017/05/10/elf-lookup-dt-gnu-hash/ for .gnu.hash table layout.
6043  uint32_t maskWords = *reinterpret_cast<const uint32_t *>(hashContent + 8);
6044  uint32_t shift2 = *reinterpret_cast<const uint32_t *>(hashContent + 12);
6045  uint32_t hash2 = hash >> shift2;
6046  uint32_t n = (hash / bits) % maskWords;
6047 
6048  const char *bloomfilter = hashContent + 16;
6049  const char *hash_pos = bloomfilter + n*(bits/8); // * (Bits / 8)
6050  uint64_t word = *reinterpret_cast<const uint64_t *>(hash_pos);
6051  uint64_t bitmask = ( (1ULL << (hash % bits)) | (1ULL << (hash2 % bits)));
6052  return (bitmask & word) == bitmask;
6053 }
6054 
6055 // Lookup for normal symbols
6056 static bool LookupNormalSymbols(llvm::object::ObjectFile *RealSoFile, const std::string& mangled_name, const std::string& LibName)
6057 {
6058  uint32_t hashedMangle = GNUHash(mangled_name);
6059  // Check Bloom filter. If false, it means that this library doesn't contain mangled_name defenition
6060  if (!LookupBloomFilter(RealSoFile, hashedMangle))
6061  return false;
6062 
6063  auto Symbols = RealSoFile->symbols();
6064  for (auto S : Symbols) {
6065  uint32_t Flags = S.getFlags();
6066  // DO NOT insert to table if symbol was undefined
6067  if (Flags & llvm::object::SymbolRef::SF_Undefined)
6068  continue;
6069 
6070  // Note, we are at last resort and loading library based on a weak
6071  // symbol is allowed. Otherwise, the JIT will issue an unresolved
6072  // symbol error.
6073  //
6074  // There are other weak symbol kinds (marked as 'V') to denote
6075  // typeinfo and vtables. It is unclear whether we should load such
6076  // libraries or from which library we should resolve the symbol.
6077  // We seem to not have a way to differentiate it from the symbol API.
6078 
6079  llvm::Expected<StringRef> SymNameErr = S.getName();
6080  if (!SymNameErr) {
6081  Warning("LookupNormalSymbols", "Failed to read symbol");
6082  continue;
6083  }
6084 
6085  if (SymNameErr.get() == mangled_name)
6086  return true;
6087  }
6088 
6089  return false;
6090 }
6091 
6092 static void* LazyFunctionCreatorAutoloadForModule(const std::string& mangled_name,
6093  cling::Interpreter *fInterpreter) {
6094  using namespace llvm::object;
6095  using namespace llvm::sys::path;
6096  using namespace llvm::sys::fs;
6097 
6098  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6099 
6100  static bool sFirstRun = true;
6101  static bool sFirstSystemLibrary = true;
6102  // sLibraies contains pair of sPaths[i] (eg. /home/foo/module) and library name (eg. libTMVA.so). The
6103  // reason why we're separating sLibraries and sPaths is that we have a lot of
6104  // dupulication in path, for example we have "/home/foo/module-release/lib/libFoo.so", "/home/../libBar.so", "/home/../lib.."
6105  // and it's waste of memory to store the full path.
6106  static std::vector< std::pair<uint32_t, std::string> > sLibraries;
6107  static std::vector<std::string> sPaths;
6108 
6109  // For system header autoloading
6110  static std::vector< std::pair<uint32_t, std::string> > sSysLibraries;
6111  static std::vector<std::string> sSysPaths;
6112 
6113  if (sFirstRun) {
6114  TCling__FindLoadedLibraries(sLibraries, sPaths, *fInterpreter, /* searchSystem */ false);
6115  sFirstRun = false;
6116  }
6117 
6118  // The JIT gives us a mangled name which has only one leading underscore on
6119  // all platforms, for instance _ZN8TRandom34RndmEv. However, on OSX the
6120  // linker stores this symbol as __ZN8TRandom34RndmEv (adding an extra _).
6121 #ifdef R__MACOSX
6122  std::string name_in_so = "_" + mangled_name;
6123 #else
6124  std::string name_in_so = mangled_name;
6125 #endif
6126 
6127 
6128  // Iterate over files under this path. We want to get each ".so" files
6129  for (std::pair<uint32_t, std::string> &P : sLibraries) {
6130  llvm::SmallString<400> Vec(sPaths[P.first]);
6131  llvm::sys::path::append(Vec, StringRef(P.second));
6132  const std::string LibName = Vec.str();
6133 
6134  auto SoFile = ObjectFile::createObjectFile(LibName);
6135  if (!SoFile)
6136  continue;
6137 
6138  if (LookupNormalSymbols(SoFile.get().getBinary(), name_in_so, LibName)) {
6139  if (gSystem->Load(LibName.c_str(), "", false) < 0)
6140  Error("LazyFunctionCreatorAutoloadForModule", "Failed to load library %s", LibName.c_str());
6141 
6142  // We want to delete a loaded library from sLibraries cache, because sLibraries is
6143  // a vector of candidate libraries which might be loaded in the future.
6144  sLibraries.erase(std::remove(sLibraries.begin(), sLibraries.end(), P), sLibraries.end());
6145  void* addr = llvm::sys::DynamicLibrary::SearchForAddressOfSymbol(mangled_name.c_str());
6146  return addr;
6147  }
6148  }
6149 
6150  // Normal lookup failed! Fall back to system library
6151  if (sFirstSystemLibrary) {
6152  TCling__FindLoadedLibraries(sSysLibraries, sSysPaths, *fInterpreter, /* searchSystem */ true);
6153  sFirstSystemLibrary = false;
6154  }
6155 
6156  for (std::pair<uint32_t, std::string> &P : sSysLibraries) {
6157  llvm::SmallString<400> Vec(sSysPaths[P.first]);
6158  llvm::sys::path::append(Vec, StringRef(P.second));
6159  const std::string LibName = Vec.str();
6160 
6161  auto SoFile = ObjectFile::createObjectFile(LibName);
6162  if (!SoFile)
6163  continue;
6164 
6165  auto RealSoFile = SoFile.get().getBinary();
6166 
6167  if (LookupNormalSymbols(RealSoFile, name_in_so, LibName)) {
6168  if (gSystem->Load(LibName.c_str(), "", false) < 0)
6169  Error("LazyFunctionCreatorAutoloadForModule", "Failed to load library %s", LibName.c_str());
6170 
6171  sSysLibraries.erase(std::remove(sSysLibraries.begin(), sSysLibraries.end(), P), sSysLibraries.end());
6172  void* addr = llvm::sys::DynamicLibrary::SearchForAddressOfSymbol(mangled_name.c_str());
6173  return addr;
6174  }
6175 
6176  // Lookup for dynamic symbols
6177  auto sections = RealSoFile->sections();
6178  for (auto section : sections) {
6179  llvm::StringRef sectionName;
6180  section.getName(sectionName);
6181 
6182  // .dynstr contains string of dynamic symbols
6183  if (sectionName == ".dynstr") {
6184  llvm::StringRef dContents;
6185  section.getContents(dContents);
6186  // If this library contains mangled name
6187  if (dContents.contains(mangled_name)) {
6188  if (gSystem->Load(LibName.c_str(), "", false) < 0)
6189  Error("LazyFunctionCreatorAutoloadForModule", "Failed to load library %s", LibName.c_str());
6190 
6191  // Delete a loaded library from sLibraries cache.
6192  sSysLibraries.erase(std::remove(sSysLibraries.begin(), sSysLibraries.end(), P), sSysLibraries.end());
6193  void* addr = llvm::sys::DynamicLibrary::SearchForAddressOfSymbol(mangled_name.c_str());
6194  return addr;
6195  }
6196  }
6197  }
6198  }
6199 
6200  // Lookup failed!!!!
6201  return nullptr;
6202 }
6203 
6204 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6205 /// Autoload a library based on a missing symbol.
6206 
6207 void* TCling::LazyFunctionCreatorAutoload(const std::string& mangled_name) {
6208  if (fCxxModulesEnabled)
6209  return LazyFunctionCreatorAutoloadForModule(mangled_name, fInterpreter);
6210 
6211  // First see whether the symbol is in the library that we are currently
6212  // loading. It will have access to the symbols of its dependent libraries,
6213  // thus checking "back()" is sufficient.
6214  if (!fRegisterModuleDyLibs.empty()) {
6215  if (void* addr = dlsym(fRegisterModuleDyLibs.back(),
6216  mangled_name.c_str())) {
6217  return addr;
6218  }
6219  }
6220 
6221  int err = 0;
6222  char* demangled_name_c = TClassEdit::DemangleName(mangled_name.c_str(), err);
6223  if (err) {
6224  return 0;
6225  }
6226 
6227  std::string name(demangled_name_c);
6228  free(demangled_name_c);
6229 
6230  //fprintf(stderr, "demangled name: '%s'\n", demangled_name);
6231  //
6232  // Separate out the class or namespace part of the
6233  // function name.
6234  //
6235 
6236  std::string::size_type pos = name.find("__thiscall ");
6237  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
6238  name.erase(0, pos + sizeof("__thiscall ")-1);
6239  }
6240  pos = name.find("__cdecl ");
6241  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
6242  name.erase(0, pos + sizeof("__cdecl ")-1);
6243  }
6244  if (!strncmp(name.c_str(), "typeinfo for ", sizeof("typeinfo for ")-1)) {
6245  name.erase(0, sizeof("typeinfo for ")-1);
6246  } else if (!strncmp(name.c_str(), "vtable for ", sizeof("vtable for ")-1)) {
6247  name.erase(0, sizeof("vtable for ")-1);
6248  } else if (!strncmp(name.c_str(), "operator", sizeof("operator")-1)
6249  && !isalnum(name[sizeof("operator")])) {
6250  // operator...(A, B) - let's try with A!
6251  name.erase(0, sizeof("operator")-1);
6252  pos = name.rfind('(');
6253  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
6254  name.erase(0, pos + 1);
6255  pos = name.find(",");
6256  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
6257  // remove next arg up to end, leaving only the first argument type.
6258  name.erase(pos);
6259  }
6260  pos = name.rfind(" const");
6261  if (pos != std::string::npos) {
6262  name.erase(pos, strlen(" const"));
6263  }
6264  while (!name.empty() && strchr("&*", name.back()))
6265  name.erase(name.length() - 1);
6266  }
6267  } else {
6268  TClassEdit::FunctionSplitInfo fsi;
6269  TClassEdit::SplitFunction(name, fsi);
6270  name = fsi.fScopeName;
6271  }
6272  //fprintf(stderr, "name: '%s'\n", name.c_str());
6273  // Now we have the class or namespace name, so do the lookup.
6274  TString libs = GetClassSharedLibs(name.c_str());
6275  if (libs.IsNull()) {
6276  // Not found in the map, all done.
6277  return 0;
6278  }
6279  //fprintf(stderr, "library: %s\n", iter->second.c_str());
6280  // Now we have the name of the libraries to load, so load them.
6281 
6282  TString lib;
6283  Ssiz_t posLib = 0;
6284  while (libs.Tokenize(lib, posLib)) {
6285  if (gSystem->Load(lib, "", kFALSE /*system*/) < 0) {
6286  // The library load failed, all done.
6287  //fprintf(stderr, "load failed: %s\n", errmsg.c_str());
6288  return 0;
6289  }
6290  }
6291 
6292  //fprintf(stderr, "load succeeded.\n");
6293  // Get the address of the function being called.
6294  void* addr = llvm::sys::DynamicLibrary::SearchForAddressOfSymbol(mangled_name.c_str());
6295  //fprintf(stderr, "addr: %016lx\n", reinterpret_cast<unsigned long>(addr));
6296  return addr;
6297 }

6316 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6317 /// Internal function. Inform a TClass about its new TagDecl or NamespaceDecl.
6318 
6319 void TCling::UpdateClassInfoWithDecl(const void* vTD)
6320 {
6321  const NamedDecl* ND = static_cast<const NamedDecl*>(vTD);
6322  const TagDecl* td = dyn_cast<TagDecl>(ND);
6323  std::string name;
6324  TagDecl* tdDef = 0;
6325  if (td) {
6326  tdDef = td->getDefinition();
6327  // Let's pass the decl to the TClass only if it has a definition.
6328  if (!tdDef) return;
6329  td = tdDef;
6330  ND = td;
6331 
6332  if (llvm::isa<clang::FunctionDecl>(td->getDeclContext())) {
6333  // Ignore declaration within a function.
6334  return;
6335  }
6336  clang::QualType type( td->getTypeForDecl(), 0 );
6337 
6338  auto declName=ND->getNameAsString();
6339  if (!TClass::HasNoInfoOrEmuOrFwdDeclaredDecl(declName.c_str())){
6340 // printf ("Impossible to find a TClassEntry in kNoInfo or kEmulated the decl of which would be called %s. Skip w/o building the normalized name.\n",declName );
6341  return;
6342  }
6343 
6344  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetNormalizedName(name, type, *fInterpreter, *fNormalizedCtxt);
6345  } else {
6346  name = ND->getNameAsString();
6347  }
6348 
6349  // Supposedly we are being called while something is being
6350  // loaded ... let's now tell the autoloader to do the work
6351  // yet another time.
6352  SuspendAutoloadingRAII autoLoadOff(this);
6353  // FIXME: There can be more than one TClass for a single decl.
6354  // for example vector<double> and vector<Double32_t>
6355  TClass* cl = (TClass*)gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(name.c_str());
6356  if (cl && GetModTClasses().find(cl) == GetModTClasses().end()) {
6357  TClingClassInfo* cci = ((TClingClassInfo*)cl->fClassInfo);
6358  if (cci) {
6359  // If we only had a forward declaration then update the
6360  // TClingClassInfo with the definition if we have it now.
6361  const TagDecl* tdOld = llvm::dyn_cast_or_null<TagDecl>(cci->GetDecl());
6362  if (!tdOld || (tdDef && tdDef != tdOld)) {
6363  cl->ResetCaches();
6364  TClass::RemoveClassDeclId(cci->GetDeclId());
6365  if (td) {
6366  // It's a tag decl, not a namespace decl.
6367  cci->Init(*cci->GetType());
6368  TClass::AddClassToDeclIdMap(cci->GetDeclId(), cl);
6369  }
6370  }
6371  } else if (!cl->TestBit(TClass::kLoading) && !cl->fHasRootPcmInfo) {
6372  cl->ResetCaches();
6373  // yes, this is almost a waste of time, but we do need to lookup
6374  // the 'type' corresponding to the TClass anyway in order to
6375  // preserve the opaque typedefs (Double32_t)
6376  cl->fClassInfo = (ClassInfo_t *)new TClingClassInfo(fInterpreter, cl->GetName());
6377  // We now need to update the state and bits.
6378  if (cl->fState != TClass::kHasTClassInit) {
6379  // if (!cl->fClassInfo->IsValid()) cl->fState = TClass::kForwardDeclared; else
6380  cl->fState = TClass::kInterpreted;
6381  cl->ResetBit(TClass::kIsEmulation);
6382  }
6383  TClass::AddClassToDeclIdMap(((TClingClassInfo*)(cl->fClassInfo))->GetDeclId(), cl);
6384  }
6385  }
6386 }

6415 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6416 
6417 void TCling::UpdateListsOnCommitted(const cling::Transaction &T) {
6418  std::set<TClass*> modifiedTClasses; // TClasses that require update after this transaction
6419 
6420  // If the transaction does not contain anything we can return earlier.
6421  if (!HandleNewTransaction(T)) return;
6422 
6423  bool isTUTransaction = false;
6424  if (!T.empty() && T.decls_begin() + 1 == T.decls_end() && !T.hasNestedTransactions()) {
6425  clang::Decl* FirstDecl = *(T.decls_begin()->m_DGR.begin());
6426  if (llvm::isa<clang::TranslationUnitDecl>(FirstDecl)) {
6427  // The is the first transaction, we have to expose to meta
6428  // what's already in the AST.
6429  isTUTransaction = true;
6430  }
6431  }
6432 
6433  std::set<const void*> TransactionDeclSet;
6434  if (!isTUTransaction && T.decls_end() - T.decls_begin()) {
6435  const clang::Decl* WrapperFD = T.getWrapperFD();
6436  for (cling::Transaction::const_iterator I = T.decls_begin(), E = T.decls_end();
6437  I != E; ++I) {
6438  if (I->m_Call != cling::Transaction::kCCIHandleTopLevelDecl
6439  && I->m_Call != cling::Transaction::kCCIHandleTagDeclDefinition)
6440  continue;
6441 
6442  for (DeclGroupRef::const_iterator DI = I->m_DGR.begin(),
6443  DE = I->m_DGR.end(); DI != DE; ++DI) {
6444  if (*DI == WrapperFD)
6445  continue;
6446  TransactionDeclSet.insert(*DI);
6447  ((TCling*)gCling)->HandleNewDecl(*DI, false, modifiedTClasses);
6448  }
6449  }
6450  }
6451 
6452  // The above might trigger more decls to be deserialized.
6453  // Thus the iteration over the deserialized decls must be last.
6454  for (cling::Transaction::const_iterator I = T.deserialized_decls_begin(),
6455  E = T.deserialized_decls_end(); I != E; ++I) {
6456  for (DeclGroupRef::const_iterator DI = I->m_DGR.begin(),
6457  DE = I->m_DGR.end(); DI != DE; ++DI)
6458  if (TransactionDeclSet.find(*DI) == TransactionDeclSet.end()) {
6459  //FIXME: HandleNewDecl should take DeclGroupRef
6460  ((TCling*)gCling)->HandleNewDecl(*DI, /*isDeserialized*/true,
6461  modifiedTClasses);
6462  }
6463  }
6464 
6465 
6466  // When fully building the reflection info in TClass, a deserialization
6467  // could be triggered, which may result in request for building the
6468  // reflection info for the same TClass. This in turn will clear the caches
6469  // for the TClass in-flight and cause null ptr derefs.
6470  // FIXME: This is a quick fix, solving most of the issues. The actual
6471  // question is: Shouldn't TClass provide a lock mechanism on update or lock
6472  // itself until the update is done.
6473  //
6474  std::vector<TClass*> modifiedTClassesDiff(modifiedTClasses.size());
6475  std::vector<TClass*>::iterator it;
6476  it = set_difference(modifiedTClasses.begin(), modifiedTClasses.end(),
6477  ((TCling*)gCling)->GetModTClasses().begin(),
6478  ((TCling*)gCling)->GetModTClasses().end(),
6479  modifiedTClassesDiff.begin());
6480  modifiedTClassesDiff.resize(it - modifiedTClassesDiff.begin());
6481 
6482  // Lock the TClass for updates
6483  ((TCling*)gCling)->GetModTClasses().insert(modifiedTClassesDiff.begin(),
6484  modifiedTClassesDiff.end());
6485  for (std::vector<TClass*>::const_iterator I = modifiedTClassesDiff.begin(),
6486  E = modifiedTClassesDiff.end(); I != E; ++I) {
6487  // Make sure the TClass has not been deleted.
6488  if (!gROOT->GetListOfClasses()->FindObject(*I)) {
6489  continue;
6490  }
6491  // Could trigger deserialization of decls.
6492  cling::Interpreter::PushTransactionRAII RAII(fInterpreter);
6493  // Unlock the TClass for updates
6494  ((TCling*)gCling)->GetModTClasses().erase(*I);
6495 
6496  }
6497 }
6498 
6499 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6500 /// Helper function to go through the members of a class or namespace and unload them.
6501 
6502 void TCling::UnloadClassMembers(TClass* cl, const clang::DeclContext* DC) {
6503 
6504  TDataMember* var = 0;
6505  TFunction* function = 0;
6506  TEnum* e = 0;
6507  TFunctionTemplate* functiontemplate = 0;
6508  TListOfDataMembers* datamembers = (TListOfDataMembers*)cl->GetListOfDataMembers();
6509  TListOfFunctions* functions = (TListOfFunctions*)cl->GetListOfMethods();
6510  TListOfEnums* enums = (TListOfEnums*)cl->GetListOfEnums();
6511  TListOfFunctionTemplates* functiontemplates = (TListOfFunctionTemplates*)cl->GetListOfFunctionTemplates();
6512  for (DeclContext::decl_iterator RI = DC->decls_begin(), RE = DC->decls_end(); RI != RE; ++RI) {
6513  if (isa<VarDecl>(*RI) || isa<FieldDecl>(*RI)) {
6514  const clang::ValueDecl* VD = dyn_cast<ValueDecl>(*RI);
6515  var = (TDataMember*)datamembers->FindObject(VD->getNameAsString().c_str());
6516  if (var) {
6517  // Unload the global by setting the DataMemberInfo_t to 0
6518  datamembers->Unload(var);
6519  var->Update(0);
6520  }
6521  } else if (const FunctionDecl* FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(*RI)) {
6522  function = (TFunction*)functions->FindObject(FD->getNameAsString().c_str());
6523  if (function) {
6524  functions->Unload(function);
6525  function->Update(0);
6526  }
6527  } else if (const EnumDecl* ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(*RI)) {
6528  e = (TEnum*)enums->FindObject(ED->getNameAsString().c_str());
6529  if (e) {
6530  TIter iEnumConst(e->GetConstants());
6531  while (TEnumConstant* enumConst = (TEnumConstant*)iEnumConst()) {
6532  // Since the enum is already created and valid that ensures us that
6533  // we have the enum constants created as well.
6534  enumConst = (TEnumConstant*)datamembers->FindObject(enumConst->GetName());
6535  if (enumConst && enumConst->IsValid()) {
6536  datamembers->Unload(enumConst);
6537  enumConst->Update(0);
6538  }
6539  }
6540  enums->Unload(e);
6541  e->Update(0);
6542  }
6543  } else if (const FunctionTemplateDecl* FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*RI)) {
6544  functiontemplate = (TFunctionTemplate*)functiontemplates->FindObject(FTD->getNameAsString().c_str());
6545  if (functiontemplate) {
6546  functiontemplates->Unload(functiontemplate);
6547  functiontemplate->Update(0);
6548  }
6549  }
6550  }
6551 }
6552 
6553 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6554 
6555 void TCling::UpdateListsOnUnloaded(const cling::Transaction &T)
6556 {
6557  HandleNewTransaction(T);
6558 
6559  // Unload the objects from the lists and update the objects' state.
6560  TListOfFunctions* functions = (TListOfFunctions*)gROOT->GetListOfGlobalFunctions();
6561  TListOfFunctionTemplates* functiontemplates = (TListOfFunctionTemplates*)gROOT->GetListOfFunctionTemplates();
6562  TListOfEnums* enums = (TListOfEnums*)gROOT->GetListOfEnums();
6563  TListOfDataMembers* globals = (TListOfDataMembers*)gROOT->GetListOfGlobals();
6564  cling::Transaction::const_nested_iterator iNested = T.nested_begin();
6565  for(cling::Transaction::const_iterator I = T.decls_begin(), E = T.decls_end();
6566  I != E; ++I) {
6567  if (I->m_Call == cling::Transaction::kCCIHandleVTable)
6568  continue;
6569 
6570  if (I->m_Call == cling::Transaction::kCCINone) {
6571  UpdateListsOnUnloaded(**iNested);
6572  ++iNested;
6573  continue;
6574  }
6575 
6576  for (DeclGroupRef::const_iterator DI = I->m_DGR.begin(),
6577  DE = I->m_DGR.end(); DI != DE; ++DI) {
6578 
6579  // Do not mark a decl as unloaded if we are going to keep it
6580  // (because it comes from the pch) ...
6581  if ( (*DI)->isFromASTFile() )
6582  continue;
6583 
6584  // Deal with global variables and global enum constants.
6585  if (isa<VarDecl>(*DI) || isa<EnumConstantDecl>(*DI)) {
6586  TObject *obj = globals->Find((TListOfDataMembers::DeclId_t)*DI);
6587  if (globals->GetClass()) {
6588  TDataMember* var = dynamic_cast<TDataMember*>(obj);
6589  if (var && var->IsValid()) {
6590  // Unload the global by setting the DataMemberInfo_t to 0
6591  globals->Unload(var);
6592  var->Update(0);
6593  }
6594  } else {
6595  TGlobal *g = dynamic_cast<TGlobal*>(obj);
6596  if (g && g->IsValid()) {
6597  // Unload the global by setting the DataMemberInfo_t to 0
6598  globals->Unload(g);
6599  g->Update(0);
6600  }
6601  }
6602  // Deal with global functions.
6603  } else if (const FunctionDecl* FD = dyn_cast<FunctionDecl>(*DI)) {
6604  TFunction* function = (TFunction*)functions->Find((TListOfFunctions::DeclId_t)FD);
6605  if (function && function->IsValid()) {
6606  functions->Unload(function);
6607  function->Update(0);
6608  }
6609  // Deal with global function templates.
6610  } else if (const FunctionTemplateDecl* FTD = dyn_cast<FunctionTemplateDecl>(*DI)) {
6611  TFunctionTemplate* functiontemplate = (TFunctionTemplate*)functiontemplates->FindObject(FTD->getNameAsString().c_str());
6612  if (functiontemplate) {
6613  functiontemplates->Unload(functiontemplate);
6614  functiontemplate->Update(0);
6615  }
6616  // Deal with global enums.
6617  } else if (const EnumDecl* ED = dyn_cast<EnumDecl>(*DI)) {
6618  if (TEnum* e = (TEnum*)enums->Find((TListOfEnums::DeclId_t)ED)) {
6619  globals = (TListOfDataMembers*)gROOT->GetListOfGlobals();
6620  TIter iEnumConst(e->GetConstants());
6621  while (TEnumConstant* enumConst = (TEnumConstant*)iEnumConst()) {
6622  // Since the enum is already created and valid that ensures us that
6623  // we have the enum constants created as well.
6624  enumConst = (TEnumConstant*)globals->FindObject(enumConst->GetName());
6625  if (enumConst) {
6626  globals->Unload(enumConst);
6627  enumConst->Update(0);
6628  }
6629  }
6630  enums->Unload(e);
6631  e->Update(0);
6632  }
6633  // Deal with classes. Unload the class and the data members will be not accessible anymore
6634  // Cannot declare the members in a different declaration like redeclarable namespaces.
6635  } else if (const clang::RecordDecl* RD = dyn_cast<RecordDecl>(*DI)) {
6636  std::vector<TClass*> vectTClass;
6637  // Only update the TClass if the definition is being unloaded.
6638  if (RD->isCompleteDefinition()) {
6639  if (TClass::GetClass(RD, vectTClass)) {
6640  for (std::vector<TClass*>::iterator CI = vectTClass.begin(), CE = vectTClass.end();
6641  CI != CE; ++CI) {
6642  UnloadClassMembers((*CI), RD);
6643  (*CI)->ResetClassInfo();
6644  }
6645  }
6646  }
6647  // Deal with namespaces. Unload the members of the current redeclaration only.
6648  } else if (const clang::NamespaceDecl* ND = dyn_cast<NamespaceDecl>(*DI)) {
6649  std::vector<TClass*> vectTClass;
6650  if (TClass::GetClass(ND->getCanonicalDecl(), vectTClass)) {
6651  for (std::vector<TClass*>::iterator CI = vectTClass.begin(), CE = vectTClass.end();
6652  CI != CE; ++CI) {
6653  UnloadClassMembers((*CI), ND);
6654  if (ND->isOriginalNamespace()) {
6655  (*CI)->ResetClassInfo();
6656  }
6657  }
6658  }
6659  }
6660  }
6661  }
6662 }
6663 
6664 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6665 // If an autoparse was done during a transaction and that it is rolled back,
6666 // we need to make sure the next request for the same autoparse will be
6667 // honored.
6668 void TCling::TransactionRollback(const cling::Transaction &T) {
6669  auto const &triter = fTransactionHeadersMap.find(&T);
6670  if (triter != fTransactionHeadersMap.end()) {
6671  std::size_t normNameHash = triter->second;
6672 
6673  fLookedUpClasses.erase(normNameHash);
6674 
6675  auto const &iter = fClassesHeadersMap.find(normNameHash);
6676  if (iter != fClassesHeadersMap.end()) {
6677  auto const &hNamesPtrs = iter->second;
6678  for (auto &hName : hNamesPtrs) {
6679  if (gDebug > 0) {
6680  Info("TransactionRollback",
6681  "Restoring ability to autoaparse: %s", hName);
6682  }
6683  fParsedPayloadsAddresses.erase(hName);
6684  }
6685  }
6686  }
6687 }

6711 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6712 /// Get the list of shared libraries containing the code for class cls.
6713 /// The first library in the list is the one containing the class, the
6714 /// others are the libraries the first one depends on. Returns 0
6715 /// in case the library is not found.
6716 
6717 const char* TCling::GetClassSharedLibs(const char* cls)
6718 {
6719  if (!cls || !*cls) {
6720  return 0;
6721  }
6722  // lookup class to find list of libraries
6723  if (fMapfile) {
6724  TEnvRec* libs_record = 0;
6725  libs_record = fMapfile->Lookup(cls);
6726  if (libs_record) {
6727  const char* libs = libs_record->GetValue();
6728  return (*libs) ? libs : 0;
6729  }
6730  else {
6731  // Try the old format...
6732  TString c = TString("Library.") + cls;
6733  // convert "::" to "@@", we used "@@" because TEnv
6734  // considers "::" a terminator
6735  c.ReplaceAll("::", "@@");
6736  // convert "-" to " ", since class names may have
6737  // blanks and TEnv considers a blank a terminator
6738  c.ReplaceAll(" ", "-");
6739  // Use TEnv::Lookup here as the rootmap file must start with Library.
6740  // and do not support using any stars (so we do not need to waste time
6741  // with the search made by TEnv::GetValue).
6742  TEnvRec* libs_record = 0;
6743  libs_record = fMapfile->Lookup(c);
6744  if (libs_record) {
6745  const char* libs = libs_record->GetValue();
6746  return (*libs) ? libs : 0;
6747  }
6748  }
6749  }
6750  return 0;
6751 }
6752 
6753 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6754 /// Get the list a libraries on which the specified lib depends. The
6755 /// returned string contains as first element the lib itself.
6756 /// Returns 0 in case the lib does not exist or does not have
6757 /// any dependencies.
6758 
6759 const char* TCling::GetSharedLibDeps(const char* lib)
6760 {
6761  if (!fMapfile || !lib || !lib[0]) {
6762  return 0;
6763  }
6764  TString libname(lib);
6765  Ssiz_t idx = libname.Last('.');
6766  if (idx != kNPOS) {
6767  libname.Remove(idx);
6768  }
6769  TEnvRec* rec;
6770  TIter next(fMapfile->GetTable());
6771  size_t len = libname.Length();
6772  while ((rec = (TEnvRec*) next())) {
6773  const char* libs = rec->GetValue();
6774  if (!strncmp(libs, libname.Data(), len) && strlen(libs) >= len
6775  && (!libs[len] || libs[len] == ' ' || libs[len] == '.')) {
6776  return libs;
6777  }
6778  }
6779  return 0;
6780 }

6810 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6811 /// Refresh the list of include paths known to the interpreter and return it
6812 /// with -I prepended.
6813 
6814 const char* TCling::GetIncludePath()
6815 {
6816  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
6817 
6818  fIncludePath = "";
6819 
6820  llvm::SmallVector<std::string, 10> includePaths;//Why 10? Hell if I know.
6821  //false - no system header, true - with flags.
6822  fInterpreter->GetIncludePaths(includePaths, false, true);
6823  if (const size_t nPaths = includePaths.size()) {
6824  assert(!(nPaths & 1) && "GetIncludePath, number of paths and options is not equal");
6825 
6826  for (size_t i = 0; i < nPaths; i += 2) {
6827  if (i)
6828  fIncludePath.Append(' ');
6829  fIncludePath.Append(includePaths[i].c_str());
6830 
6831  if (includePaths[i] != "-I")
6832  fIncludePath.Append(' ');
6833  fIncludePath.Append('"');
6834  fIncludePath.Append(includePaths[i + 1], includePaths[i + 1].length());
6835  fIncludePath.Append('"');
6836  }
6837  }
6838 
6839  return fIncludePath;
6840 }

7050 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7051 
7052 int TCling::UnloadFile(const char* path) const
7053 {
7054  cling::DynamicLibraryManager* DLM = fInterpreter->getDynamicLibraryManager();
7055  std::string canonical = DLM->lookupLibrary(path);
7056  if (canonical.empty()) {
7057  canonical = path;
7058  }
7059  // Unload a shared library or a source file.
7060  cling::Interpreter::CompilationResult compRes;
7061  HandleInterpreterException(fMetaProcessor, Form(".U %s", canonical.c_str()), compRes, /*cling::Value*/0);
7062  return compRes == cling::Interpreter::kFailure;
7063 }
7064 
7065 std::unique_ptr<TInterpreterValue> TCling::MakeInterpreterValue() const {
7066  return std::unique_ptr<TInterpreterValue>(new TClingValue);
7067 }

7078 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7079 /// Get the interpreter value corresponding to the statement.
7080 int TCling::Evaluate(const char* code, TInterpreterValue& value)
7081 {
7082  auto V = reinterpret_cast<cling::Value*>(value.GetValAddr());
7083  auto compRes = fInterpreter->evaluate(code, *V);
7084  return compRes!=cling::Interpreter::kSuccess ? 0 : 1 ;
7085 }
