7088 
7089 void TCling::RegisterTemporary(const TInterpreterValue& value)
7090 {
7091  using namespace cling;
7092  const Value* V = reinterpret_cast<const Value*>(value.GetValAddr());
7093  RegisterTemporary(*V);
7094 }
7095 
7096 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7097 /// Register value as a temporary, extending its lifetime to that of the
7098 /// interpreter. This is needed for TCling's compatibility interfaces
7099 /// returning long - the address of the temporary objects.
7100 /// As such, "simple" types don't need to be stored; they are returned by
7101 /// value; only pointers / references / objects need to be stored.
7102 
7103 void TCling::RegisterTemporary(const cling::Value& value)
7104 {
7105  if (value.isValid() && value.needsManagedAllocation()) {
7106  R__LOCKGUARD(gInterpreterMutex);
7107  fTemporaries->push_back(value);
7108  }
7109 }
7110 
7111 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7112 /// If the interpreter encounters Name, check whether that is an object ROOT
7113 /// could retrieve. To not re-read objects from disk, cache the name/object
7114 /// pair for a given LookupCtx.
7115 
7116 TObject* TCling::GetObjectAddress(const char *Name, void *&LookupCtx)
7117 {
7118  // The call to FindSpecialObject might induces any kind of use
7119  // of the interpreter ... (library loading, function calling, etc.)
7120  // ... and we _know_ we are in the middle of parsing, so let's make
7121  // sure to save the state and then restore it.
7122 
7123  if (gDirectory) {
7124  auto iSpecObjMap = fSpecialObjectMaps.find(gDirectory);
7125  if (iSpecObjMap != fSpecialObjectMaps.end()) {
7126  auto iSpecObj = iSpecObjMap->second.find(Name);
7127  if (iSpecObj != iSpecObjMap->second.end()) {
7128  LookupCtx = gDirectory;
7129  return iSpecObj->second;
7130  }
7131  }
7132  }
7133 
7134  // Save state of the PP
7135  Sema &SemaR = fInterpreter->getSema();
7136  ASTContext& C = SemaR.getASTContext();
7137  Preprocessor &PP = SemaR.getPreprocessor();
7138  Parser& P = const_cast<Parser&>(fInterpreter->getParser());
7139  Preprocessor::CleanupAndRestoreCacheRAII cleanupRAII(PP);
7140  Parser::ParserCurTokRestoreRAII savedCurToken(P);
7141  // After we have saved the token reset the current one to something which
7142  // is safe (semi colon usually means empty decl)
7143  Token& Tok = const_cast<Token&>(P.getCurToken());
7144  Tok.setKind(tok::semi);
7145 
7146  // We can't PushDeclContext, because we go up and the routine that pops
7147  // the DeclContext assumes that we drill down always.
7148  // We have to be on the global context. At that point we are in a
7149  // wrapper function so the parent context must be the global.
7150  Sema::ContextAndScopeRAII pushedDCAndS(SemaR, C.getTranslationUnitDecl(),
7151  SemaR.TUScope);
7152 
7153  TObject* specObj = gROOT->FindSpecialObject(Name, LookupCtx);
7154  if (specObj) {
7155  if (!LookupCtx) {
7156  Error("GetObjectAddress", "Got a special object without LookupCtx!");
7157  } else {
7158  fSpecialObjectMaps[LookupCtx][Name] = specObj;
7159  }
7160  }
7161  return specObj;
7162 }
7163 
7164 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7165 /// Inject function as a friend into klass.
7166 /// With function being f in void f() {new N::PrivKlass(); } this enables
7167 /// I/O of non-public classes.
7168 
7169 void TCling::AddFriendToClass(clang::FunctionDecl* function,
7170  clang::CXXRecordDecl* klass) const
7171 {
7172  using namespace clang;
7173  ASTContext& Ctx = klass->getASTContext();
7174  FriendDecl::FriendUnion friendUnion(function);
7175  // one dummy object for the source location
7176  SourceLocation sl;
7177  FriendDecl* friendDecl = FriendDecl::Create(Ctx, klass, sl, friendUnion, sl);
7178  klass->pushFriendDecl(friendDecl);
7179 }

7484 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7485 /// Interface to cling function
7486 
7487 void TCling::CallFunc_SetFuncProto(CallFunc_t* func, ClassInfo_t* info, const char* method, const std::vector<TypeInfo_t*> &proto, Long_t* offset, EFunctionMatchMode mode /* = kConversionMatch */) const
7488 {
7489  TClingCallFunc* f = (TClingCallFunc*) func;
7490  TClingClassInfo* ci = (TClingClassInfo*) info;
7491  llvm::SmallVector<clang::QualType, 4> funcProto;
7492  for (std::vector<TypeInfo_t*>::const_iterator iter = proto.begin(), end = proto.end();
7493  iter != end; ++iter) {
7494  funcProto.push_back( ((TClingTypeInfo*)(*iter))->GetQualType() );
7495  }
7496  f->SetFuncProto(ci, method, funcProto, offset, mode);
7497 }

7503 {

7508  iter != end; ++iter) {

7523 //______________________________________________________________________________
7524 //
7525 // ClassInfo interface
7526 //
7527 
7528 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7529 /// Return true if the entity pointed to by 'declid' is declared in
7530 /// the context described by 'info'. If info is null, look into the
7531 /// global scope (translation unit scope).
7532 
7533 Bool_t TCling::ClassInfo_Contains(ClassInfo_t *info, DeclId_t declid) const
7534 {
7535  if (!declid) return kFALSE;
7536 
7537  const clang::Decl *scope;
7538  if (info) scope = ((TClingClassInfo*)info)->GetDecl();
7539  else scope = fInterpreter->getCI()->getASTContext().getTranslationUnitDecl();
7540 
7541  const clang::Decl *decl = reinterpret_cast<const clang::Decl*>(declid);
7542  const clang::DeclContext *ctxt = clang::Decl::castToDeclContext(scope);
7543  if (!decl || !ctxt) return kFALSE;
7544  if (decl->getDeclContext()->Equals(ctxt))
7545  return kTRUE;
7546  else if (decl->getDeclContext()->isTransparentContext() &&
7547  decl->getDeclContext()->getParent()->Equals(ctxt))
7548  return kTRUE;
7549  return kFALSE;
7550 }

7696 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7697 
7698 bool TCling::ClassInfo_IsLoaded(ClassInfo_t* cinfo) const

8101 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8102 
8103 void TCling::SetDeclAttr(DeclId_t declId, const char* attribute)
8104 {
8105  Decl* decl = static_cast<Decl*>(const_cast<void*>(declId));
8106  ASTContext &C = decl->getASTContext();
8107  SourceRange commentRange; // this is a fake comment range
8108  decl->addAttr( new (C) AnnotateAttr( commentRange, C, attribute, 0 ) );
8109 }

8112 //
8113 // Function Template interface
8114 //
8115 
8116 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8117 
8118 static void ConstructorName(std::string &name, const clang::NamedDecl *decl,
8119  cling::Interpreter &interp,
8120  const ROOT::TMetaUtils::TNormalizedCtxt &normCtxt)
8121 {
8122  const clang::TypeDecl* td = llvm::dyn_cast<clang::TypeDecl>(decl->getDeclContext());
8123  if (!td) return;
8124 
8125  clang::QualType qualType(td->getTypeForDecl(),0);
8126  ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetNormalizedName(name, qualType, interp, normCtxt);
8127  unsigned int level = 0;
8128  for(size_t cursor = name.length()-1; cursor != 0; --cursor) {
8129  if (name[cursor] == '>') ++level;
8130  else if (name[cursor] == '<' && level) --level;
8131  else if (level == 0 && name[cursor] == ':') {
8132  name.erase(0,cursor+1);
8133  break;
8134  }
8135  }
8136 }
8137 
8138 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8139 
8140 void TCling::GetFunctionName(const clang::FunctionDecl *decl, std::string &output) const
8141 {
8142  output.clear();
8143  if (llvm::isa<clang::CXXConstructorDecl>(decl))
8144  {
8145  ConstructorName(output, decl, *fInterpreter, *fNormalizedCtxt);
8146 
8147  } else if (llvm::isa<clang::CXXDestructorDecl>(decl))
8148  {
8149  ConstructorName(output, decl, *fInterpreter, *fNormalizedCtxt);
8150  output.insert(output.begin(), '~');
8151  } else {
8152  llvm::raw_string_ostream stream(output);
8153  auto printPolicy = decl->getASTContext().getPrintingPolicy();
8154  // Don't trigger fopen of the source file to count lines:
8155  printPolicy.AnonymousTagLocations = false;
8156  decl->getNameForDiagnostic(stream, printPolicy, /*Qualified=*/false);
8157  }
8158 }

8216 {

8219  return ft->getTemplateParameters()->size();
8220 }

8223 /// Return the number of required template arguments of the
8224 /// function template described by ft_info.
8225

8227 {

8230  return ft->getTemplateParameters()->getMinRequiredArguments();
8231 }
8232 
8233 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8234 /// Return the property of the function template.
8235 
8236 Long_t TCling::FuncTempInfo_Property(FuncTempInfo_t *ft_info) const
8237 {
8238  if (!ft_info) return 0;
8239 
8240  long property = 0L;
8241  property |= kIsCompiled;
8242 
8243  const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl *ft = (clang::FunctionTemplateDecl*)ft_info;
8244 
8245  switch (ft->getAccess()) {
8246  case clang::AS_public:
8247  property |= kIsPublic;
8248  break;
8249  case clang::AS_protected:
8250  property |= kIsProtected;
8251  break;
8252  case clang::AS_private:
8253  property |= kIsPrivate;
8254  break;
8255  case clang::AS_none:
8256  if (ft->getDeclContext()->isNamespace())
8257  property |= kIsPublic;
8258  break;
8259  default:
8260  // IMPOSSIBLE
8261  break;
8262  }
8263 
8264  const clang::FunctionDecl *fd = ft->getTemplatedDecl();
8265  if (const clang::CXXMethodDecl *md =
8266  llvm::dyn_cast<clang::CXXMethodDecl>(fd)) {
8267  if (md->getTypeQualifiers() & clang::Qualifiers::Const) {
8268  property |= kIsConstant | kIsConstMethod;
8269  }
8270  if (md->isVirtual()) {
8271  property |= kIsVirtual;
8272  }
8273  if (md->isPure()) {
8274  property |= kIsPureVirtual;
8275  }
8276  if (const clang::CXXConstructorDecl *cd =
8277  llvm::dyn_cast<clang::CXXConstructorDecl>(md)) {
8278  if (cd->isExplicit()) {
8279  property |= kIsExplicit;
8280  }
8281  }
8282  else if (const clang::CXXConversionDecl *cd =
8283  llvm::dyn_cast<clang::CXXConversionDecl>(md)) {
8284  if (cd->isExplicit()) {
8285  property |= kIsExplicit;
8286  }
8287  }
8288  }
8289  return property;
8290 }
8291 
8292 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8293 /// Return the property not already defined in Property
8294 /// See TDictionary's EFunctionProperty
8295 
8296 Long_t TCling::FuncTempInfo_ExtraProperty(FuncTempInfo_t* ft_info) const
8297 {
8298  if (!ft_info) return 0;
8299 
8300  long property = 0L;
8301  property |= kIsCompiled;
8302 
8303  const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl *ft = (clang::FunctionTemplateDecl*)ft_info;
8304  const clang::FunctionDecl *fd = ft->getTemplatedDecl();
8305 
8306  if (fd->isOverloadedOperator()) {
8307  property |= kIsOperator;
8308  }
8309  else if (llvm::isa<clang::CXXConversionDecl>(fd)) {
8310  property |= kIsConversion;
8311  } else if (llvm::isa<clang::CXXConstructorDecl>(fd)) {
8312  property |= kIsConstructor;
8313  } else if (llvm::isa<clang::CXXDestructorDecl>(fd)) {
8314  property |= kIsDestructor;
8315  }
8316 
8317  return property;
8318 }
8319 
8320 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8321 /// Return the name of this function template.
8322 
8323 void TCling::FuncTempInfo_Name(FuncTempInfo_t *ft_info, TString &output) const
8324 {
8325  output.Clear();
8326  if (!ft_info) return;
8327  const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl *ft = (clang::FunctionTemplateDecl*)ft_info;
8328  std::string buf;
8329  GetFunctionName(ft->getTemplatedDecl(), buf);
8330  output = buf;
8331 }
8332 
8333 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8334 /// Return the comments associates with this function template.
8335 
8336 void TCling::FuncTempInfo_Title(FuncTempInfo_t *ft_info, TString &output) const
8337 {
8338  output.Clear();
8339  if (!ft_info) return;
8340  const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl *ft = (const clang::FunctionTemplateDecl*)ft_info;
8341 
8342  // Iterate over the redeclarations, we can have multiple definitions in the
8343  // redecl chain (came from merging of pcms).
8344  if (const RedeclarableTemplateDecl *AnnotFD
8345  = ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetAnnotatedRedeclarable((const RedeclarableTemplateDecl*)ft)) {
8346  if (AnnotateAttr *A = AnnotFD->getAttr<AnnotateAttr>()) {
8347  output = A->getAnnotation().str();
8348  return;
8349  }
8350  }
8351  if (!ft->isFromASTFile()) {
8352  // Try to get the comment from the header file if present
8353  // but not for decls from AST file, where rootcling would have
8354  // created an annotation
8355  output = ROOT::TMetaUtils::GetComment(*ft).str();
8356  }
8357 }

8366 /// Interface to cling function

8531 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8532 
8533 auto TCling::MethodCallReturnType(TFunction *func) const -> EReturnType
8534 {
8535  if (func) {
8536  return MethodInfo_MethodCallReturnType(func->fInfo);
8537  } else {
8538  return EReturnType::kOther;
8539  }
8540 }
8541 
8542 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8543 
8544 auto TCling::MethodInfo_MethodCallReturnType(MethodInfo_t* minfo) const -> EReturnType
8545 {
8546  TClingMethodInfo* info = (TClingMethodInfo*) minfo;
8547  if (info && info->IsValid()) {
8548  TClingTypeInfo *typeinfo = info->Type();
8549  clang::QualType QT( typeinfo->GetQualType().getCanonicalType() );
8550  if (QT->isEnumeralType()) {
8551  return EReturnType::kLong;
8552  } else if (QT->isPointerType()) {
8553  // Look for char*
8554  QT = llvm::cast<clang::PointerType>(QT)->getPointeeType();
8555  if ( QT->isCharType() ) {
8556  return EReturnType::kString;
8557  } else {
8558  return EReturnType::kOther;
8559  }
8560  } else if ( QT->isFloatingType() ) {
8561  int sz = typeinfo->Size();
8562  if (sz == 4 || sz == 8) {
8563  // Support only float and double.
8564  return EReturnType::kDouble;
8565  } else {
8566  return EReturnType::kOther;
8567  }
8568  } else if ( QT->isIntegerType() ) {
8569  int sz = typeinfo->Size();
8570  if (sz <= 8) {
8571  // Support only up to long long ... but
8572  // FIXME the TMethodCall::Execute only
8573  // return long (4 bytes) ...
8574  // The v5 implementation of TMethodCall::ReturnType
8575  // was not making the distinction so we let it go
8576  // as is for now, but we really need to upgrade
8577  // TMethodCall::Execute ...
8578  return EReturnType::kLong;
8579  } else {
8580  return EReturnType::kOther;
8581  }
8582  } else {
8583  return EReturnType::kOther;
8584  }
8585  } else {
8586  return EReturnType::kOther;
8587  }
8588 }

8875 
8876 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8877 
8878 void TCling::SnapshotMutexState(ROOT::TVirtualRWMutex* mtx)
8879 {
8880  if (!fInitialMutex.back()) {
8881  if (fInitialMutex.back().fRecurseCount) {
8882  Error("SnapshotMutexState", "fRecurseCount != 0 even though initial mutex state is unset!");
8883  }
8884  fInitialMutex.back().fState = mtx->GetStateBefore();
8885  }
8886  // We will "forget" this lock once we backed out of all interpreter frames.
8887  // Here we are entering one, so ++.
8888  ++fInitialMutex.back().fRecurseCount;
8889 }
8890 
8891 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8892 
8893 void TCling::ForgetMutexState()
8894 {
8895  if (!fInitialMutex.back())
8896  return;
8897  if (fInitialMutex.back().fRecurseCount == 0) {
8898  Error("ForgetMutexState", "mutex state's recurse count already 0!");
8899  }
8900  else if (--fInitialMutex.back().fRecurseCount == 0) {
8901  // We have returned from all interpreter frames. Reset the initial lock state.
8902  fInitialMutex.back().fState.reset();
8903  }
8904 }
8905 
8906 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8907 /// Re-apply the lock count delta that TCling__ResetInterpreterMutex() caused.
8908 
8909 void TCling::ApplyToInterpreterMutex(void *delta)
8910 {
8911  R__ASSERT(!fInitialMutex.empty() && "Inconsistent state of fInitialMutex!");
8912  if (gInterpreterMutex) {
8913  if (delta) {
8914  auto typedDelta = static_cast<TVirtualRWMutex::StateDelta *>(delta);
8915  std::unique_ptr<TVirtualRWMutex::StateDelta> uniqueP{typedDelta};
8916  gCoreMutex->Apply(std::move(uniqueP));
8917  }
8918  }
8919  fInitialMutex.pop_back();
8920 }
8921 
8922 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8923 /// Reset the interpreter lock to the state it had before interpreter-related
8924 /// calls happened.
8925 
8926 void *TCling::RewindInterpreterMutex()
8927 {
8928  if (fInitialMutex.back()) {
8929  std::unique_ptr<TVirtualRWMutex::StateDelta> uniqueP = gCoreMutex->Rewind(*fInitialMutex.back().fState);
8930  // Need to start a new recurse count.
8931  fInitialMutex.emplace_back();
8932  return uniqueP.release();
8933  }
8934  // Need to start a new recurse count.
8935  fInitialMutex.emplace_back();
8936  return nullptr;
8937 }
